title: chuck wagon stew
directions: Trim excess fat off stew meat and save fat to brown meat.
Cut beef into 1 1/2-inch cubes.
Add to hot fat and cook until brown on all sides.
Add tomatoes and onion flakes; cover and simmer for 1 hour or until meat is almost tender.
Drain kidney beans and add salt, chili powder, black pepper, garlic powder, oregano leaves and sugar.
Blend flour with water.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes or until thickened.
Serve over hot, cooked rice.

title: lady baltimore cake
directions: Beat butter and sugar until very light and creamy. Add milk alternately with flour with which baking powder has been sifted. Beat thoroughly and add the beaten egg whites. Bake about 40 minutes in 2 lightly greased cake pans. Fill with Lady Baltimore filling.

title: hot fudge cake
directions: Heat oven to 350 degrees.
In mixing bowl, mix flour, granulated sugar, 2 Tbsp cocoa, the baking powder and salt.
Stir in milk, shortening and nuts.
Pour batter into ungreased baking pan, 9 x 9 x 2 inches.
Stir together brown sugar and 1/4 cup cocoa; sprinkle over batter in pan.
Pour hot water on batter. Bake 45 minutes.
While hot, cut cake into squares; invert onto dessert plates and spoon sauce over each piece.
Serve warm and if you wish, top with sweetened whipped cream.
Makes 9 servings.

title: fresh vegetables with fettuccine
directions: Heat oil in a 4 to 5-quart pan over medium heat.
Add onion and cook, stirring occasionally, until soft (about 7 minutes). Add garlic and mushrooms.
Cook, stirring, until all liquid has evaporated (about 5 minutes).
Add tomatoes and basil.
Continue to cook until mixture is thickened (about 10 more minutes), stirring occasionally.

title: sunday beef and chicken casserole
directions: Heat oil in skillet, add chicken and saute until browned on all sides.
Place chicken in casserole.
Add beef to oil in skillet, saute until brown on all sides.
Add to casserole.
Add onions to skillet, saute until lightly browned.
Stir in flour, cook 1 minute, stirring.
Gradually stir in wine, stock and vinegar. Bring to boil, season with salt and pepper.
Stir in thyme and cranberry sauce.
Stir well until cranberry sauce melts.
Spoon mixture into casserole.
Cover with lid or foil.
Bake in 325° oven for 1 1/2 hours.
Stir in mushrooms, cook 30 minutes more or until chicken and beef are tender.
Serve with wild rice.
Makes 6 servings.

title: marinated sliced tomatoes
directions: Combine all ingredients, except tomatoes, and stir until well blended.
Slice tomatoes and top with dressing.
Cover and refrigerate at least one hour.

title: clumpies (dumplings)
directions: Combine flour, salt, sugar and margarine in a bowl.
Slowly add water forming a soft batter.
Beat for 2 more minutes.
Drop by spoonfuls into boiling soup or stew.
Let boil until they rise to top or float.

title: 7 layer bars
directions: Mix margarine and graham cracker crumbs; press into 8-inch pan.
Layer margarine, chocolate chips, butterscotch chips, coconut and pecans.
Pour Eagle Brand milk over.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes, or until brown.

title: american cheese tubers
directions: Layer in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan 1/2 of cubed potatoes and 1/2 of chopped onion.
Slice pats of butter over layer; sprinkle with pepper.
Place 4 to 5 singles slices over top.
Repeat layer with remaining ingredients.
Add enough milk to cover bottom of pan. Cover pan with foil and bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours until potatoes are tender.
Stir potatoes to mix cheese.

title: diabetic pie
directions: Mix first four ingredients together.
Blend pudding as directed on box.
Pour into graham cracker crust.
Spread whipped topping on top.

title: butternut squash loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Grease a 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
In bowl, combine squash, eggs, sugar and oil.
Remove 1 tablespoon raisins and 1 tablespoon walnuts.
Stir in remaining raisins, walnuts and orange peel.

title: western potatoes
directions: Scrub and slice potatoes very thin (leave the potatoes unpeeled).
Melt butter and mix dry onion soup.
Put layers of potatoes into 1-quart casserole and drizzle with onion and butter mixture.
Add 2 to 3 tablespoons of water; cover tightly.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Bake the pie shells.
In saucepan, mix together the sugar, cornstarch and Jell-O.
Add cold water; bring to gentle boil, stirring often, until thick and clear.
Set aside to cool.
Also, add red food coloring.
Arrange strawberries in pie shells.
Cut large ones in half.
Pour cooled glaze over strawberries.
Chill in refrigerator.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: round steak casserole
directions: Brown
round
steak
in
skillet.
Transfer
pieces
to casserole dish.
Lay
pieces of peeled, sliced raw potatoes on top of	meat.
Add
bay leaves and can of tomato sauce.
Cover with aluminum
foil.
Bake
at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes. Add green beans. Re-cover and bake 20 minutes more. Remove bay leaves before serving.

title: chess bars
directions: Mix together yellow cake mix, butter and 1 egg.
Pat into 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Then mix cream cheese, powdered sugar and 2 eggs together and put into cake pan.
Bake at 325° for 50 minutes.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Dip slices into blended egg and milk. Coat with dry mixture and fry until crisp (in enough oil to cover the coated tomato).
Turn once.
Serve hot.

title: butter pecan ice cream
directions: Combine pecans, white sugar and butter in frying pan.
Cook for 7 minutes, until dark.
Pour out on foil.
Cool.
Break into small chunks.
Combine brown sugar, whipping cream, milk and vanilla.
Pour pecan mixture into milk mixture.
Freeze in an ice cream freezer until firm.

title: fried chicken
directions: Wash and dry chicken.
Sprinkle with seasoning salt (Accent) and black pepper.
In bowl, beat buttermilk and eggs for 1 minute. Pour flour for dredging in chicken onto a plate.
Add seasoning salt and pepper.
Heat skillet and add Crisco to 1-inch deep.
Roll chicken in flour; dip into buttermilk/egg mixture, then dredge again in flour.
When oil is hot, add chicken.
Cover and cook 10 minutes on each side.
Remove and drain on paper towel.

title: the best carrots
directions: Slice and boil carrots until tender, then drain.
Saute onion in butter until tender.

title: old-timey pickled okra
directions: Pack in quart jars:
okra, 1 hot pepper, 1 garlic clove, 1 nice sprig of dill.
Bring vinegar, water and salt to boil.
Pour over okra.
Seal.
Do not open for 6 weeks.

title: mexican breakfast or brunch
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch baking dish with Pam and set aside.
Beat eggs lightly with milk.
Put shells in dish and pour egg mixture and corn on top of shells.
Top with cheese.
Cover with foil and refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes, until set and browned.

title: tomato rice
directions: Saute sausage, garlic and onion about 2 minutes.
Add tomatoes, peppers and tomato sauce, then add cooked rice and hot sauce.
Heat to boiling, then simmer about 2 minutes.

title: iced decaf tea
directions: Fill 1 1/2-quart saucepan 3/4 full of hot water.
Put tea bags in water and bring to a boil.
Take off stove and set for 5 minutes.
Put sugar in a gallon container.
Add hot tea.
Stir until sugar is dissolved.
Add cold water until full; chill.
Pour over ice in glasses.
Tastes just like regular tea to me.

title: chocolate chip walnut pie
directions: Place cookie sheet in oven and preheat to 350°.
In large bowl, combine first 5 ingredients until well blended.
Stir in walnuts.
Sprinkle chocolate chips in bottom of pie crust. Carefully pour mixture over chocolate chips.
Bake 50 to 55 minutes in oven until knife inserted in center comes out clean. Cool.
Makes 8 servings.

title: basic sugar cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a large bowl cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add egg and vanilla.
Stir until smooth.
In small bowl combine flour and salt.
Add dry ingredients to creamed mixture; stir until a soft dough forms.
On lightly floured surface roll dough 1/4 inch thick; cut.
Bake 6 to 10 minutes until edges are light brown.
Cool completely.

title: veal stew
directions: Mix flour and peppers in a large paper bag.
Add veal cubes and shake until cubes are lightly and evenly coated with flour mixture.

title: pumpkin scones
directions: In a large bowl, combine pumpkin and melted margarine.
Mix together flour, baking powder, sugar and spices and add, stirring just to combine.
Drop onto sprayed baking sheet by large spoon, placing scones 1 1/2 inches apart.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes or until lightly browned.
Makes 10 scones.

title: tom mcclain's old fashioned teacakes
directions: With mixer cream sugar and margarine and add egg.
Add soda, vanilla and lemon flavorings.
Add flour; if sticky, add a bit more flour.
Roll out to 1/4-inch thick.
Cut in desired shapes. Bake in 325° oven 10 to 12 minutes or until tan.
Makes 4 1/2 dozen.
May be doubled.

title: apple crumb pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. In a

large saucepan, combine apples, dry pudding mix, water, spices and apple juice. Stir in apples all together. Cook over medium heat until apples soften and mixture starts to boil, stirring often. Spoon hot apples into pie crust. Mix graham cracker crumbs, brown Sugar Twin and pecans. Sprinkle crumbs over the top. Bake 18 to 22 minutes. Serve with Cool Whip or vanilla ice cream or sherbet.

title: pineapple chess pie
directions: Blend and pour in a 9-inch unbaked pie shell.
Bake in 400° oven for 15 minutes.
Turn oven temperature down to 350° and bake another 10 minutes.
Do not overbake.
(The 2 oven settings will prevent the crust from becoming soggy.)

title: aunt sue's lemon squares
directions: Crumble flour and margarine together.
Press into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes.
Cool.

title: hungarian pastry
directions: Beat 2 egg whites.
Set aside.
Cream butter and sugar, add vanilla and 2 egg yolks one at a time.
Sift flour, baking powder and soda; add to creamed mixture a little at a time.
Spread on 9 x 13 inch cookie sheet with sides.
Spread jam on crust.
Add 1/2 cup chopped nuts, and then put beaten egg whites on top. Sprinkle with remaining 1/4 cup chopped nuts.
Bake at 350° for 20 - 25 minutes.

title: pam's sloppy joes
directions: Brown ground meat and onion in skillet.
In saucepan, simmer ketchup, vinegar and sugar for 15 minutes.
Add to drained ground meat and serve on semi-hard rolls.

title: easy beef
directions: Pour soup and brown gravy mix into slow cooker; mix well. Add soup can of water and mix.
Add beef cubes and cook on medium for as much as 8 hours.
Before serving, add mushrooms.

title: split pea soup
directions: Cook peas in salted water for about 1 hour.
Skim off foam and discard.
Saute carrots, sweet potatoes, celery and onions in butter for 10 minutes.
Stirring constantly, add herbs and cooked vegetables for another 5 minutes.
Add to soup.
Simmer for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Add wine and pepper.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: strawberry pineapple salad
directions: Drain pineapple and strawberries.
Save juice for your Jell-O. Heat juice to a boil.
Pour into Jell-O to dissolve.
Pour in pineapple, strawberries and pecans into Jell-O; mix well.
Pour half into bowl.
Let set.
After set, pour half of salad into a bowl and spread with sour cream.
Pour rest of Jell-O mixture over sour cream and let set 30 minutes or until firm.

title: no bake chocolate balls
directions: Melt chocolate chips in microwave or double boiler.
Mix in syrup, 3 cups powdered sugar, nuts, coffee (dissolved in hot water) and cookie crumbs.
Form into 1-inch balls.
Roll in 1/2 cup powdered sugar.
Store in covered container a day or so to ripen.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Cook sliced carrots in salted water; pour over mixture. Better the second day.

title: green rice
directions: Cook in oven at 300° for 1 hour.

title: beef and vegetable fried rice
directions: In a large skillet, brown ground beef.
Add garlic and ginger. Remove from heat, pour off drippings.
In same skillet, add oil. Stir-fry peppers and pea pods until crisp and tender.
Add cooked rice, soy sauce and olive oil.
Mix well and add the cooked beef and onions and heat about 5 minutes.
Ready.

title: cheesy cauliflower
directions: Break off outer leaves of the cauliflower and trim the stem close to the base.
Wash in cool water; shake off the excess.

title: linda hayes' recipe for tirami su
directions: Whip the heavy cream, adding sugar, until a little stiff. Whip the Mascarpone cheese, adding vanilla until soft and creamy. Mix the cheese and cream together.
Chop up the chocolate.
Dip the biscuits, in batches of 6, into coffee until not quite soaked. Place the first batch of soaked biscuits in a glass bowl; cover with a layer of the cream-cheese mixture.
Sprinkle with chopped chocolate; toss in some cinnamon.
Repeat the layers of biscuits, cream-cheese mixture and chopped chocolate and cinnamon two to three times, ending with chocolate and cinnamon.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix well.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour in tube pan.

title: sugarless cookies(diabetic)
directions: Boil together for 3 minutes the water, margarine, dates and cinnamon.
Let cool and add remaining ingredients.
Mix well. Drop onto greased cookie sheets.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Nuts may be added.
One cookie equals 1 bread and 1/2 fat exchange on diabetic diet.

title: yeast muffins
directions: Mix yeast in warm water.
Mix sugar and Crisco in large bowl. Add beaten egg.
Add yeast-water mixture.
Slowly add flour and stir until well mixed.
Place in airtight container and keep in refrigerator.
When ready to bake, drop by spoonfuls into greased muffin tins.
Bake at 400° until brown.
Mixture will keep 3 or 4 days in refrigerator.

title: pork casserole
directions: Brown meat and green pepper in oil in large skillet.
Season with salt and pepper.
Add soups and corn.
Mix.
Simmer while you cook the noodles and drain.
Combine all in casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: chili con queso
directions: Melt cheese into tomato sauce, then add hot sauce.
Serve with Doritos.
Makes 3 cups.

title: chicken rolls
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Separate 1 package crescent dinner rolls into 4 squares.
Pat 1/4 of mixture on middle of each square.
Roll dough around mixture and pinch together.
Place on cookie sheet, sprinkle Italian bread crumbs and Parmesan cheese on top.
Bake at 375° approximately 11 to 13 minutes.

title: maple fruit dip
directions: Blend sour cream with maple syrup well.
Refrigerate.
Serve with any prepared fresh fruit in season.

title: applesauce cookies
directions: Cream together butter and sugars.
Add almond extract, eggs, vanilla and applesauce.
Mix well.
Blend in flour, oatmeal, baking soda and almonds.
If desired, add pecan pieces and raisins.
Drop by teaspoons onto Teflon coated cookie sheet and bake at 360° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Servings:

title: chocolate caramel pecan squares
directions: Line a baking sheet with graham crackers.
In a saucepan, melt the candy with whipping cream until candy is melted.
Pour over graham crackers.
While candy is still warm, press pecans into candy.
Cool, cut into squares and serve.

title: lemon delight
directions: Mix together cake mix and pudding mix, then add lemon flavoring, eggs, water and buttermilk. Mix well. Bake at 350° in a bundit pan for 35-40 minutes.

title: barbecue
directions: Cook meat until tender.
Pour sauce in with it.
Cook until all ingredients are done.

title: lemon lush(make one day ahead)
directions: Cream and spread in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.

title: old time bread pudding
directions: Put into greased 1 1/2-quart baking dish, the buttered toast squares.
Sprinkle over the seedless raisins.
Pour over toast a mixture of the beaten eggs, sugar, salt, milk, boiling water and vanilla.
Let stand 10 minutes, then sprinkle with 4 teaspoons sugar and 1/4 teaspoon cinnamon.
Bake in moderately slow oven (350°) for 30 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: crab and pasta salad
directions: Bring a large pot of lightly salted water to a boil. Cook pasta shells 10 - 12 minutes, until done, and drain. In a bowl, blend the sour cream, mayonnaise, lemon juice, honey mustard and dill. Season with salt and pepper. In a large bowl, toss together the cooked pasta, sour cream mixture, crab meat, red bell pepper, green bell pepper and green onions. Cover and chill until serving.

title: oatmeal biscuits(obviously a very old recipe.)
directions: Take the oatmeal, flour, baking powder, mix with butter and milk made hot in a saucepan.
Roll out quickly and bake in very thin cakes.

title: taco soup
directions: Cook beef, add onions and drain.
Add rest of ingredients. Simmer 1 hour.
Top with sour cream, grated cheese or crushed corn chips.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix the ingredients and refrigerate.

title: lemon-baked chicken
directions: Skin chicken.
Rub 1 teaspoon of butter on each breast. Sprinkle pepper, salt, paprika and parsley on breasts after applying lemon juice.
Put 2 tablespoons of water in pan to prevent sticking.
Bake at 425° for 35 minutes or until done in a 9 x 9-inch baking pan.
Serves 4.

title: noodle side dish
directions: Cook noodles and drain.
While still hot, stir in cottage cheese and sour cream and continue to stir until cottage cheese melts.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Makes a good side dish to complement any meat dish.

title: vegetable or chip dip
directions: Mix well and allow to set a few hours or overnight.

title: ground beef and noodle casserole
directions: Pour this over 3 cups cooked noodles (8 ounce package) in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Then add 1 cup Mozzarella cheese on top.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: beef and sausage casserole
directions: Cook rice, set aside.
Cook sausage, beef and onion, drain. Combine meat rice and remaining ingredients, except almonds or cheese.
Spoon into lightly greased 12 x 8 x 2 baking dish. Sprinkle with almonds or grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: gary's famous chili
directions: Brown meat in pan. Remove and drain fat.
In pan, saute onions and peppers in olive oil.

Add meat back into pan and simmer 10 to 15 minutes. Add oregano, basil, chili powder, cumin, salt and pepper to taste. Add tomatoes, tomato paste, 1 can of water from paste can, Tabasco sauce, vinegar and brown sugar. Simmer 45 minutes, stirring often.
Drain beans (except baked beans) and add to pot. Simmer 15 minutes. Serve in bowl sprinkled with Monterey Jack cheese.
Serve with hard bread or French bread.

title: quiche 1
directions: Toss cheese with flour.
Add half and half, eggs, shrimp and seasonings.
Mix well.
Pour into pastry shell.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes or until set.
Makes 6 servings.

title: orange glazed chicken
directions: Brown chicken on both sides in hot oil in large skillet.
Move chicken to one side.
Add carrots and celery; cook and stir until carrots are crisp-tender.
Meanwhile, mix orange juice, broth, cornstarch, onion powder and salt.
Add to skillet; bring to boil. Reduce heat, cover and simmer until chicken is thoroughly cooked, about 10 minutes.
Stir in rice; spoon marmalade over chicken. Cover; remove from heat.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Fluff with fork.

title: cinnamon muffins
directions: Sift together all dry ingredients.
In a separate bowl, mix together milk, oil and beaten eggs.
Combine all ingredients and cook in small muffin tins (greased).
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes.

title: mushroom and onion chicken
directions: Place chicken in a baking dish.
Arrange mushrooms and onion on top.
Add chicken broth.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until chicken is tender.

title: fried okra patties
directions: Mix all ingredients together into a smooth batter.
Add 2 cups of sliced fried okra.
Drop by spoonfuls into oil which has been heated in a skillet to 400°.
Fry until golden brown, turning once.
Remove with slotted spoon and drain on absorbent paper. Serve hot.

title: veggie salad
directions: Bring oil, vinegar and sugar to a boil.
Pour over veggies and refrigerate.
This will marinate itself.
Keeps for a long time.

title: hot spiced apple drink
directions: Mix well and store in tightly sealed container.
To use, place 1 to 3 teaspoons in cup of hot apple juice.

title: carrot cake
directions: Sift all dry ingredients (except sugar).
Mix oil, sugar and eggs, beating after each addition.
Add dry ingredients to this mixture and mix well.
Add carrots, pineapple and nuts.
Bake at 350° in a greased and floured pan for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Cream brown sugar, white sugar and 1 stick butter.
Add flour, eggs (one at a time), 1/2 cup butter (melted), vanilla and salt. Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Do not overbake.
(This tends to make pie watery.)
Makes 2 pies.

title: pecan chicken
directions: Combine soy sauce, water, ginger, garlic and chicken in bowl. Heat oil in skillet.
Add mixture.
Stir-fry until chicken is cooked and soy sauce mixture coats chicken (approximately 5 to 8 minutes).
Add onion, mushrooms, garlic and pecans.
Cook 3 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: new york style spinach tortellini
directions: Bring chicken broth and water to a boil.
Add spinach, stewed tomatoes and tortellini.
Cook until done.

title: mushroom and brown rice "stuffing"
directions: Rinse, pat dry and slice mushrooms (make about 11 cups).
In a large saucepot, melt one-third of the butter.
Add about one-third of the mushrooms; saute until golden, about 3 minutes.
Remove with a slotted spoon.
Repeat 2 more times with remaining mushrooms and butter.
Return mushrooms to saucepot.
Add beef broth, salt, thyme, sage and black pepper; bring to a boil.
Add walnuts, raisins and scallions; continue to simmer until rice is tender, about 10 minutes.
If desired, spoon mushrooms and brown rice mixture into cavity.
Roast following favorite directions.
Yield: 12 cups.

title: rye bread appetizers
directions: Spread Miracle Whip dressing onto rye bread.
Mix all other ingredients together and spread on the bread.
Toast at 350 degrees until the cheese is melted.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Saute onion in small amount of butter.
Drain any water off of spinach and add to onion.
Add cottage cheese and eggs.
Pour into casserole dish and sprinkle Cheddar cheese and bacon bits on top. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: gingerbread mixture
directions: Sift together twice all ingredients except shortening.
Cut shortening into dry ingredients with 2 knives or pastry blender until mixture resembles cornmeal.
Store in a tight jar or can in refrigerator.
Makes enough mixture for 6 to 8-inch square pan of gingerbread.
The mixture will keep 3 months, as long as shortening stays sweet.

title: m&m cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Stir together flour, baking soda and salt. In a large bowl cream butter, Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Beat until light and fluffy, add dry ingredients; fold in by hand 1 1/2 cups of nuts.
Decorate cookies with the M&M's. Bake 10 to 12 minutes.
Cool on wire rack.

title: quick candied yams
directions: Place yams in shallow baking dish.
Combine syrup from can, sugar and butter in saucepan, stirring to boil, to thicken.
Pour sauce over yams.
Bake in a 350° oven for 20 to 30 minutes, basting frequently.
Sprinkle lightly with ground cinnamon and/or nutmeg.

title: frozen fruit dessert
directions: Cream the cream cheese, lemon juice and juice from cocktail in one bowl.
Whip the whipping cream; add creamed mixture.
Put in cube trays, then fill in fruit.

title: rocks cookies
directions: Mix shortening, sugar and eggs until smooth.
Blend dry ingredients and add to mixture.
Beat until well mixed.
Add raisins and nuts; blend well.
Drop by teaspoons on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes about 5 dozen 2-inch cookies.

title: roast opossum
directions: Clean the 'possum by scalding and scraping.
Chill overnight. Parboil in a large vessel in a large quantity of water to which has been added 1 teaspoon of baking soda.
Cook until tender. This does two things, cooks out much of the fat grease and makes the meat tender.

title: "blender" custard pie
directions: Mix all ingredients in blender 5 minutes.
Pour into greased and floured 10 or 11-inch pie pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: creole string beans
directions: Cook bacon until crisp, remove from skillet.
Add onion and green pepper to 3 tablespoons bacon drippings.
Cook until tender. Blend in flour, sugar, Worcestershire sauce, salt, pepper and mustard.
Add tomatoes and juice.
Cook, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Add beans.
Heat crumbled bacon and stir.

title: cherry delight
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients and press into a 9 x 13 pan.
Beat cream cheese, eggs, sugar and vanilla together until fluffy and pour into crust.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes until set. Cool for 2 hours.
When completely cooled, top with pie filling. Can put any flavor you like to change it.

title: dirt cake
directions: Crush cookies.
Line dish 13 x 9 x 2-inch with half of cookies.
Mix sugar, vanilla and cream cheese until smooth.
Add pudding mix and milk.
Beat until creamy.
Pour over cookies.
Add remainder of cookies.
Press the cookies down.
Cover with Cool Whip.
Top with nuts or crushed cookies.
Chill overnight.

title: crock-pot ribs (easy)
directions: Place frozen ribs in crock-pot in the morning.
Pour in jar of barbecue sauce.
Fill barbecue sauce jar halfway with water and shake.
Pour over ribs.
Add peeled onion.
Cook all day on low heat.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Toss with Sauce.

title: rice chicken
directions: Mix
well,
all
soups
and water; add rice and pour in large casserole dish that has been buttered.
Place chicken on top. Sprinkle
with
paprika.
Preheat
oven
Cover dish tightly with
foil.
Bake 1 1/2 hours, uncover and bake 1 more hour.

title: caribbean pumpkin soup
directions: Dice vegetables and saut in oil till just tender.
Drain off oil.
Add rest of ingredients except salt and pepper and bring to a boil.
Simmer uncovered 1/2 hour.
Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: chili-corn muffins
directions: Combine dry ingredients. Add grated cheese. Mix. Beat eggs. Add corn, buttermilk, oil and green chiles. Add to dry ingredients. Mix well. Spoon into greased muffin tins. Bake at 400° for 25 minutes or until brown around edges. Serve with Pinto Bean Stew without meat for complete protein.

title: grandmother's stack cake
directions: Sift 4 cups flour into a large mixing bowl.
Make a "well" in center.
Pour in sugar, beaten eggs, shortening, butter and vanilla.
Add buttermilk gradually, working all ingredients into flour.
Add more flour until a stiff dough is formed.
Chill for at least 30 minutes.

title: mallo-smooth fudge
directions: Mix sugar, butter, milk and marshmallow cream in 1 quart pan. Bring to full boil for 5 minutes; stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and add chocolate chips.
Stir until melted and smooth. Add nuts and vanilla.
Pour into lightly greased 8 inch square pan; cool.
Note: Scorches very easy.

title: cheesy potato soup
directions: Melt butter.
Blend in flour.
Add milk, broth, salt and paprika.
Cook and stir until thick and bubbly.
Reduce heat.
Add cheese.
Stir to melt.
Add potatoes, onions and bacon bits. Simmer 15 minutes.
Serves six.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Mix sugar and flour. Melt oleo, cocoa and water. Bring to boil. Gradually pour over flour and sugar. Then add eggs, soda, salt, buttermilk and vanilla. Bake in layer pan at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: chicken noodle bake
directions: Cook noodles until tender.
Drain.
Add next 3 ingredients; put buttered crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° until bubbly and brown.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Mix dry pudding mix with crushed pineapple, then add all other ingredients.

title: southwestern chili dip
directions: Let butter and cheese spread soften to room temperature.
Mix together the mayo, garlic and seasoned salt.
Add crab meat. Spread on split English muffins.
Freeze 10 minutes if for immediate use, then cut into quarters.
Broil until bubbly-crispy or freeze.
When ready to use, cut, then broil.

title: hot fudge chocolate cake
directions: In large bowl, combine sugar, eggs and Crisco oil; beat until smooth.
In a saucepan, combine butter, water, cocoa and salt. Bring to boil and set aside.
Add to ingredients in large bowl buttermilk, flour, soda and vanilla.
Combine mixture in saucepan to mixture in bowl.
Do not use mixer after adding hot chocolate from saucepan.
Pour into 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: party cheese ball
directions: Let cream cheese set at room temperature 1/2 hour.
Blend with mixer until creamy.
Add crushed pineapple (drained), finely chopped onion and seasoned salt and blend.
Add green peppers and nuts.
Shape into a ball, roll in chopped nuts and garnish with parsley or paprika.
Serve with crackers or celery.
Let set overnight for the best blend of ingredients.
To reduce fat, use nonfat cream cheese, still tastes great!

title: microwave cheesy chicken wings
directions: Wash chicken; combine cracker crumbs or bread crumbs with cheese and seasonings.
Dip chicken in butter, then in seasonings mixture.
Then put wings in microwave-safe baking dish.
Place thicker parts of chicken towards the outside of dish.
Cover with double paper toweling.
Bake chicken at High power for about 9 minutes.
Then rearrange wings and microwave for another 6 to 7 minutes until chicken wings are tender.

title: fresh fruit pizza
directions: Make cookie dough and spread on a 14-inch greased pizza pan and prick with a fork.
Then bake 15 minutes or until done.
Cool.
Mix softened cream cheese, whipped topping, vanilla, and lemon juice Beat well.
Spread on bake cookie.
Then arrange fruit on top. Examples of fruit to use:
strawberries, fresh pineapple, grapes, raspberries, blackberries, bananas, peaches, kiwi, or any fruit that you want or that is in season.
Use Fruit Fresh on bananas and peaches so they don't get brown.
Watermelon, cantaloupe, or honey dew may also be used.

title: summer cooler
directions: Heat 2 cups of the pineapple juice and the sugar over medium flame, stirring constantly, to dissolve sugar.
Mix with remaining pineapple juice, cranberry juice and lemon juice.
Refrigerate. When ready to serve, mix chilled juices, water, almond extract and ginger ale in punch bowl.
Makes 35 (6-ounce) servings.

title: mom's raw ripe tomato relish
directions: Chop tomatoes and drain them overnight in a colander set in a large, deep container.
Chop the green, pepper, onions and celery and mix them together and stir them into the drained tomatoes. Mix the remaining ingredients and pour over the vegetables.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix undrained pineapple with pudding mix by pouring into pineapple.
Stir in rest of ingredients.
Stir by hand.
Cool.

title: frozen strawberry delight
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Combine muffin mix and butter.
Pat into an ungreased 8-inch square pan and bake 10 to 12 minutes.

title: crunchy parmesan chicken
directions: Melt margarine in a bowl. Crush Ritz crackers on a piece of wax paper with rolling pin. Dip chicken breasts or pieces in melted margarine and then the crushed cracker crumbs.
Place in greased pan (not overlapping).
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Place in a 350° oven for about 45 minutes or until brown.

title: squash casserole 1
directions: Layer squash and cracker crumbs in casserole.
Mix remaining ingredients, except cheese, and pour over squash and crackers. Top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until brown.

title: pumpkin chiffon fantasy
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients and press into a 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
(Or you can use two 9-inch pie plates.) Combine next 3 ingredients and beat until fluffy.
Spread over crust and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool.

title: rhubarb custard pie
directions: Mix and pour into unbaked pie crust.
Bake at 375° to 400° for about an hour, or until custard is set.
Serve with meringue on top or Cool Whip.

title: salmon ball
directions: Beat all ingredients together.
Form into a ball.
Roll in chopped fresh parsley or pecans.

title: chicken divan
directions: Spray 9 x 9-inch Pyrex dish.
Spread broccoli on bottom. (Fresh broccoli is preferable chopped in 3 to 4 pieces.)
Mix soup, mayonnaise, water, lemon juice, curry and cheese.
Pour over layer of broccoli and chicken pieces.
Melt margarine and pour over mixture.
Top with Pepperidge Farm dressing.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes.
Can easily be doubled.
Use a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Freezes well.

title: buttermilk pralines
directions: Cook sugar, buttermilk, soda and Karo to a soft-ball stage. Just before removing, add pecans.
Remove; add butter and vanilla. Beat until mixture loses its gloss and holds shape.
Drop on waxed paper by mounds.

title: party mints
directions: Mix with mixer.
Roll between 2 pieces of waxed paper.
Cut with small cutter and using cake decorator with star tube make mints.

title: cheese cup cakes
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Line muffin pans with cup cake papers.
Place one vanilla wafer cookie in the bottom of each cup cake paper.
In a medium bowl, cream together cream cheese and sugar.
Beat in eggs and vanilla until smooth.
Pour over wafers in cupcake papers.
Bake in 350 degree oven for 15 minutes or until golden and set.

title: poverty casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except potato chips.
Layer ingredients and a layer of potato chips.
Save a small amount of potato chips for top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: new england chicken soup
directions: Cut up chicken breasts.
Simmer until cooked in soy sauce and maple syrup with diced onion.
Add the other ingredients.
Bring to boil, then reduce heat and simmer 20 minutes.

title: nancy luthy's fix and forget it pork chops and rice
directions: In saucepan, combine uncooked rice, water, undrained corn, carrot, onion and thyme.
Bring to boiling.
Stir in soup. Transfer mixture to 2-quart rectangular baking dish.
Trim excess fat from chops.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Arrange on rice and cover with foil.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.

title: dessert pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spread crescent roll dough on 13-inch pizza pan and pinch seams together.
Bake for 10 to 15 minutes and let cool completely.

title: ono cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch (deep) pan.
Melt butter in microwave in a large bowl.
Mix milk and eggs in separate bowl, then add to somewhat cooled butter (cool in freezer for a few minutes), then add dry ingredients to butter, milk and eggs.
Put in pan and bake for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: lemon turkey stir-fry
directions: Cut green onions into 2-inch pieces; quarter mushrooms. Thinly slice zucchini and red pepper.

title: nut crisp cookies
directions: Mix oleo, sugar and eggs until light and fluffy. Sift flour, soda and salt. Mix with first mixture. Add vanilla and nutmeats. Drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 minutes at 375°. Let cool a few minutes on cookie sheet.

title: champagne salad
directions: Mix strawberries, cream cheese and sugar.
Add remaining ingredients.
Use 9 x 13-inch dish.
Keep in freezer.
Can be made in advance.

title: mrs. ford's spaghetti
directions: Put bacon grease in skillet, add finely chopped onions and brown these two ingredients.
Add meat and cook until redness is gone from the meat.
Do not cook until it becomes browned.
Add chili powder.
(The chili powder will mix better if dissolved in two tablespoons water.)
Add tomato soup and tomatoes.
In a separate pot, boil 2 boxes spaghetti in salt water for about 10 minutes.
Drain and run cold water over spaghetti.
Add spaghetti to the sauce and let it simmer together for 30 minutes.

title: hamburger-noodle casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and drain while noodles are cooking.
Saute onion and green pepper in water.
Drain and add to hamburger.
Add chili powder, salt and pepper. Add tomatoes, corn, olives, pasta shells and cheese.
Mix well.
Pour into a large casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: applesauce refrigerator cookies
directions: Cream together shortening and sugar.
Add egg.
Sift together flour, soda, salt and cinnamon.
Fold gradually into creamed mixture alternately with applesauce.
Add nuts; mix into stiff dough.
Wrap in waxed paper and store in refrigerator.
Slice thin.
Bake on greased cookie sheet in moderate oven at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Yields 14 dozen.

title: peach pie
directions: Cook water, sugar and cornstarch until clear and thick.
Add jello.
Cool.
Pour over fresh fruit and fill baked crust.
Top with whipped cream.

title: tropical fruit cake
directions: Grease a loaf pan and line the sides and bottom with waxed paper.
In a large bowl, place the nuts, dates, and fruit.
Sift the dry ingredients together.
Beat eggs and vanilla until fluffy. Pour over the fruit mixture.
Bake 1 hour and 45 minutes in a slow oven at 300°.
Peel off the paper, cool before cutting.

title: barbecued beef brisket
directions: Sprinkle beef with celery salt, garlic powder, and onion powder.
Place in a shallow dish.
Pour liquid smoke and worcestershire sauce over meat; cover with foil and refrigerate 8 hours, turning once.

title: mexican pizza
directions: Layer all ingredients in baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: lime salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 1 1/2 cups boiling water.
Add marshmallows. When cool, add juice.
Combine nuts and celery with 1/2 cup mayonnaise and cream cheese; add crushed pineapple and whipped cream.
Add nut mixture to jello.
Pour in 1 large greased mold.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Blend pretzels with 2 tablespoons sugar and margarine.
Press in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Let cool.
Blend cream cheese and 3/4 cup sugar together.
Add Cool Whip.
Spread over pretzel mixture.

title: zucchini pie
directions: Stir together all ingredients. Pour into a greased 9-inch pie plate. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Cool 10 minutes before serving.

title: yuletide punch
directions: Boil water with sugar in saucepan until sugar is dissolved. Add cranberry juice, cinnamon sticks and cloves.
Cook over low heat for 5 to 10 minutes.
Cool and strain.
Add remaining ingredients. Refrigerate.
Float lemon slices on top.
Serves 25 people.

title: microwave caramel corn(good and easy)
directions: Place popcorn in large brown paper grocery sack. In saucepan, combine the margarine, syrup, brown sugar and salt. Stir until boiling. Let boil 5 minutes without stirring. Remove from heat and add the soda, vanilla and maple. Mix well (looks foamy) and pour over popcorn in sack. Fold bag top down and microwave on HIGH for 1 1/2 minutes, then shake, then 1 1/2 minutes, then shake, then 45 seconds, then shake and 30 seconds, then shake. Spread out in new paper sack to cool.

title: cheryl's meatballs
directions: Mix brown sugar with vinegar until dissolved. Add ketchup and pineapple chunks. Pour over meatballs that have been placed in a crock-pot and cook on low for 4 hours or until hot.

title: mushroom appetizers
directions: Melt butter (more can be added, if needed) in large frying pan and saute onions briefly before adding sliced mushrooms.
Cook for about 6 to 8 minutes, until moisture disappears.
Add cream and flour (Wondra) to thicken slightly.
Remove from heat.
Season to taste.

title: coconut pie
directions: Beat egg yolks and milk together, set aside. In saucepan, mix together flour and sugar.
Add egg and milk, vanilla and butter. Cook on medium heat until thick, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and add coconut.
Pour in baked pie shell.
Beat egg whites and put on top.

title: soft raisin cookies
directions: Early in day or up to 2 weeks before serving.
Into large bowl, measure all ingredients except raisins and nuts.
With mixer at low speed, beat ingredients until just mixed; increase speed to medium and beat 2 minutes.
Occasionally scraping bowl with rubber spatula.
Stir in raisins and walnuts or pecans until well blended. Preheat oven to 375°.
Drop batter by heaping tablespoonfuls about 2inches apart on greased cookie sheets.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes until lightly browned around edges.
Remove cookies to wire racks to cool completely.
Store cookies in tightly covered containers. Makes about 2 1/2 dozen.

title: mexican chili
directions: Brown meat with green or red peppers (finely chopped or bite-size).
Add onions.
Drain off fat.
Blend in remaining items. Let stew in crock-pot for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
This will enhance flavor.
Serve topped with grated cheese and sour cream and don't forget the crackers.

title: german red cabbage(old family recipe)
directions: Peel off dry pieces of cabbage.
Cut into quarters, remove thick veins.
Soak in cold water for 15 to 20 minutes to refresh. Sliver on cutting board before you soak.

title: hawaiian pizza
directions: Mix the flour, sugar and Crisco; save 1 cup for topping.
Add the remaining dough ingredients; mix together and press onto 1 large or 2 small cookie sheets.
Pinch edges.

title: macaroni
directions: Put water in, then the macaroni.
Cook it about 3 minutes. When it's done cooked put the cheese in and stir it up.
Eat it with a spoon.

title: crock pot macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook noodles for 4 minutes.
Drain and pour in crock pot.
Add remaining ingredients, saving 1/4 of the cheese for top.
Cook on low for 2 hours or until bubbly.
Serve.

title: salt dough
directions: Mix salt and flour together.
Then add water, a little at a time.
Knead 7 to 10 minutes until dough is smooth and putty-like. Mold and shape and then bake at 250° until hard and dry.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix with electric mixer.
Grease and flour 3 small loaf pans or 2 large loaf pans.
Pour into pans equally.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions.
Drain well. Add soup, mayonnaise and water chestnuts.
Sprinkle top with stuffing mix.
Melt butter and pour over stuffing mix.
Bake 20 minutes at 375°.

title: date-apple muffins
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients together.
Add fruit and vegetable to dry ingredients.
Put oil, milk, eggs and vanilla together.
Make a well in the first mixture.
Pour wet ingredients in and stir until moist.
Put 1/4 cup in muffin tins.
Bake for 20 minutes at 375°.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into rectangle baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chocolate chip pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In a large bowl beat eggs until foamy. Mix in flour, sugar and brown sugar; mix well.
Blend in melted butter.
Stir in chocolate chips and walnuts, pour into pie shell. Bake 1 hour.
Serve warm, topped with Cool Whip or ice cream.

title: champagne frozen dessert
directions: Whip Cool Whip, cream cheese and sugar.
Add chopped walnuts, crushed pineapple, strawberries and bananas.
Put in an oblong or square pan.
Freeze.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour into pie shell and bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: mixed vegetable casserole
directions: Mix vegetables, cheese, mayonnaise, celery and onion together and place in greased casserole dish.
Melt oleo, mix with crackers and spread over top.
Bake about 30 minutes at 350° or until done.

title: sweet and sour carrots
directions: Wash and peel carrots.
Cut in rounds about 1/4-inch thick. Cook in small amount of salted water until tender (approximately 15 minutes).
Boil liquid ingredients and spices for 15 minutes. Drain carrots.
Layer 1/2 carrots, onions and peppers; pour half the sauce on.
Then repeat.
Refrigerate one night or longer.
A week of marinating is best for full flavor.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Crust:
Mix butter and flour together until crumbly.
Add 1/2 c. of nuts.
Pat mixture into 8x12-inch dish.
Bake at 300° for 15 minutes.
Cool.
Second Layer:
Combine cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Beat well.
Fold in half of whipped topping.
Pour it onto cooled crust.
Third Layer:
Combine pudding and milk.
Beat until set.
Spread over second layer.
Forth Layer:
Spread remaining whipped topping on top.
Sprinkle top with 1/2 c. nuts. Refrigerate several hours before serving.

title: easy brownies
directions: Melt chocolate, oleo and butter flavoring together.
Blend gently by hand the sugar, flour, eggs and vanilla.
Stir in chocolate mixture.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: red and green salad
directions: Dissolve lime Jell-O
in 1 cup hot water.
Place in top of double
boiler.
Add
marshmallows and stir until marshmallows are almost
completely
dissolved.
Remove from heat and add pineapple and juice.
Stir until cool and add lemon juice. Blend softened
cream
cheese
with
mayonnaise and stir until cooled into the
cool
pineapple
and
juice.
Fold
in
cream (lightly whipped).
Pour
into
9-inch square glass dish.
Set in refrigerator until	mixture
gets lightly firm and top with cherry-flavored Jell-O (2
cups hot water and 1 package cherry Jell-O).
Congeal slightly before pouring over mixture.

title: date nut bread
directions: Pour 1 cup boiling water over dates; let cool.
Heat oven to 350°.
Butter an 8 1/2 x 4 1/2-inch loaf pan.
Mix flour, soda and salt.
Beat butter, sugar and vanilla until creamy.
Beat in eggs, one at a time; beat well after each.
Beat in flour mixture alternately with date mixture.
Stir in nuts.
Pour into pan; bake until toothpick stuck in center comes out clean, about 1 hour. Cool 10 minutes before slicing.

title: no better cheese dip
directions: Cook sausage and hamburger; drain.
Add seasoning to sausage and hamburger.
Put in crock-pot; cut up cheese in chunks (2 small blocks or half large block).
Add soup (no water).
Let everything melt and stir thin; add Ro-Tel.
Put crock-pot on low until hot. Serve with nacho chips.

title: french chocolate
directions: Combine water and chocolate and cook over low flame until smooth, stirring constantly for about 4 minutes.
Add sugar and salt; continue to cook, stirring until thick, about 4 minutes longer.
Cool.
Whip cream.
Fold chocolate mixture into cream. To serve, place 2 heaping tablespoonfuls of mixture in a mug. Fill with hot milk.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and refrigerate overnight.
Serve with fresh vegetables, especially good with celery sticks.
This will keep for a long time in the refrigerator.

title: honeydew, raspberries and cream
directions: In a small bowl, blend soft cream cheese, yogurt and honey. Refrigerate, covered, until serving time.

title: strawberry supreme cake
directions: Bake cake mix according to directions on box.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Mix and bake 20 to 30 minutes at 350°, uncovered.
Serve with chips or crackers.
Recipe can be doubled.

title: hot chicken wings
directions: Cut chicken wings apart at each joint.
Discard tips.
Coat with seasoned salt.
Deep fry at 400° for 12 minutes until browned. Melt butter; add hot sauce and heat in saucepan until warm.
Dip wings in sauce and place on baking rack in roasting pan.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes at 300°.
Serve warm.

title: cranberry delight
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving syrup.
Add enough boiling water to syrup to make 1 cup. Dissolve gelatin in hot liquid.
Stir in cranberry sauce and orange peel. Chill until partially set. Fold in mandarin oranges and pineapple.
Whip the cream. Fold into fruit mixture.
Pour into a 6-cup mold and chill until set. Serves 8 to 10.

title: impossible pumpkin pie(makes own crust)
directions: Mix all ingredients 1 minute in blender, or 2 minutes by hand. Pour into greased large pie plate.
Bake 50 to 55 minutes, until a knife inserted into center comes out clean.
Bake at 350°.

title: christina's pumpkin bread
directions: Combine sugar, oil and eggs. Add pumpkin. Sift dry ingredients. Add to pumpkin mixture.
Mix well. Add water and mix for 1 minute.
Pour into 3 greased and floured loaf pans or 2 tube pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: sweet potato pudding
directions: Mix together and put in baking dish. Add topping.

title: cream cheese bars
directions: Mix together cake mix, butter and one egg to make crust. Press into a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Beat together powdered sugar, cream cheese and 2 eggs and pour on top of the crust.
Bake at 325 for 30-35 minutes.

title: poppy seed salad dressing
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients and onions in blender and add oil, blending all the time.
Stir in poppy seed.

title: broccoli and cauliflower with mustard sauce
directions: Combine broccoli and cauliflower in steamer and cook until tender.
In a medium bowl, blend remaining ingredients with a wire whisk.
Cook in a saucepan until thickened.
Stir while cooking. Pour over vegetables.

title: layered salad
directions: Tear head of lettuce into bite size pieces into bottom of large glass bowl.
Add in layers:
peas, green pepper, celery and onion. Spread mayonnaise over all.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Layer bacon bits and Cheddar cheese.
Cover with Saran Wrap first, then cover with foil.
Refrigerate for 12 to 24 hours.

title: white sauce(basic)
directions: Melt butter over low heat in saucepan.
Slowly add flour and blend for about 3 to 5 minutes.
Stir in the milk slowly, stirring constantly.
Cook and stir sauce with wire whisk or wooden spoon until thickened and smooth.

title: melba cheesecake pie(9-inch pie to be prepared in pie plate cover)
directions: Microwave
butter in pie plate cover 1/2 to 1 minute on Full power
or until melted.
Mix in crumbs and 2 tablespoons sugar; press onto bottom and sides of pie plate.
Microwave on Full power
1 1/2 to 2 minutes or until hot.
Arrange peaches on crust.

title: plantation barbecue sauce
directions: In saucepan, combine all ingredients.
Simmer for 15 minutes. Very good on chicken, beef or ribs.
Makes 2 1/2 cups.

title: buffalo wings
directions: Heat oil in large skillet over medium high heat.
When oil is sizzling hot, add wings a few at a time.
Fry, turning until golden brown, about 8 to 10 minutes.
Remove and drain on paper towels.
Place wings in stainless steel bowl.
Drizzle melted butter over wings, covering each with pastry brush.
Add hot sauce over each wing, spreading with pastry brush.
For mild sauce, use 2 tablespoons; for medium, use 4 tablespoons and for extra hot, use 10 tablespoons.
Serve with Blue cheese dip and celery sticks.

title: graham cracker cookies
directions: Mix all together and put in greased pan with flour.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Take a sharp knife and run around pan; turn over hard on board.
Cut in squares.

title: busy day coffee cake
directions: Place shortening in mixing bowl.
Sift in all dry ingredients. Add half of the milk mix until flour is moistened.
Beat 2 minutes at medium speed.
Add rest of milk and vanilla; beat 3 minutes longer.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: memaw cole's million dollar pie
directions: Mix milk with lemon juice. Add Cool Whip, mixing well after each addition. Drain juice off all fruit. Add to Cool Whip mixture, stirring well. Add pecans. Stir well again.
Pour into 3 graham cracker crusts. Refrigerate at least 2 hours before serving. Break pecans into small pieces. Cut fruit into small pieces.

title: dirt
directions: Mix cream cheese and 1 cup milk, beat.
Add 2 cups milk and pudding.
Beat well.
Add Cool Whip and mix.
Make a layer of crushed cookies in the bottom of the serving container.
Cover with the filling.
Add another layer of crushed cookies (can decorate with gummy worms).

title: au gratin carrots
directions: Cook carrots until crisp-tender. Drain and set aside.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix well with spoon or mixer. Grease medium loaf pan and pour batter. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: irish bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar until white and creamy.
Add eggs and beat well.
Stir in flour and milk gradually.
Add raisins that have been floured and lastly add lemon extract.
Grease and flour 2 loaf pans or angel food pan.
Bake in a 375° preheated oven for 1 hour or a little longer if angel food pan is used. Let cool in pan.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Mix all but cornbread
mix
in a large bowl.
Add cornbread mix one package
at
a
time.
Mixture
will
be a stiff batter. Bake in a well-greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 45 minutes.

title: hot vegetable casserole
directions: Place in an 11 x 7-inch pan in this order: asparagus, nuts, soup, cheese and peas and cover with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Pour rice evenly over bottom of greased baking dish.
Add chicken broth; place chicken in dish and season with salt, pepper and paprika.
Sprinkle onion soup over chicken; spread the mushroom soup evenly over chicken.
Place in 350° oven for 1 hour. Cover with foil; return to oven for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: apple crisp
directions: Butter an 8 x 10-inch baking dish and slice into this the apples to a depth of 1-inch.
Dot with butter and sprinkle generously with the cinnamon candies.
Cover and cook on top of stove for a few minutes.

title: tostado casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Brown beef in skillet and drain off fat.
Add 1 1/2 cups tomato sauce and taco seasoning; mix well.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: In a large bowl, combine cheese, soup, sour cream, onion, 1/4 cup melted butter, salt and pepper.
Mix well.
Fold in hash browns.
Pour mixture in greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Toss together corn flake crumbs and 1 tablespoon melted butter. Sprinkle over casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until golden brown and potatoes are tender.
Makes about 10 servings.

title: chinese chicken wings
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Chop parsley and onions.
Add garlic, vegetable oil, soy sauce and honey.
Marinate chicken in mixture overnight, if possible, or for several hours.
Bake for 1 hour.

title: clever crab
directions: Mix all (except bread) and spread on bread.
Top with bread and cut into mini sandwiches.
Garnish with black olive on a party toothpick.

title: angel food dessert
directions: Make jello with 2 cups boiling water; add the 2 cups ice cream instead of water or ice.
Add fruit.
Pour over cake pieces.
Top with Cool Whip.
Refrigerate.

title: golden glow ambrosia
directions: Arrange
peaches
and
pears
in bottom of baking dish, sprayed
with
nonstick
spray.
Scatter pineapple chunks over peaches and
pears.
Arrange lemon-coated apples in dish. Blot cherries and scatter over other fruit along with pecans.

title: eggplant souffle
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Peel and boil eggplant until done. Mash with potato masher. Stir in butter while hot. Season with salt and pepper.
Stir in eggs, milk, saltines and onion.
Put into casserole and top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes. Serves 6 to 8.

title: honey bun cake
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in mixing bowl.
Beat at medium speed until smooth and creamy; set aside.
Combine brown sugar, cinnamon and pecans.
Set aside.
Pour half of batter in greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Sprinkle half of brown sugar mixture over batter.
Repeat procedure with rest of batter and brown sugar mixture.
Gently swirl batter with knife.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean when inserted.
Let cool completely, then add glaze.

title: ambrosia
directions: Mix ingredients and dip up and put in serving dishes.

title: banana pudding
directions: Layer cookies on bottom; add slice bananas.
Mix milk with pudding mix and fold in the condensed milk with the Cool Whip. Layer this on top of banana and repeat layers.
Chill for several hours or overnight before serving.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream the sugar and shortening.
Beat in eggs, one at a time, and stir in banana.
Sift dry ingredients and add alternately with orange juice. Stir in nuts.
Bake in greased loaf pan from 60 to 75 minutes at 325°.

title: spicy broccoli casserole(makes 6 to 8 servings)
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions; drain. In a large mixing bowl, combine cooked broccoli, onions, mushrooms, pimentos, almonds and cayenne pepper. Pour into a greased 1 1/2-quart casserole dish. Cover with soup; top with cheese. Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: oatmeal apple cake
directions: Combine and set aside the first 5 ingredients.
Combine and stir well the next 4 ingredients.
Add sugar mixture to dry mixture.
Add apples and nuts.
If batter is much too thick, add a very small amount of water.
Spread batter in a greased and floured 8-inch square dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until a toothpick comes out clean.
Serve plain, with ice cream, or with cream cheese frosting.
Double recipe for a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: french dressing
directions: Place all ingredients into a food blender.
Blend on high for 2 minutes.

title: possum pie
directions: Crush Ritz crackers.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Mix in sugar, vanilla, crackers and pecans.
Put in Pyrex dish and cook for 25 minutes at 325°.
Cool completely and add Cool Whip. Sprinkle with coconut.

title: beef and biscuit casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and chopped onion in skillet; drain.
Stir in tomato sauce, chili powder and salt.
Simmer while preparing dough.

title: crosscut pickle slices
directions: Wash and slice unpeeled cukes into 1/4-inch slices.
Discard ends.
Add onion and salt and mix.
Put garlic cloves over top. Cover with ice cubes and let stand 3 hours or overnight.
Drain and remove garlic cloves.
Heat sugar, turmeric, celery seed, mustard seed and white vinegar to boiling.
Add drained cukes and onion slices and boil 5 minutes.
Start to count processing time as soon as water in canner returns to boil.

title: beef and mushrooms over rice
directions: Add the mushrooms, peppers and onions to the oleo and cook 15 minutes in a 12-inch skillet.
Then add the beef, broth and seasonings.
Cook over low to medium heat for 1 1/2 to 1 3/4 hours.
Add the cornstarch to a little water and add to mixture until it thickens.
Serve hot over cooked rice.
Serves 4.
Two hours total cooking time.

title: kahlua
directions: Bring water, sugar and instant coffee to boil.
Simmer 1 1/2 hours.
Let cool.
Add vanilla and vodka.
Refrigerate.

title: burnt sugar pie
directions: In an iron skillet burn 1 cup of sugar until it turns a golden brown.
Add 1 cup boiling water and stir.
Cook until it makes a syrup.
Mix together in saucepan the 1 1/2 cups sugar and flour. Add the beaten egg yolks and milk.
Stir in the syrup and cook until thick.
Add butter and vanilla and pour into two baked pie shells.
Top with meringue and bake until brown or you may let cool and top with whipped topping.

title: hamburger stroganoff
directions: Saute onion and garlic in butter over medium heat.
Stir in meat and brown.
Stir in flour, salt, pepper and mushrooms.
Cook 5 minutes.
Stir in soup.
Simmer, uncovered, 10 minutes.
Stir in sour cream.
Heat through.
Serve over 1 small package noodles, cooked as directed.

title: overnight layer salad
directions: Layer salad in order given.
Cover with lid.
Refrigerate overnight.
Don't mix until ready to serve.

title: potato and sausage soup
directions: To a large stockpot, add potatoes and chicken stock. Bring to a simmer and cook until potatoes are fork-tender, about 20 minutes. Saut pan over medium heat, add sausage and chopped onion in pan and saut until completely cooked. Drain sausage mixture; add celery and saut a few additional minutes. Add sausage mixture to stockpot with butter. Add cream and extra broth, if needed. Add vinegar, vanilla and parsley at end of cooking. Season to taste with salt and pepper.

title: reese's fudge
directions: Mix first four ingredients.
Press into a 9 x 9-inch pan. Melt chocolate chips and pour over top.
Let harden, then cut into squares.

title: anna's cranberry salad
directions: Combine cranberries, sugar and 2 1/2 tablespoons water in blender; blend until all sugar is dissolved and cranberries are chopped.
Drain pineapple and set juice aside for jello.
Mix jello by instructions on box, but substitute juice for cold water. Put jello in 8 x 8-inch dish.
Chill until partially set.
When jello is partially set, combine with rest of ingredients and mix well.
Chill over night or until firmly set.

title: stuffed bacon rolls
directions: Partially cook bacon.
Drain; reserve 2 tablespoons drippings. Set bacon aside.
Cook onion and garlic in reserved drippings till tender but not brown.
In bowl, combine egg and tomato sauce; stir in bread crumbs, mushrooms, onion mixture, parsley, 1/4 teaspoon salt, and 1/8 teaspoon pepper.
Add meat; mix well.
Divide into 4 parts.
Place 2 slices bacon side by side on waxed paper.
Cut another slice in half crosswise.
Place the 2 half slices at one end of bacon slices, overlapping slightly.
Pat 1/4 of meat mixture evenly over bacon; roll up jelly-roll style, starting from narrow end.
Place rolls, seam side down, on rack in 12 x 7-1/2 x 2-inch baking dish.
Repeat with remaining bacon and meat.
Bake at 350 degrees for about 40 minutes for medium doneness.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Blend with fork the softened oleo and flour.
Add sugar. Sprinkle crumbled (lumpy) mixture over fruit in dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until brown.
Sprinkle sugar over hot cobbler.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Store in covered container & refrigerate 4-6 hours before serving.

title: thelma's light rolls
directions: Mix all ingredients, except flour, then add flour.
Let it rise until double in size.
Punch down; knead again.
Let rise again until double in size.
Cover dough with warm wet towel, then roll out dough.
Cut into rolls.
Let rolls rise on pan until double again.
Bake in oven for 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: cajun potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes first until cooked.
Add seasoning and boil about 5 minutes and let set.
More seasoning, the hotter it is.
The longer it sets the better it is.
The recipe is also good for corn.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Make filling by mixing 1 tablespoon flour, sugar, peaches, allspice and butter.
Cook over low heat until butter melts. Remove from heat.
Make crust by mixing remaining flour, Crisco and water in a mixing bowl to form a dough.
Divide into halves. Roll out each half until large enough to fit in a deep pie pan. Put 1 crust in the bottom of the pan.
Pour in filling.
Cover with other crust.
Press edge all around with a fork.
Bake in a 350° preheated oven for 1 hour or until golden brown.

title: company cabbage
directions: Put cabbage, carrots, onion, salt and pepper into slow pot. Pour in chicken broth and enough boiling water to cover vegetables. Cover and cook on high 3 or 4 hours. Melt butter in small skillet; stir in mustard and pecans. Toss to coat. Transfer vegetables to serving dish. Top with butter and pecan mixture and sprinkle with paprika. Makes about 6 servings.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook rice and broccoli (separate).
Fry onion until tender. Mix all ingredients together and stir well.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: spoon dumplings
directions: Add enough milk to make a firm dough.
Drop dough by teaspoons into boiling water.
Cook about ten minutes.
They will come to surface.

title: onion and apple casserole
directions: Peel onions and slice about 1/4-inch thick.
Cook 10 minutes in a covered saucepan in 1/2-inch boiling water and 1/2 teaspoon of the salt.
Meanwhile, peel the apples and slice them 1/8-inch thick.
Drain the onions, reserving the liquid to use later.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake until firm at 425° for 45 to 55 minutes.
Insert silver knife 1-inch from side to test doneness; should come out clean.
Makes 4 (8-inch) or three (9-inch) pies.

title: olive balls
directions: Cut butter into flour.
Add cheese.
Form dough around pimento olives.
Bake at 425° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: chocolate chip cookies #1
directions: Stir.
Put on cookie sheet with spoon.
Cook 50 minutes. Medium.
Take it out.
Put it on a plate.

title: dill bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in water and 2 tablespoons sugar.
Mix all ingredients except flour in a large bowl and beat well.
Then add flour until it is not sticky.
Let raise for 2 hours, then work and make into a loaf and place in a loaf pan.
Oil the top and let raise until double size.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: tuna 'n pasta stuffed tomato
directions: Combine tuna, macaroni, cheese, onion, green pepper, celery and pickle.
In a separate bowl, mix together salad dressing, yogurt, lemon juice and black pepper.
Pour dressing over tuna mixture and toss.
Chill at least one hour.
Remove stems from tomatoes, place each on a bed of lettuce and cut through to within 1/4-inch of bottom to form six equal sections.
Spread sections and scoop in tuna mixture.

title: stuffed cherry tomatoes
directions: Place tomatoes, stem-side down, on cutting board.
Cut thin slice from top of each tomato.
Using small spoon, scoop out tomato pulp; discard.
Invert tomatoes on paper towels; drain thoroughly.

title: perky peas
directions: In medium saucepan, saute celery, onion and mushrooms in margarine until celery is crisp-tender.
Gently stir in remaining ingredients; heat through.
Makes 6 servings.

title: cream cheese cookies
directions: Mix together the cream cheese and butter or margarine.
Add egg and vanilla.
Add 1/3 cake mix at a time and mix well.
(Do not use mixer for last 1/3 of mix.)
Drop on greased cookie sheet with spoon.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Mix and put into a casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes or until liquid is absorbed.

title: hawaiian drop cookies
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder and salt. Cream the shortening, sugar and extracts.
Beat in egg until mixture is fluffy. Blend in flour, fruit and nuts. Drop by teaspoonfuls. Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.

title: chicken divan
directions: Arrange broccoli on bottom of baking dish.
Place chicken on broccoli.
Mix cream of chicken soup (undiluted), mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry powder together.
Pour over chicken. Sprinkle cheese over top.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: homemade brownies
directions: Beat sugar and margarine until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add flour alternately with syrup and beat well.
Add nuts.
Spread in 11 x 15-inch jelly roll pan.
Grease pan with margarine.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: shrimp and wild rice casserole(serves six)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a small skillet, saute mushrooms, celery and onion in olive oil until tender and lightly browned. Combine remaining ingredients, using half of pimientos.
Pour mixture into an 8 x 8-inch casserole dish.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes until bubbly.
Garnish with remaining pimientos and parsley sprigs.

title: chicken macaroni casserole
directions: Mix altogether and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cover dish.
Make in 1 1/2-quart dish.

title: creamy rice
directions: Prepare rice according to directions.
Add soup to desired consistency.
Mix in almond, salt and pepper.
Serve warm.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients and then mix all other ingredients separately.
Combine mixtures and pour evenly in greased Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: caramel popcorn
directions: Mix everything except popcorn and baking soda in a glass casserole dish; put in microwave on High.
Bring to boil.
Let boil 1 1/2 minutes.
Remove from micro and add teaspoon of baking soda and stir with fork until frothy.
Pour over popped popcorn which you placed in brown paper bag.
Close tightly and shake. Place bag closed in microwave on High for 1 1/2 minutes.
Remove and shake.
Repeat this step for a total of 3 times, being sure to shake.
Spread out onto wax paper to cool.
Also may add peanuts to bag of popped popcorn if desired.

title: chicken and broccoli casserole
directions: Boil broccoli until tender.
Cook chicken with onion, celery and salt.
Butter casserole dish.
Layer broccoli and chicken. Mix soups and mayo together.
Spread over chicken.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve with mashed potatoes.

title: crab dip
directions: Mix this together and chill overnight.
When ready to serve, pour this mixture over it:

title: pork chop and potato scallops
directions: In skillet, brown chops.
Blend soup, sour cream, water and parsley.
In 2-quart casserole, alternate with layers of potatoes. Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Top with pork chops. Cover and bake at 375° for 1 1/2 hours.
It is best if left in oven for 1/2 hour or longer. Great dish for hubby who is always late coming home from work.
Makes 4 servings.

title: cheddar cheese ball
directions: Get Cheddar, cream cheese and onion to room temperature.
Beat with mixer.
Add mayonnaise and lemon juice.
Refrigerate 2 hours, then shape into ball.
Roll in pecan meal, if desired.
Set out 1/2 hour before serving.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour in greased casserole. Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: stuffed cabbage rolls
directions: Parboil entire cabbage in salt water. Separate 12 large leaves which will be used to wrap rolls. Mix salt, pepper, sage, onions, bell peppers, egg and meat together. Form 12 meatballs. Wrap each ball in a cabbage leaf. "If they don't want to stay together, I push a tooth pick thru." Place into a greased baking dish. Bake covered with heavy foil, for 30 minutes. Remove cover, pour tomato sauce over rolls, and recover with foil. Bake for an additional 30 minutes.
Drain the rolls and serve.

title: fish etouffee
directions: Rehydrate etouffee mix in 1 cup water.
Slowly add rehydrated mixture to 1/2 cup melted butter, stirring until well blended. Add crabmeat and simmer 10 minutes.

title: banana oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine butter and sugar until creamy.
Beat in egg.
In a bowl, combine dry ingredients, except rolled oats.
Stir into butter mixture thoroughly.
Blend in bananas, walnuts and rolled oats.
Using teaspoon, drop batter onto greased cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Yields 5 dozen.

title: taco casserole
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Drain and add seasoning mix and water. Cook on low for a few minutes.
Melt cheese and add tomatoes and mushroom soup.

title: a.1.-derful chicken(makes 4 servings)
directions: In medium bowl, combine dressing, steak sauce, apricot preserves and onion soup mix.
Arrange chicken pieces, skin-side up, in 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan; spoon steak sauce mixture evenly over chicken.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients with half the nuts, then roll the cheese ball in the rest of the nuts.

title: four layer dessert
directions: Combine flour, nuts and margarine.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Blend together cream cheese, powdered sugar and 1 cup Cool Whip.
Spread on top of crust.
Mix pudding and milk.
Pour over cream cheese mixture.
Top with remaining Cool Whip.
Garnish as desired.

title: tuna burgers
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Fill 6 hamburger buns with mixture. Brush buns with butter.
Bake on cookie sheet in hot oven, 400°, about 10 minutes.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Grease a 10-inch skillet.
Brown sausage and onion; drain well.
In a large bowl, mix egg, corn meal mix, corn and oil.
Pour half of corn mix into greased skillet; sprinkle with sausage, cheese and hot pepper rings.
Pour remaining batter over top.
Bake at 425° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: au gratin potatoes
directions: Place parboiled potatoes in casserole dish. In a boiler, melt butter; stir in flour, salt and milk. Cook until thickened, stirring constantly. Add cheese and cook until cheese melts. Pour sauce over potatoes. Place in 350° oven for 30 minutes. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Pour sauce over sliced potatoes and bake 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350°.

title: broccoli cheese squares
directions: Cook broccoli and drain.
Chop finely (puree in food processor).
Preheat oven to 350° and in glass baking dish (13 x 9-inch), melt margarine in oven.
Beat eggs and add flour, milk, salt and baking powder and mix thoroughly.
Stir in cheese, broccoli and onion.
Pour into dish, spreading evenly and sprinkle top with seasoned salt, if desired.
Bake until set (30 to 35 minutes).
Let stand 5 minutes before cutting.

title: creamy ground beef casserole
directions: Brown beef, stirring to crumble. Drain fat. Stir in tomato sauce. Simmer for 20 minutes, stirring occasionally. Cook macaroni according to package directions. Drain and set aside.

title: turkey buffet casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and add soup and 1/2 can water.
Simmer until thickened.
Prepare rice according to the number of people you are serving.
Place in separate bowls each of the remaining ingredients.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Mix the sugar cookie mix as directed.
Put it on a pizza pan and cook for 10 minutes.
Let it cool.
(Make it look like a pizza.)
Mix together the cream cheese, confectioners sugar and Cool Whip; put on top of cookie crust.
Put the drained fruit cocktail on top, then the fresh strawberries.

title: pumpkin pie cake
directions: Combine ingredients except cake mix and butter.
Pour into pan.
Sprinkle dry cake mix over pumpkin mixture.
Pat down gently with spoon.
Sprinkle chopped nuts.
Drizzle melted butter over cake.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: crock-pot enchiladas
directions: Saute meat and onion.
Drain fat.
Add rest of ingredients, except cheese and tortillas.
Simmer 30 minutes.
Put layer of meat mixture in crock-pot.
Add 2 flour tortillas and top with cheese.
Continue layering until you use all meat.
End with cheese on top.
Turn crock-pot on high until it begins to bubble, then turn it to low for two hours.
Instead of crock-pot, layer in casserole dish and bake 35 minutes.
Start at 350° for 10 minutes, then turn to 335° for 25 minutes.

title: chicken fajitas
directions: Combine spinach, fajita seasoning and broth in deep pan. Heat 5 minutes over medium heat. Put in rest of ingredients; heat until cheese melts. Spoon into warm tortillas and enjoy!

title: lemon squares
directions: Mix until crumbly the butter, flour and confectioners sugar. Pat into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Beat eggs and add 2 cups sugar (regular).
Add tablespoon of flour, lemon juice and baking powder.
Pour over crust and bake 25 minutes more. Cool and cut into squares.
Can be topped with extra confectioners sugar.

title: parmesan oven-fried chicken
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients; set aside.
Dip chicken in salad dressing, then in bread crumb mixture.
Place chicken, bone side down, in 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish that has been cooked with vegetable spray.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: hot cider(microwave)
directions: Combine apple cider, cinnamon sticks, allspice, cloves, molasses and sliced oranges in a bowl.
Heat, uncovered, 15 minutes, stirring every 5 minutes.
Remove cinnamon sticks, cloves and oranges.
Add lemon juice.
Makes 8 servings.

title: tapioca
directions: Measure packing syrups from the fruits.
Add enough water to make 3 1/2 cups liquid.
Cook pudding according to the package directions, using the fruit liquid.
Cool.
Add mandarins and pineapple.
Chill.
Serves 10.

title: crab casserole
directions: Melt butter.
Add all ingredients, top with buttered crumbs.

title: shrimp creole
directions: In
large
stir-fry skillet place oil
or
butter.
Add onion, garlic, celery, tomatoes, tomato paste, water, parsley, sugar, salt
and pepper.
Cook on medium heat for
to
20 minutes. Add shrimp.
Add cornstarch to 1/4
cup
cold
water and stir into mixture to thicken. Cook until thickened.
Serve over steamed rice.
Serves 4.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Cut crust off bread and cut into cubes.
Lightly grease or Pam a 2-quart casserole dish.
Line bread cubes in dish, using 1/2 of bread.
Beat eggs, milk and seasonings.
Sprinkle 1/3 of cheese on bread cubes.
Add another layer of bread and 1/3 of cheese.
Pour milk mixture over bread and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes. Remove from oven; top with rest of cheese.
Sprinkle with 1 tablespoon dry parsley.
Return to oven; bake 10 minutes more.

title: mustard
directions: Mix mustard and vinegar together and let stand overnight.
Beat eggs; add 1 cup sugar.
Mix well.
Add mustard, vinegar and pinch of salt.
Boil mixture until thick, about the consistency of custard, in a double boiler.
Stays fresh quite awhile.

title: crusty cornbread
directions: Mix all dry ingredients.
Add egg, milk and oil.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 400°.

title: ham and cabbage casserole
directions: Boil cabbage until tender with onion, bell pepper, celery and seasonings; drain boiled ingredients and pour into a casserole dish.
Mix evaporated milk and homogenized milk with flour; pour over cabbage mixture.
Add ham and mix well.
Bake for about 1 hour or until the ingredients in the casserole have simmered down at 350°; remove from oven.
Sprinkle with cheese; place back in oven until cheese has melted.

title: eggplant parmesan
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Peel eggplant if desired and cut into 1/4-inch slices.
Dip each slice into eggs, then into bread crumbs.
Saute in oil until golden brown on both sides.
Place layer of eggplant in roaster; sprinkle with oregano, Parmesan and Mozzarella.
Cover well with tomato sauce.
Repeat until all eggplant is used, topping last layer of sauce with several slices of Mozzarella.
Bake uncovered 1/2 hour or until sauce is bubbly and cheese is melted.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: hot cranberry tea
directions: Serve hot in crock-pot.
Add 4 cups hot water.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Prepare Jell-O as on package except put several ice cubes to chill Jell-O to harden.
Take ice cubes out after Jell-O hardens. Pour 1 tub Cool Whip and mix together well.
Combine sliced strawberries with Jell-O and Cool Whip.
Pour into a graham cracker pie crust and refrigerate until firm.

title: cream cheese frosting
directions: Blend softened cream cheese and vanilla flavoring.
Gradually add powdered sugar until it reaches desired consistency.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken and chop in small pieces.
Save broth.
In a large casserole dish, melt margarine and add stuffing mix.
Stir until mix is coated with margarine.
Remove half of mix; add half of the chicken and pour cream of mushroom soup over remaining half of mix. Add the remaining mix and chicken and pour cream of chicken soup over.
Pour chicken broth over this and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: peanutty cereal treats
directions: Place butter, peanut butter and marshmallows in an 8 to 12-cup measure.
Microwave on High for 2 1/2 to 3 1/2 minutes; stir until smooth.
Stir in cereal and peanuts; blend well.
Press into a 9-inch square pan.
Cool; cut into squares.

title: ma thompson's ham and vegetable soup
directions: Boil ham until tender in enough water to cover.
Remove ham from broth, add vegetables to broth and cook until vegetables are tender.
Do not overcook.
Serve with cornbread.

title: whole cranberry salad
directions: Fix jello as directed (omit 1 cup cold water).
Chill until set.
Add cranberries, pecans and celery.
Chill until firm. Yields 8 servings.

title: no-fry fried chicken
directions: Dip chicken in skim milk to which has been added the hot sauce.
Mix cornflakes, paprika, salt and pepper.
Coat chicken in cornflake mixture.
Bake for 40 minutes at 350° in a pan lined with foil and sprayed with Pam.
Brown under broiler for 5 minutes.
Do not turn chicken.

title: greek bread
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Spread on one loaf of Italian bread.
Heat in oven until cheese bubbles.

title: apricot almond bars
