directions: Cream the first 3 ingredients together. Stir together flour, nuts and salt. Add to creamed mixture. Mix until crumbly. Reserve 1 cup for topping. Pat remaining into ungreased oblong baking pan. Combine preserves and remaining ingredients. Spread over crumb layer.
Top with reserved crumbs. Bake at 350° until golden, 30 to 35 minutes. Cut while warm.
Yields 32 bars.

title: no bake cheesecake
directions: Beat cream cheese until smooth.
Gradually beat in sugar. blend in sour cream and vanilla.
Fold in whipped topping, blending well. Spoon into crust.
Chill until set.
Garnish with strawberries or cherries if desired.

title: peanut butter snack bars
directions: Line a 9-inch square baking pan with foil.
In 1-quart saucepan, combine butter, 2 tablespoons peanut butter, honey and brown sugar.
Heat over low heat.
Stir occasionally until smooth and melted.
Pour hot mixture over cereal in large bowl.
Stir well.
Turn cereal mixture into foil-lined pan.
Press down evenly.
Cool completely.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Place in layers in an 11 x 9-inch baking dish the broccoli, 1/2 stick oleo broken into bits and cheese, broken up.
Spread soup over final layer.
Break up the other 1/2 stick of oleo over top of soup.
Place crackers on top and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: apple dump cake
directions: In one bowl, combine the first 4 ingredients.
In another bowl, combine remaining ingredients.
Mix the 2 mixtures together. Bake at 325° for 45 to 55 minutes in greased 13 x 9-inch pan. Serve with custard, ice cream or whipped cream.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 325°. Place 1/2 package of crackers on bottom. Add a thick layer of cabbage. Add milk and butter. Season to taste. Add a thick layer of cheese and the remainder of crackers. Top with a light layer of cheese. Bake for 35 minutes. Let cool. Serve.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Mix soups together with milk and heat.
Cook broccoli and cauliflower.
Mash fine.
Put mixtures together and heat.

title: cheese potato casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a greased dish (13 x 9-inches) place ingredients.
Also sprinkle some cheese on top.
Bake 1 hour.

title: chicken-broccoli casserole
directions: Mix soup, sour cream, milk, lemon juice and curry powder together. Add broccoli, chicken and cheese and mix thoroughly.
Place in a lightly greased 2-quart casserole; top with breadcrumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly.
Yield: 6 servings.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix together; form in ball.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix together and chill.

title: crock-pot macaroni and cheese
directions: Mix all ingredients and place in a greased crock pot.
Start on high, and cut back to low.
Takes about 3 hours.
(I use extra cheese and milk.)

title: sweet and sour pork
directions: Trim fat from pork; cut pork into 3/4-inch pieces.
Mix egg, 2 tablespoons cornstarch, 2 tablespoons vegetable oil, 1 teaspoon salt, 1 teaspoon soy sauce and the white pepper in glass or plastic bowl.
Stir in pork.
Cover; refrigerate for 20 minutes. Cut each tomato into 8 wedges.
Cut green pepper into 1-inch pieces.
Heat vegetable oil (1 1/2 inches) in wok to 350°.
Mix flour, 3/4 cup water, 2 tablespoons cornstarch, 1 teaspoon salt and the baking soda.
Stir pork pieces into batter until well coated.
Fry about 15 pieces at a time until light brown, turning frequently, 4 minutes.
Drain on paper towel.
Increase oil temperature to 375°.
Fry pork all at one time until golden brown, about 1 minute.
Drain on paper towel; place pork on heated platter.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix the sugar and flour. Add the oleo, pecans, chocolate tidbits, vanilla and eggs.
Mix and bake in a 9-inch pie shell at 325° for 1 hour.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Drain all fruit.
Mix all ingredients together except Cool Whip.
Pour into pie shells.
Spread Cool Whip on top and chill for about 1 hour.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix all ingredients well. Drop in hot grease. Fry until golden brown.

title: boston style butt
directions: Place meat in deep kettle; cover with water.
Simmer for 60 minutes per pound or until tender.
Remove from water.
Place in shallow baking pan.
Spread meat with mustard and stud with whole cloves.
Sprinkle with brown sugar.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes or until meat is glazed.

title: chocolate chip pistachio cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake in greased and floured tube or Bundt pan for 50 to 60 minutes at 350°.

title: german chocolate upside-down cake
directions: Mix together coconut and nuts; place in bottom of a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Prepare cake according to directions; pour over coconut and nut mixture.

title: microwave pralines
directions: In
quart
microwave-safe
casserole,
stir together brown sugar,
granulated sugar, water, corn syrup and butter. Cover with lid
or
plastic wrap, turning back one section to vent steam. Microwave at High setting (100% power) 8 minutes, stirring
after 4 minutes.
Stir in pecans and vanilla, cover again
and microwave
minutes more.
Stir in confectioners sugar until well blended, continue stirring for 1 to 2 minutes or
until mixture
begins
to
thicken
and
loses its gloss. Quickly
drop by
rounded
tablespoonful
3 inches apart onto buttered wax paper.
(If mixture becomes to thick to drop from a spoon, stir in a few drops hot water.) Let stand until set.

title: rum cake
directions: Mix in order.
Pour in greased, round layer pan or pie plate. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: broccoli balls
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large bowl. Chill 1 hour.
Roll in balls and bake at 325° for 15 to 25 minutes.

title: mandarin orange mold
directions: Heat 1 cup of apricot syrup to boiling.
Add jello.
Dissolve and cool.

title: dean's chicken and broccoli
directions: Slice up all vegetables and put to the side. Cut chicken up into bite-size pieces. Flour chicken and fry until brown on both sides. In a saucepan, boil chicken broth, soy sauce, garlic and sugar. Reduce mixture by half.
Steam or saute broccoli and onion until tender. Add chicken and sauce; simmer over medium heat for 20 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: baked pineapple
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving 3 tablespoons juice.
Mix flour and sugar; slowly add pineapple juice.
Add chunks.
Pour mixture into greased casserole dish.
Combine margarine and cracker crumbs; sprinkle over mixture.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Line bottom of casserole with round crackers.
Pour melted margarine over.
Mix vegetables and mayonnaise; pour into dish. Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: buttermilk candy
directions: Cream the butter and sugar. Add the buttermilk, soda and Karo. Cook until the mixture forms soft ball when dropped into cold water. Remove from heat and add the vanilla and nuts. Beat well before pouring into 8 x 8-inch pan. Makes 36 pieces.

title: baked parmesan chicken
directions: Combine bread crumbs, cheese and pepper.
Set aside.
Dip pieces of chicken in melted margarine. Roll each piece in bread crumb mixture.
Place chicken in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes only until golden brown.
Yields 6 servings.

title: mary's famous pineapple bake
directions: Drain sliced pineapple, saving 1/3 cup juice. Place pineapple slices in a lightly greased 11 x 7 x 1 1/2-inch baking dish. Sprinkle with cheese. Combine remaining pineapple juice, sugar and flour in small mixing bowl. Pour mixture over cheese. Combine cracker crumbs and butter in small mixing bowl and sprinkle over flour mixture. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until bubbly. Makes 8 servings.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add eggs, mixing well.
Make a paste with food coloring and cocoa and add to mixture.
Add salt and flour with buttermilk and vanilla.
Alternately add soda and vinegar; blend, don't beat.
Bake 30 minutes at 350° in two greased and floured pans (9-inch).

title: banana split cake
directions: Layer over creamed mixture.

title: carrot salad
directions: Add water to carrots and cook.
Drain.
Pour soup over hot carrots.
Add onions, green peppers, celery, Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper.

title: borscht(cold red beet soup)
directions: Boil beets until tender.
Let cool for about 1 hour.
Peel and dice.
In large bowl, place diced beets, diced onion and diced cucumber.
Mix and add vinegar and sugar (mix together until sugar dissolves); add sour cream.
Tie two bunches of dill (with dental floss).
Mix in with the ingredients.
Stir gently.
Cover with Saran Wrap and marinate overnight.
Serve with buttermilk.

title: applesauce meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients and shape into loaf.
Bake at 350° about 1 hour.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Combine all ingredients except cabbage and sauerkraut.
Steam cabbage to loosen leaves.
Separate leaves and roll 2 tablespoons of meat mixture in each leaf.
Fasten with toothpick.
Place rolled leaves on bed of sauerkraut and bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: bread bowl spinach dip
directions: With serrated knife, cut straight down in a circle neat the sides of the bread.
Gently reach in the cut and separate the bread along the bottom, removing a cylinder of bread from the loaf.
Set aside.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Sift flour and measure.
Add soda, salt and spices.
Sift together three times.
Cream butter and egg, gradually adding sugar.
Beat well.
Add nuts and raisins.
Add flour alternately with applesauce.
Bake at 350° in 8 x 4-inch loaf pan.
(For two 10-inch layers, make recipe 1 1/2 times.)

title: banana blueberry bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Mix Bisquick, oats and sugar in a large mixing bowl.
Set aside.
In a small bowl, mix eggs and milk. Add to dry ingredients along with bananas.
Mix well.
Fold in blueberries.
Pour mixture into a well greased loaf pan.
Bake for about 30 minutes or until a pick inserted in center comes out clean.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Mix pudding and pineapple (do not drain pineapple) together. Mix well.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Cover and refrigerate at least 2 hours or overnight, if you wish.

title: pimento and cheese in a bread bowl
directions: Mix thoroughly grated cheese, pimentos, mayonnaise and pepper.
Remove the top and middle section of bread loaf. Fill opening with pimento and cheese spread.
Serve with bread pieces and crackers.

title: mushroom gravy
directions: Make-ahead tip:
Since you don't need meat drippings, you can make this gravy up to 2 days ahead.
Cook's tip:
Cooking the flour until it's a deep caramel color gives this gravy its robust flavor.

title: pigs in a blanket
directions: Mix hamburger, pork, seasonings, egg and rice together.
Shape mixture into medium size balls.
Peel cabbage into leaves.
Hold the leaves under hot water to make them pliable.
Wrap leaves around the hamburger balls.
Place on bottom of large pot.
Pour tomatoes and sauerkraut over these.
Add more cabbage, if desired. Add enough water to fill pot.
Cook, covered, at medium temperature for approximately 1 hour.

title: ham ball
directions: Mix can of ham and cream cheese well.
Add onions and mix. Roll in parsley, refrigerate.
Serve with Ritz crackers or Wheat Thins.

title: mulled cider(microwave)
directions: Place cider, sugar, salt and nutmeg in 1-quart measuring cup. Tie spices in cheesecloth and drop into cider.
Cook on High for 4 to 5 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Remove spice bag and serve hot.
Garnish with orange slices.

title: beef zucchini pie
directions: Brown meat, zucchini, celery, onion, salt, dry mustard and pepper.
Mix milk and eggs until well blended.
Stir into meat mixture.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Smash/cut the artichoke hearts into small pieces and mix with the first 4 ingredients.
Then add the mayonnaise a couple of tablespoons at a time until all ingredients mix well.
Place in microwave bowl and microwave on High for 5 to 8 minutes until hot and bubbly.
Serve with crackers.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Combine cream cheese, margarine and sugar, beating until light and fluffy. Add vanilla or lemon extract and salt.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add flour and mix well. Spoon into greased 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours or until cake tests done. Cool 10 minutes and remove from pan.

title: kathie lee's apricot chicken
directions: Wash boneless chicken breasts and place in a 9 1/2 x 13 1/2-inch baking dish.
In a separate bowl, mix Russian salad dressing, apricot preserves and water.
Pour mixture over chicken and bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.
Remove from oven.
Place pineapple and green pepper on chicken.
Return to oven for 1/2 hour.

title: no cook chocolate chews
directions: Blend butter and corn syrup, then stir in melted chocolate and vanilla.
Mix sugar and dry milk, gradually stir into first mixture, then knead until thoroughly blended.
Shape into 3/4-inch rolls and cut in 1-inch pieces.
Makes about 1 1/2 pounds.

title: sugarless bars for diabetic
directions: Boil the raisins, dates, pineapple and water for 3 minutes. Add margarine to this mixture; let cool.
Mix flour, baking soda, eggs and vanilla; add to the cool fruit mixture.
Add nuts.
Put in a 10 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes, or until done.

title: parfait
directions: Blend fruit into mixture and chill several hours.

title: corn bread
directions: Mix flour, cornmeal, salt and baking powder.
Stir in milk; quantity needed will vary.
Batter should be on the thin side.
Add eggs and shortening.
Mix well.
Bake in a greased pan at 400° until brown.

title: bavarian frankfurter bake
directions: Reserve 4 franks.
Slice the remaining ones 1/4-inch thick. Mix. Mix soup and mayonnaise.
Combine half the soup with the sliced franks, caraway seed and sauerkraut.
Spread in a large baking dish.
Stir remaining soup mixture into potato slices. Spread over kraut mixture.
Combine buttered crumbs and paprika; sprinkle over potatoes.
Cut the reserved franks in half and press into top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Saut onions in butter/margarine. Add green beans, mushrooms, water chestnuts and cream of celery soup. Heat until all is mixed. Pour into a casserole dish. Cover with foil and put into oven at 350° for 45 minutes. Remove foil and put shredded cheese on top and cook, uncovered, for 15 minutes or until cheese is melted on top. Serves 8 to 10.
tags: cream of celery soup or cream of chicken soup

title: ritz cracker pecan pie
directions: Whip egg whites until stiff.
While beating, add 1 cup sugar, a little at a time.
Then add baking powder and vanilla.
Fold crackers and nuts into egg whites.

title: great layered dip
directions: Layer in large plate or bowl with sides, starting with beans. Pour salsa on right before serving.
Serve with chips or crackers.

title: mom's easy cheese rolls
directions: Sprinkle yeast over very warm water in a large bowl.
Add a pinch of the sugar; stir to dissolve.
Let stand until bubbly, about 10 minutes.
Stir in rest of sugar, oil and salt.
Sift 3 cups of the flour with the dry milk; stir into the yeast mixture. Beat until smooth.
Stir in enough of the flour to make a soft but sticky dough.

title: cajun meat pie
directions: Saute onions and bell pepper in vegetable oil.
Add ground beef, bouillon powder and Cajun seasoning.
Saute until done.
Add mashed potatoes and mix well.
Line pie pan with first pie crust. Pour in meat mixture. Cover with second crust. Poke a few holes in the crust. Bake at 375° for 35 minutes.
Mixture can also be used for small individual pies.

title: oyster cracker snacks
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except crackers.
Pour mixture over crackers and mix carefully to coat.
Allow to stand for 1 hour at room temperature, stirring occasionally.
Store crackers in airtight container in a cool place.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Cook the 3 ingredients together until peanuts are done or until real brittle stage.
Syrup gets brown and the peanuts pop. Take off heat and add all at once the soda, melted butter and vanilla.
Stir real hard (it will bubble up).
Pour immediately while still bubbling onto a buttered cookie sheet to cool and harden.

title: vinegar pie crust
directions: Work together flour, salt and shortening.
Whip together egg, water and vinegar, then add to flour mixture.
Divide into 3 balls.
Roll each out on a floured board.
Makes 3 pie crusts.

title: party dip
directions: Mix ingredients together and chill at least 1 hour. Serve with chips and/or raw vegetables.

title: broccoli ham casserole
directions: Saute margarine and onion in microwave.
Combine soup, cheese and milk in pan over low heat.
Add margarine and onion.
Heat until mixed well.
Add rest of ingredients and stir well.
Put in a 2-quart baking dish.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: baked grits with cheese
directions: Cook grits.
Add 1 1/2 c. cheese reserving enough for top. Add eggs and pepper.
Mix well.
Pour into greased shallow 1 1/2 quart casserole.
Top with remaining cheese. Sprinkle with paprika and bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: pork chops and rice
directions: Brown pork chops in shortening.
Remove from skillet and add water and onion soup mix to drippings.
Stir and bring to a boil. Spread rice in bottom of 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Pour water mixture over rice.
Place browned pork chops on top of rice. Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 60 minutes.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: fresh coconut pie
directions: Combine ingredients and pour into an unbaked pie shell.
Bake 350° for 30 minutes or until set.

title: chicken supreme
directions: Cook chicken in boiling water (1 to 2 hours). Debone and cut into bite-size pieces.
In casserole dish, mix sour cream and soup.
Add chicken pieces and mix again.
Make stuffing following package directions.
Put stuffing over chicken in casserole dish. Do not mix together during baking.
Bake, covered, at 350°
for 1 hour.
Serves 4.

title: english dessert trifle
directions: Slice the pound cake.
Cover with fruit cocktail. Pour vanilla pudding over (not instant).
Top with whipped cream or Cool Whip. Quick and good.

title: spoon biscuits
directions: Combine flour and milk.
Stir well.
Add mayonnaise and stir. Butter small muffin tins.
Spoon dough into tins about 1/2 to 2/3 full.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Makes 9 (2-inch) biscuits.

title: potato casserole
directions: Spray pan with Pam and bake for 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Pour boiling water over oatmeal and margarine; let stand 20 minutes.
Cream together sugar, brown sugar and eggs.
Stir into oatmeal mixture.
Add 1 1/2 cups flour, salt, soda, baking powder, nutmeg and cinnamon.
Mix well.
Bake in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan 30 to 35 minutes at 350° until done.

title: russell's beloved spinach lasagne
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown ground beef and drain.
Add the next 8 ingredients and water and simmer for 20 minutes.
Combine Ricotta cheese and drained spinach.
Place a layer of noodles in the bottom of a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Top with 1/2 of Ricotta cheese mixture.
Lay another layer of noodles and top with 1/2 Mozzarella.
Repeat the layers.
Cover pan with foil and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: steak and royal rice
directions: Broil steak at 350° until tender.
Saute onions in butter. Add rice, mushrooms and salt.
Heat thoroughly.
Fluff lightly with a fork.
Serve with steak; garnish with onion rings, fried. Serves 6.

title: zucchini mushroom casserole
directions: In skillet, heat oil and saute onion and green pepper until tender.
Add zucchini and mushrooms with parsley, garlic, oregano and basil until softened.
Stir in tomatoes, breaking with fork, and tomato sauce.
Salt and pepper and simmer 10 to 15 minutes.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Separate rolls into triangles.
Place in ungreased 12-inch pizza pan with points toward center.
Press over bottom and up sides of pan to form crust.
Spoon ground pork over crust. Sprinkle with potatoes, bacon and mushrooms.
Top with cheese.
In a bowl, beat eggs, milk and salt.
Pour into crust.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese over all.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Good for supper too!

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix together and chill until ready to serve.

title: pistachio dessert
directions: Mix flour, butter and nuts together.
Pat into ungreased 9 X 13 pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Let cool.

title: french toast
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except bread.
Put butter in frying pan.
Dip slices of bread into mixture.
Cook on medium heat for 2 minutes, each side.
Top with syrup or cinnamon sugar.

title: homemade noodles
directions: Combine all ingredients to make a stiff dough.
Roll thin on floured surface.
Slice with noodle cutter or thinly with knife. Drop into boiling broth and cook, uncovered, for 5 minutes.
Makes 3 cups noodles.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all together and roll in nuts.

title: almond bark heavenly treat
directions: Melt almond bark (or Eagle Brand vanilla candy coating) in microwave or in heavy saucepan over low heat.
When melted, add cereal, pretzels and nuts.
Stir to coat well; drop onto aluminum foil to cool.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Add other ingredients, except taco chips.
Add taco chips right before serving.

title: hawaiian chicken
directions: Cover chicken with sauce mixture and cook at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: homemade soup
directions: Combine all ingredients while ham, or whatever meat you are using for seasoning, is cooking.

title: chicken souffle
directions: Place chicken in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour soups over chicken.
Arrange bread cubes over soups; pour melted margarine over.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 60 minutes.

title: beefy mexican lasagna
directions: Brown ground beef; drain.
Add tomato sauce and taco seasoning.
Simmer 5 minutes.
In bowl, combine 1 cup Cheddar cheese, cottage cheese and eggs.
Place 3 tortillas on bottom of a greased 8 x 12-inch baking dish.
Overlap 6 tortillas around sides of baking dish.
Spoon meat mixture evenly in dish.
Top with 3 tortillas, then with cheese mixture.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 45 minutes.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake 5 minutes longer.

title: breakfast souffle
directions: Brown and drain sausage.
In bowl, mix eggs, milk and seasonings (with wire whisk).
Add bread cubes, grated cheese and meat.
Stir.
Pour into 13 x 9 x 3-inch pan.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Remove from refrigerator 30 minutes before baking. Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Serve warm.

title: pumpkin cheesecake bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large mixing bowl on low speed, combine cake mix, 1 egg, butter and 2 teaspoons pumpkin spice until crumbly.
Press into bottom of a 15 x 10-inch jellyroll pan.

title: ham and potato au gratin
directions: Boil potatoes 10 minutes, drain.
Layer potatoes, ham and mushrooms in shallow 2-quart casserole.
In medium saucepan, melt 1/4 cup margarine and stir in flour, blending thoroughly.
Slowly add milk, stirring until thickened.
Fold in cheese and sour cream and pour over casserole.
Combine crumbs and margarine; sprinkle over casserole.
Bake in 350° oven 30 to 40 minutes until hot and bubbly.

title: apple brownies
directions: Cream margarine and sugar until smooth.
Add beaten egg and vanilla; mix well.
Sift together the next 6 dry ingredients. Beat them into wet mixture.
Add apples and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes in 8-inch square greased pan.
Cool and cut in squares.

title: homemade yogurt
directions: In microwavable bowl (4 cup Pyrex measuring cup is good), mix milk, instant dry milk and water.
Place in microwave, insert meat probe and bring temperature to 180°.
(If you don't have microwave, you can heat milk in heavy saucepan until just beginning to simmer.)
Remove from oven, cover and let cool to lukewarm.
Add commercial yogurt or some from a previous batch as starter.
(Note:
Commercial yogurt must have live cultures.) Pour into cups (half-pint Mason jars are good).
Set in small styrofoam cooler or insulated box, along with a quart jar of boiling water.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix all ingredients well and refrigerate overnight.

title: taco crescent pie
directions: Brown ground beef.
Add taco seasoning, water and olives.
Let simmer for 5 minutes.

title: savory potato bake
directions: The potato, as most will agree, is versatile, nutritious and universally appealing.
When this version, seasoned with cheese, cream and eggs, has palled, get inspired with new creations by using one or more of the ingredients recommended under our tips.

title: beef brisket
directions: Line a 9 x 13-inch pan with foil.
Mix ingredients and spread over brisket.
Cover and bake in a 300° oven for 1 hour per pound of brisket.
Uncover 30 minutes before removing from oven.
Let cool before slicing (I prefer to remove the excess marinade before slicing).

title: banana bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugars until light and add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Stir in bananas.
Sift together dry ingredients and add to the banana mix.
Pour in greased 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: baked corn casserole
directions: Combine and put in greased 9 x 12-inch dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: nachos
directions: In saucepan or microwave, heat until cheese is melted.
Serve over tortilla chips.

title: mary's cinnamon coffee cake
directions: Put all together in a bowl and mix at highest speed for 5 minutes.
Mix 1/2 cup brown sugar and 2 teaspoons cinnamon.
Put cake mixture and cinnamon mixture in layers in greased Bundt pan or 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350°.

title: fettucine with zucchini mushroom sauce
directions: Cook garlic in olive oil.
Stir in tomatoes, basil and salt. Heat through.
Cook spaghetti, drain and top with tomato mixture. Add Mozzarella and Parmesan; toss and serve.

title: sweet potato rolls
directions: Melt margarine in 13 x 9 x 2-inch casserole dish.
In a pan, put sugar, water and vanilla.
Heat until sugar is dissolved. Set aside.
Mix flour, Crisco and milk together.
Mix well. Roll out dough.
Put potatoes on dough, then sprinkle cinnamon over potatoes.
Roll up, cut and put in buttered dish.
Pour sugar and water over rolls and bake for 55 or 60 minutes at 350°.

title: pineapple pie
directions: Blend all ingredients and put into graham cracker crust.
Let set 2 to 3 hours after mixing.
It's delicious!

title: shrimp casserole
directions: Cook onions, bell pepper, celery and garlic in butter until tender.
Add soup, water, parsley, green onions, chopped shrimp and pimento.
Heat thoroughly.
Stir in rice and 1/2 of the bread. Cook a little longer.
Season to taste.

title: seafood casserole
directions: Grease a 6 to 8-quart ovenproof casserole dish.
Combine shrimp, crab, scallops, potatoes, celery, onion, Worcestershire sauce, salt, pepper, egg, oyster sauce and mayonnaise.
Mix well. Put the mixture into the prepared casserole dish.
Sprinkle cornflake crumbs over.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: upside-down ham loaf
directions: Place green pepper rings in baking dish.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Press ham mixture on top of peppers.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° in oven 1 1/2 hours.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Place cream cheese in mixer bowl; add peanut butter and vanilla.
Let mix for a minute.
Add milk slowly, scraping bowl. After mixture is well blended, slowly add confectioners sugar. Remove from mixer and fold in Cool Whip.
Turn into crust.
Cover with lid that came with pie crust and seal.
Place in freezer for at least 6 hours or overnight.

title: chicken and olive pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Place pizza crust on baking sheet or 12-inch pizza pan.
Spread salsa over crust.
Top with corn, chicken, olives and cheese.
Bake 10 minutes or until heated through or until cheese is melted.

title: deluxe three bean bake
directions: Cook bacon until crisp.
Drain on paper towels, reserving drippings.
Saute onion in drippings until lightly browned.
Stir in sugar and catsup.
Add all beans, cheese and bacon.
Blend. Spoon into 2 quart baking dish and bake in a preheated 350° oven about 35 minutes.

title: double lemon cream pie
directions: Cut butter into flour; add nuts and form ball.
Press firmly into bottom and up sides of 9-inch deep dish pie pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Cool.

title: new orleans "cream cheese"
directions: In small bowl, using high speed of electric mixer, beat cottage cheese until smooth.
Then add sour cream, sugar and vanilla.
Beat until very smooth.
Next, pour cheese mixture into 8 muffin-sized paper liners.
Place within cups of metal muffin pan.
Freeze until firm (about 2 hours).*

title: taco dip #2
directions: Combine ingredients and spread on cookie sheet, pizza pan, etc.

title: a traditional whole wheat bread
directions: Mix in a large bowl.
Dissolve yeast in warm liquid (85°) with 1 teaspoon honey.
When it bubbles up (5 to 10 minutes), add remaining honey, salt, oil and 3 cups flour.
Beat for 2 minutes at medium speed with mixer.
Add 1 more cup flour; beat briefly. Add remaining flour until you have a soft dough.
Turn dough out onto a firm, lightly floured surface.
Knead the dough by hand, pushing the palms of your hands firmly into the dough, folding the dough in half towards you and giving it a quarter turn.
Repeat. Do this for 5 to 10 minutes.
Add more flour as you knead; don't allow dough to get too dry.

title: rosemary's baked hash browns
directions: Stir together butter, onion, cream of mushroom soup, sour cream, cheese and salt.
Add hash browns and mix together carefully.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch sprayed pan.
Top with 2 cups crushed corn flakes mixed with 1/2 cup melted butter.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Remove foil and bake another 1/2 hour until brown.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: cherokee strip coleslaw
directions: Mix well and let stand in fridge before serving.

title: low-fat muffins
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease muffin cups with cooking spray. Combine milk and applesauce with beaten eggs.
Stir in remaining ingredients until flour is moistened (batter will be lumpy).
Fill muffin cups 3/4 full.
Bake until golden brown, about 20 minutes. Remove from pan immediately.
Makes about 1 dozen.

title: nutritious delicious fries
directions: Peel and cut potatoes in strips; place in bowl.
Sprinkle with seasoned salt.
Pour an egg white over potato strips and stir until potatoes are coated.
Place on a Pam sprayed cookie sheet.
Bake at 425° for 25 to 30 minutes.
For crispier fries, turn every 10 minutes.

title: happiness cake
directions: Beat all ingredients except poppy seeds for 4 minutes.
Fold in poppy seeds.
Pour into a greased bundt pan.
Bake in a 350 degree oven for 60 minutes.
After removing from pan sprinkle with powdered sugar while still warm.

title: stuffed hot dogs
directions: Cut hot dogs lengthwise almost all the way through.
Spread open and place on cookie sheet.
Spoon mashed potatoes into hot dogs.
Cover potatoes with slices of cheese.
Bake at 350° until the cheese melts.

title: tortilla cheese wrap ups
directions: Mix cream cheese, cilantro and seasonings until well blended. Spread 1 tablespoon cream cheese mixture over each tortilla. Place 2 cheese singles on each tortilla.
Roll tightly.
Cut each tortilla in sixths.
Serve with salsa.

title: better than sex cake
directions: Bake cake mix as directed on package in 9 x 13-inch pan.
As soon as it comes out of the oven, poke holes all over the cake. Pour condensed milk over cake and caramel fudge topping.
Let cool completely.
When cool, cover top of cake with Cool Whip, then crush candy bars and sprinkle all over Cool Whip.

title: chicken spinach caesar wraps
directions: Mix Jarlsberg cheese and chicken in bowl and toss well with dressing; set aside.
Arrange 1 cup spinach leaves on one side of a tortilla.
Spoon on 1/4 of the chicken mixture.
Roll up tightly, tucking in ends.
Repeat to make 4.
Heat in microwave 1 1/2 to 2 minutes or until warm.
Slice in half.
Yields 4 wraps.

title: custard pie
directions: Mix eggs, salt, nutmeg, sugar and vanilla.
Add hot milk slowly while stirring.
Pour into unbaked pie crust.
Bake at 425° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: iced tea
directions: *This is a very little amount.
There are ten pinches in 1/8 teaspoon of soda.

title: meat and potatoes casserole
directions: Cover bottom of shallow baking dish with layer of mashed potatoes.
Over this spread any kind of leftover meat, leftover gravy and onion juice.
Cover with layer of mashed potatoes.
Dot with butter and place in hot oven (400°) for 20 minutes or until heated through and brown on top.

title: strawberry delight
directions: Dissolve jello into boiling water.
Add thawed strawberries, pineapple, bananas and pecans; mix well.
Pour half of this mixture in long Pyrex dish.
Put in refrigerator to set.

title: lime congealed salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and fold in Cool Whip.
Refrigerate and stir occasionally, if time allows (3 or 4 times).
Make night or day before you need it.

title: kahlua
directions: Simmer the coffee, water and sugar for 2 hours (fairly thick syrup).
When this is cool, add the vodka and vanilla.
Makes about 2 wine bottles full.

title: fresh pear or apple cake
directions: Mix together oil, sugar, beaten eggs and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 325°.
I use loaf pans.

title: orange chocolate charlotte
directions: Place orange peel and milk in a saucepan over low heat; bring just to a boil.
Dissolve 1 tablespoon sugar in orange juice in a shallow dish.
Set aside. Place chocolate in a large bowl; cover with plastic wrap.
Microwave on Low power for 2 1/2 minutes.
Add butter and stir well.

title: hot milk cake
directions: Heat milk and butter until milk is scalded and butter is melted.
Blend flour, salt and baking powder.
Beat eggs and add sugar until light and thick.
Add flour mixture and blend well. Pour in milk mixture and beat on high until cool. (Batter will be very thin.) Beat in vanilla.
Pour into greased tube pan (or 2 loaf pans) and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes. May be used for shortcakes or pound cake.

title: chili nuts
directions: Melt the butter over low heat in a frying pan large enough to avoid crowding.
Stir to coat the nuts and shake the pan over low heat for 8 or 10 minutes.
Turn onto paper towels to drain, then sprinkle with 2 teaspoons of chili powder.
Toss until coated and serve warm.

title: cherry cream pie
directions: Mix softened cream cheese with confectioners sugar and vanilla.
Whip cream (don't sweeten or add vanilla to cream) and add.
Place in cooled pie shell.
Top with cherry pie mix. Chill.

title: french onion soup
directions: In a 3-quart microproof casserole dish, cook onion and butter on High 10 to 12 minutes, stirring once.
Stir in flour and cook, uncovered, on High 1 minute.
Stir in broth, wine, salt and pepper.
Cook on High for 8 minutes.

title: easy beef dish
directions: Cut steak into cubes.
Combine all ingredients into casserole. Mix well and cover.
Bake for 3 hours at 300°.
Do not open oven door!
Serve with rice or noodles.

title: aggression cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients like a pie crust until soft.
Flatten 1-inch balls of dough on ungreased pan.
Press flat with bottom of drinking glass dipped in sugar.
Bake at 350° about 10 minutes.

title: speedy beef skillet
directions: Combine everything but noodles. Cover and cook about 10 minutes. Add noodles and 1/2 c. water. Cover and cook until noodles are tender (about 15 minutes). Stir occasionally.
Serves 4.

title: june hagan's coconut bonbons
directions: Heat corn syrup and stir in coconut.
Let set 1 hour.
Roll into small balls and dip in melted chocolate.
Place on waxed paper to set.
Refrigerate.

title: meat loaf
directions: Preparation:
With a very sharp knife, cut beef across grain into thin strips, 1/8-inch thick.
Combine soy sauce, garlic and ginger.
Add beef.
Toss and set aside while preparing vegetables.

title: ham roll appetizers
directions: Combine all
ingredients
and
spread on slices of ham. Roll and slice in 1/4-inch pieces. Serve on any snack cracker.

title: strawberry punch
directions: Mix 1/2 water and all the sugar until dissolved.
Add jello and stir until dissolved.
Add fruit juices and strawberries and rest of water.
Add ginger ale when served.
Makes 2 gallons.

title: chili dip
directions: Saute butter, onion and bell pepper.
Pour chili into mixture. Pour mushroom soup into mixture.
Bring all to boil.
Remove from heat, add cheese and serve.

title: simple coffee cake(microwave)
directions: In mixing bowl, combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Make a well in center of dry mixture.
Combine eggs, oil and milk; add all at once to dry mixture and stir just to moisten.
Pour into greased 8-inch round dish; sprinkle with topping.
Heat for 8 to 9 minutes, giving dish 1/4 turn every 2 minutes.
Yields 1 cake.

title: raisin puffs(makes 70 cookies)
directions: Boil the water.
Add raisins and boil until water is gone. Cool.
Combine flour, soda and salt.
Beat 1 1/2 cups sugar and margarine until creamy. Add eggs and vanilla.
Beat well.
Add dry ingredients and beat until blended.
Stir in cooled raisins. Shape into 1-inch balls.
Roll in sugar and cinnamon (stirred together).

title: s'mores bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Arrange graham crackers evenly in a 15 x 10 x 2-inch jelly roll pan.
Sprinkle with marshmallows, then chocolate chips on top.
Combine butter and brown sugar in medium microwave bowl.
Microwave 1 1/2 to 2 minutes on high until butter is melted.
Stir to blend.
Spoon evenly over marshmallows and chips.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes or until barely golden. Cool completely in pan on wire rack.
Cut into squares.
Makes 24 bars.

title: broccoli cheese casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions.
Melt butter and saute celery and onion until soft.
To this, add cheese, chicken and soup.
Heat until cheese melts.
Add drained broccoli and mix well.
Bake in 325° oven for 45 minutes.
This is excellent made ahead.
To make a delicious, hot vegetable dip, add 1 small can Pet milk and serve in a chafing dish.

title: instant spiced tea mix
directions: Mix ingredients.
Store in a glass jar.
To serve, boil water and add instant tea mix to taste.
Serve with lemon slices.

title: overnight potato salad
directions: Cook macaroni in boiling salted water according to package directions.
Drain, rinse and drain again.
Cool.
Place lettuce in bottom of a 2-quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Top with macaroni.
Stand egg slices on edge, if desired. Layer ham strips, thawed peas and shredded cheese in order. Combine the salad dressing or mayonnaise, sour cream, green onions and hot pepper sauce.
Spread over top of the salad sealing to edge of the dish.
Cover and refrigerate 24 hours or overnight. Sprinkle top with paprika and snipped parsley.
Toss before serving.

title: egg rolls-american style
directions: Combine the ingredients and bring to a slow boil; serve warm.

title: crustless coconut pie
directions: Combine eggs, sugar and butter.
Add flour.
Mix well.
Pour in vanilla flavoring and milk.
Stir in coconut.
Pour into two greased pie plates. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Thoroughly cream together the first 6 ingredients.
Sift flour, soda and salt together.
Blend into creamed mixture. Shape dough into 1-inch balls.
Roll in sugar.
Place 2 inches apart on a greased pan.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 375°.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Add ingredients one at a time as given, each in separate layers.
Do not toss.
Place salad in large bowl.
Cover and refrigerate for 8 to 9 hours
or overnight, then serve.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Mix all ingredients for 2 minutes and pour into greased loaf pans.
Bake
for
hour at 350°.
While bread is warm, punch holes in loaves and pour glaze over them.

title: lightbody stew
directions: Brown meat in 1 tablespoon oil; add a few tablespoons flour and coat meat.
Add spices, 2 cups hot water and 1 or 2 cups white wine; bring to a boil.
Add potatoes, carrots, celery, tomato and onion; simmer 2 hours.
Add remaining vegetables and simmer until tender.
Add more liquid if needed.
Keep vegetables covered in liquid.

title: "sock it to me" cake
directions: Mix together cake mix, sugar, oil, eggs and sour cream; blend well.
Stir in nuts and almond extract.
Combine brown sugar and cinnamon.
Pour half of the batter in greased and floured tube or Bundt pan.
Sprinkle sugar mixture over batter and add remaining batter.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes before removing from pan.

title: southern pecan loaf
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine the flour, baking powder and salt. Cream the margarine and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add the flour alternately with the milk to the butter mixture, beating until smooth and well combined.
Stir in the flavorings and orange rind, mixing well.
Fold in pecans.
Pour mixture into a greased and floured 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 375° for about 50 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean. Cool slightly; remove from pan.

title: christmas ribbon salad
directions: Pour hot water over Jell-O.
Add cold water.
Add pineapple. Chill lime mixture until firm in a 9 x 12-inch glass dish.

title: chocolate chess pie
directions: Mix sugar, cornmeal and cocoa in bowl.
Add eggs, butter, syrup and vanilla.
Mix well and pour into pie shell.
Bake at 325° to 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chicken breasts supreme
directions: Arrange chicken in shallow baking dish, making sure there is no overlapping.
Cover with the mushrooms.
Combine undiluted soups together, then a little at a time, blend in the wine and sour cream.
Spread over chicken completely covering all. Sprinkle almonds over sauce, dust with paprika and bake in a 350° oven for 1 1/2 hours.

title: wonderful cheese and apples
directions: Allow Camembert, Swiss and Blue cheeses to stand at room temperature for 30 minutes.
In large mixer bowl, combine the 3 cheeses with 2 packages of cream cheese.
Set aside.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion together until tender; drain. Mix with remaining ingredients. Bake 30 minutes in 300° oven.

title: pastel candied fruit peel
directions: Remove	grapefruit
sections.
Cover
grapefruit shells with water
in
saucepan.
Bring
to a boil.
Boil 15 minutes. Drain. Carefully
remove any remaining pulp or membrane.
Cut peel into thin
slices,
about
1/4-inch
wide.
Again
place grapefruit peel
in
saucepan, cover with water and boil until tender.
Mix Jell-O
with 2 cups water in heavy skillet.
Add prepared peel and
spices.
Bring
to a boil, reduce heat and continue stirring occasionally until peels are translucent and syrup is
almost absorbed 30 to 45 minutes.	Remove from heat; lift peels
from skillet with slotted spoon.
Sprinkle with 1 cup sugar;
toss lightly.
Arrange
pieces in single layer on waxed paper-lined trays.
Let dry about 12 hours or overnight. Store in tightly covered container.	Makes about 1 pound.

title: chicken pie
directions: Grease bottom of 13 x 9-inch baking dish with butter.
Put in chicken pieces.
Spread celery soup over the chicken.
Pour broth over soup.
Add mixed vegetables.
Mix the flour, melted margarine and milk together; pour over the top, spreading evenly.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: baked pineapple
directions: Beat together sugar, eggs, margarine and milk until well blended.
Stir in bread crumbs and pineapple.
Pour into greased 2-quart casserole.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: hanky panky
directions: Brown and drain meat in a skillet.
Add seasonings and cheese. Allow to melt.
Arrange bread on cookie sheets.
Put about 1 tablespoonful of mixture on each piece of bread.
Freeze.
When frozen, put in plastic bags to keep in freezer.
When ready to serve, bake on cookie sheets 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.
Serve hot; delicious!

title: baked fish
directions: Spread fish fillets in a baking dish.
Sprinkle with pepper, garlic salt and onions.
Mix soup with sour cream.
Spoon over and under fish.
Bake, uncovered, for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: banana bread(made in food processor)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Add bananas and butter; process until finely chopped, about 20 seconds.
Add remaining ingredients; process 10 seconds.
Turn off; scrape down sides of bowl with rubber spatula.
Add nuts; process about 25 seconds longer.
Do not overprocess.
Turn into greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Bake until bread springs back when touched lightly in center, about 55 to 60 minutes.
Cool before removing from pan.

title: grandma's cornbread dressing
directions: Saute onions and celery in margarine until yellow.
Mix with all ingredients and bake 30 minutes or until brown.
Serves 6 generous portions.

title: chocolate ice cream
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Add 2% milk to finish filling. Freeze to fill line.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: breakfast orange nog
directions: In blender, combine all ingredients.
Blend for 30 seconds to 1 minute or until ice cubes are crushed and mixture is frothy.

title: fudge pecan pie
directions: Combine all ingredients except pecans.
Mix in mixer bowl but do not overmix.
Stir in chopped pecans.
Pour in shell.
Arrange pecan halves on top.
Bake at 350°
for 1 hour.
Cool.
For full flavor let set one day before serving.

title: pineapple cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients, except for 1 cup pecans.
Shape and roll into 2 balls.
Roll balls in 1 cup pecans.
Refrigerate 6 hours.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix together.
Add more sugar if too sticky to roll into balls.
Put in freezer until chocolate mix is made.

title: l.b.j. dry rib seasoning
directions: This is for sprinkling on spareribs or pork chops before you barbecue them.
Use heaping measures when you are mixing it and do not skimp when you use it.
Makes about 12 ounces.

title: no bake fruit cake
directions: Soften gelatin in orange juice in measuring cup; dissolve over hot water.
Thoroughly blend in all spices.
In mixing bowl, add dates, raisins, nuts, fruits and cherries.
Stir in honey and margarine; mix with gelatin thoroughly.
Press mixture into a waxed paper lined pan.
Cover with foil; cool for at least 24 hours.

title: bran cookies
directions: Stir together cereal, flour and baking soda; set aside.
In large bowl, beat margarine, sugar and brown sugar until fluffy. Add eggs and beat well.
Add flour mixture and mix thoroughly. Drop by level teaspoonfuls.
Bake at 325° for 12 to 14 minutes or until lightly brown.

title: appetizo rye boat
directions: Blend all ingredients well and chill.
Scoop out 1 large round rye bread.
Fill with dip.
Cut the scooped out bread into bite-size pieces for dipping.
If necessary, cut up 1 small loaf of rye bread for additional pieces.

title: sarah's hot cinnamon twisters
directions: Combine the sugar and cinnamon.
Mix well.
Slightly flatten each biscuit.
Dip both sides of each biscuit in the butter, then the cinnamon mixture.
Pull and twist.
Bake on foil-lined pan for 8 minutes at 400°.

title: russian tea
directions: Mix ingredients; store in glass jar.
To serve, boil water and add instant tea mix to taste.
For a cup of hot tea, use 2 or 3 teaspoons of the mix and boiling water.

title: stuffed french toast
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Cut banana into 1/4-inch thick slices. In a bowl, whisk together half and half, eggs, vanilla, cinnamon and nutmeg. Cut a slit into bread slices horizontally, almost in half, leaving one edge intact. Stuff each bread slice with 4 to 6 banana slices (don't overstuff). In a baking dish, arrange bread slices in one layer and pour half and half mixture over them. Soak slices, turning them over once or twice to allow bread to absorb all liquid, about 15 minutes. In a 12-inch nonstick skillet, melt butter over low heat. Cook bread until golden, about 5 minutes on each side. Dust each bread slice with confectioners sugar and serve warm with maple syrup.

title: quick and easy lemon pie
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients in mixing bowl.
Stir into pie crust. Chill.
Add Cool Whip topping.

title: ground beef casserole
directions: Chop onion fine.
Brown onion and beef until pink is gone. Drain excess fat.
Mix soups together.
Cook noodles as directed and drain.
In a greased 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan or 3-quart oblong casserole dish, place noodles, then ground beef.
Sprinkle with seasoned salt.
Pour soups over meat.
Top with slices of cheese. Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: creamy chicken livers
directions: In skillet, cook (covered) the chicken livers (that have been cut in large pieces) in butter or margarine until almost tender, about 10 minutes.
Add drained or fresh mushrooms and green onion. Cook until onion and liver are tender.

title: apricot jello mold
directions: Boil 2 1/2 cups apricot nectar.
Add the Jell-O and mix well. Add the ice cream and 3/4 cup cold apricot nectar.
Mix until ice cream is melted and mixture is well blended.
Pour into mold and refrigerate overnight.

title: googie's cheezy potato casserole
directions: Spray 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish with Pam.
Drain potatoes and place in dish.
If some potatoes are larger than others, cut in half.
Precook onions for 5 minutes, drain and layer with potatoes.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper and paprika.
Dot with butter.
Mix the soups and sour cream and grated cheese thoroughly and spread over the potatoes and onions.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: double chocolate cookies
directions: In a mixing bowl, stir together all six ingredients.
Drop mix by spoonful onto an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake in 350° oven for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 4 dozen small cookies.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Brown ground beef; drain off grease.
Add tomato sauce, corn, green beans and picante sauce.
Mix well.
Put in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan that has been greased.
Top with mashed potatoes.
Add cheese on top.
Bake in a 425° oven for 15 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: hearty fish soup
directions: About 30 minutes before serving, slice carrots, onion and celery.
In 5-quart Dutch oven or saucepot over medium-high heat, in hot salad oil, cook vegetables until lightly browned. Add potatoes, clam juice, clams with their liquid, bouillon and 2 cups water.
Over high heat, heat to boiling.
Reduce heat to low. Cover and simmer 7 to 10 minutes until potatoes are almost tender. Cut cod into 2-inch chunks.
Peel, seed and cut tomato into 1 1/2-inch chunks.
Stir cod and tomato into soup on high heat. Heat to boiling. Reduce heat and simmer until fish flakes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: brownies
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Put in baking dish.
This mixture will be very dry.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Combine tomatoes, onion and Karo syrup in pan and bring to a boil, stirring constantly, then stir in macaroni.
Remove from heat; add tuna in chunks and about 2/3 of cheese.
Pour into a 2-quart casserole and cover.
Bake in a 425° oven for 20 minutes until macaroni is tender, stirring occasionally.
Sprinkle with the remaining cheese and bake, uncovered, until cheese is melted, about 5 minutes.

title: tortilla roll-ups
directions: Combine all ingredients in a food processor.
Spread over flour tortillas.
Roll up and refrigerate overnight.
Slice and serve.

title: eve's hummingbird cake
directions: Stir oil into dry ingredients to moisten with beaten eggs. Add pecans, pineapple and mashed bananas.
Bake at 350° about 25 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes before removing from pan.

title: ham and cheese biscuits
directions: Melt margarine in frying pan and saute onion.
Add Worcestershire sauce, mustard and poppy seed.
Slice rolls. Spread onion sauce on bottom of roll; top with ham slice and sprinkle with cheese.
Place top on rolls.
Bake at 450° for 20 minutes.
Serves 30 to 40.
(These can be frozen and baked later. Bake frozen rolls at least 30 minutes.)

title: easy monkey bread
directions: Cut uncooked dinner roll dough into quarters or 1/2-inch pieces and place in a large bowl. Pour melted butter, cinnamon and sugar over dough and mix well to coat all pieces of dough. Pour mixture into a greased Bundt pan and bake for 30 minutes at 350°. Allow to cool 5 minutes and flip Bundt pan upside down onto a plate to release the bread. Serve warm by picking off pieces of the cooked dough.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Note:
Zucchini may be used instead of tomatoes.

title: astounding peach pie
directions: Sprinkle 1/2 cup of the pie crust mix over the bottom of an 8-inch pie plate.
Drain peaches, reserving syrup.
Set aside a few slices for garnish; dice remaining peaches.
Combine pudding mix, allspice, reserved syrup and the milk, blending well.
Stir in diced peaches and spoon half the pudding mixture over the pie crust mix.
Sprinkle with remaining pie crust mix and top with remaining pudding mixture.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes or until set. Garnish with thawed Cool Whip and reserved peaches.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Crush cranberries in blender or food processor and set aside to drain (be sure to save juice that drains off berries).

title: irish potato casserole
directions: Boil, drain and mash potatoes.
Add cheese and remaining ingredients except paprika.
Beat until smooth.
Spoon into buttered 2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Remove from refrigerator, wait 15 minutes and bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: favorite refrigerator dinner rolls
directions: Combine hot water, sugar, salt and shortening.
Cool to lukewarm.
Dissolve yeast in warm water.
When sugar mixture has cooled to lukewarm, add to the dissolved yeast with the egg and 2 1/2 cups flour.
Beat until smooth.
Add enough of the remaining flour to make smooth dough.
Turn out on lightly floured board; knead until smooth and elastic.
Place in greased bowl, lightly oil top of dough and cover tightly.
Store in refrigerator until doubled or until needed.
Dough will keep 4 or 5 days.
Punch down.
Turn out on lightly floured board; divide into 3 pieces. Cut each piece into 9 pieces.
Form into rolls.
Place in 3 greased 8-inch round cake pans.
Cover, let rise in warm place until double or about 1 hour.
Bake in 375° oven for about 20 minutes.
Yield: 27 rolls.

title: walnut caramel triangles
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In medium bowl, combine flour and sugar; cut in margarine until crumbly.
Press firmly on bottom of a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake for 15 minutes or until lightly browned around edges.
Meanwhile, in a heavy saucepan, combine milk, cream and vanilla.
Over medium-high heat, cook and stir until mixture thickens, 8 to 10 minutes.
Stir in walnuts.
Spread evenly over prepared crust.
Bake for 20 minutes or until golden brown. Cool. Garnish with chocolate drizzle.
Chill.
Cut into triangles. Store, covered, at room temperature.

title: tasty taco casserole
directions: Brown together first 5 ingredients.
Add next 3 ingredients. In a 4-quart baking dish, layer crushed corn chips and meat alternately, ending with meat mixture.
Top with cheese and bake at 425° until cheese melts, approximately 10 to 15 minutes.

title: teriyaki marinade for grilled meats and seafood
directions: Combine all ingredients in jar with lid.
Shake well to blend. Pour
over desired meat or seafood.
Marinate 1/2 hour to overnight as desired.
Remaining
marinade
can
be used as dipping sauce or poured over rice with the meal.

title: elephant ears
directions: Deep fry tortillas in skillet until browned slightly; remove and drain on paper toweling.
Sprinkle generously with cinnamon and sugar mix.
For a chip size, cut tortillas in quarters.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix ingredients together while broccoli is cooking. Drain broccoli; then add to mixture. Top with crushed Ritz crackers. Bake at 350 degrees for 45 minutes.

title: spinach dip
directions: Cook spinach and drain, squeezing excess liquid out.
Chop water chestnuts.
Mix all ingredients and chill before serving. Sprinkle with paprika.

title: mexican dip
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish, spread cream cheese and top with chili.
Add 1/2 jar salsa and shredded cheese.
Bake or microwave until hot.
Serve warm with tortilla chips.

title: lemon icing
directions: Combine all ingredients in electric mixer bowl.
Blend at low speed, then beat at high speed until smooth.
Scrape bowl often.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Melt margarine and grate cheese.
Place 1/2 of the asparagus in a greased casserole dish. Add about half of the bread crumbs, half of the margarine and half of the cheese. Repeat layers.
Add mushroom soup.
Sprinkle with crumbs.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°. Serve hot.

title: grandma's 13 layer chocolate cake
directions: Cream sugar and oil until fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time. Sift flour and add alternately with milk to batter.
Stir in vanilla.
Spray 9-inch pans with Pam spray.
Spread 1/2 cup of batter in pans.
Bake at 375° until lightly brown.

title: oatmeal muffins
directions: Combine dry ingredients and raisins.
Add remaining ingredients.
Stir until just moistened.
Pour into muffin cups. Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: cobbler
directions: Melt butter in pan.
Mix together sugar, flour, cinnamon, baking powder and milk.
Pour over melted butter.
Pour 1 can of fruit or berries over this mixture.
Do not stir.
Bake in a 350° oven until browned, approximately 30 to 40 minutes.

title: angel cloud cake
directions: Sift together flour and 3/4 cup sugar twice.
Beat egg whites, cream of tartar, salt and vanilla until foamy.
Beat in the remaining sugar until meringue holds stiff peaks.
Add flour, sugar mixture.
Put in 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes.

title: buttermilk candy
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in 2 qt saucepan; boil to soft ball stage. Remove from heat and beat. Add pecans, vanilla, beat to light brown. Drop by teaspoonfuls fast on grease wax paper or cookie sheet.

title: double fudge saucepan brownies
directions: Stir together flour, baking soda and salt.
In saucepan, combine sugar, butter and water.
Cook over low heat until mixture comes to boil.
Remove from heat; add 1 cup chips, stirring until melted.
Stir in eggs and vanilla.
Add flour mixture.
Stir in remaining chips and nuts.
Pour into 9-inch greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: 5 layer salad
directions: Put in casserole dish in layers.

title: french dressing
directions: Beat with mixer for 10 minutes. Makes 1 quart.

title: wet-n-wild berry slush
directions: In blender, combine ingredients.
While blending, add ice cubes through hole in lid until slushy.
Grab a straw and start sippin'!!!
Serves 4.

title: three bean casserole
directions: Brown hamburger. Drain. Fry bacon. Crumble into pieces. Mix with remaining ingredients. Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown the ground beef with the taco seasoning.
Place all ingredients in a large bowl in the order given.
Mix the Italian dressing according to package directions and pour over salad. Toss and serve immediately.

title: sandwich loaf
directions: Thaw dough in refrigerator.
Saute green peppers and mushrooms in butter.
Line cookie sheet with foil and grease lightly.
Pat dough to form a square.
Cover center 1/3 with ham, salami, cheese and pepperoni.
Sprinkle with mushrooms and peppers.
Cut other 2/3 of dough into strips.
Fold strips to center alternating sides.
Pinch ends closed.
Let dough rise (about 2 hours) until double in size.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 45 minutes for white bread, 30 minutes for wheat bread.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: grape frostee
directions: Place all ingredients in blender; blend until smooth.
Serve at once.
Makes
2 servings.

title: porcupines
directions: Mix well and shape into balls.
Fry on all sides and cover with 1 can stewed tomatoes.
Bring to a boil.
Cover.
Turn on low heat and simmer for 45 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: salmon croquettes
directions: Drain salmon.
Mix salmon and bread crumbs.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Stir into salmon mixture.
Form into about 12 balls. Heat oil, about 1 inch deep, in skillet.
Spoon croquettes into hot oil.
Brown well on all sides.

title: bebe's cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening together well.
Add egg.
Beat well and add the buttermilk.
Sift the flour, cocoa, salt and soda together and add to the mixture.
Add vanilla and lastly add the boiling water.
Mix well and bake at 350° until done in a greased 8-inch square pan.

title: butterscotch bars
directions: Melt butter, peanut butter and chips together. Add marshmallows, nuts and coconut. Pour into a 9 x 13 buttered pan. Refrigerate. When cool, cut in squares. Keep refrigerated.

title: ground beef chop suey
directions: Cook celery, onion and ground beef in hot fat in large frypan for about 5 minutes, until meat begins to brown.
Blend cornstarch with water; stir into beef mixture.
Add bouillon cube, soy sauce and salt.
Cook, stirring constantly, until sauce is thickened and clear.
Stir in cabbage.
Cook, covered, for about 3 minutes, until cabbage is tender but still firm.
Serve on rice.
Provides 6 servings, 3/4 cup chop suey and 2/3 cup rice each.

title: tuna noodle supper
directions: Cook noodles as directed until tender; drain.
Mix well with mushroom soup and tuna.
Place back on burner until good and warm. Serve with salad, bread and butter.

title: breakfast cookies
directions: Fry sausage.
Drain.
Add Bisquick and grated cheese.
Add water.
Mix.
Drop on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Cream together the oil, sugar and eggs.
Beat.
Add vanilla and zucchini.
In separate bowl, combine flour, salt, baking soda, baking powder and cinnamon.
Stir into zucchini mixture.
Add raisins and nuts, if desired.
Pour into 2 greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: peanut butter tandy cake
directions: Mix ingredients, except chocolate morsels, adding milk gradually.
Pour into greased and floured jelly roll pan.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Spread with thin layer of peanut butter.
Refrigerate until firm.
Melt milk chocolate morsels in microwave.
Spread on top of cake.

title: chess cake
directions: Mix 1 egg, butter and cake mix by hand.
Press into a 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking dish (glass).
Mix remaining ingredients by mixer. Then pour cream cheese mixture over cake mix mixture.
Bake at 325° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: cracker chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken for about 30 to 40 minutes on about medium heat. After chicken is done, cut into small pieces and put in a large casserole dish. In a boiler, combine all soups, 1 cup of broth from chicken, sour cream, about 1 teaspoon of salt and 1 teaspoon of pepper (salt and pepper may vary, depending on your taste). Continue to

stir sauce so that it doesn't stick and burn. Cook on low heat. When sauce is warm, pour over chicken. Carefully stir to mix well. Crush crackers and cover top completely. Add a generous amount of melted butter (or squeeze butter) to the top. Cook in oven until crackers start browning (15 to 25 minutes). Keep an eye on it; it will burn easily without enough butter on the crackers. ENJOY!!!!

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Stir together the nuts, Karo, sugar and salt in a 1 1/2 qt. casserole dish, cook 7 1/2 minutes.
Stir after 4 minutes. After the 7 1/2 minutes, add butter and vanilla and blend well.
Cook 1 1/2 minutes more.
Add soda and stir until light and foamy.
Pour onto a lightly greased cookie sheet.
Cool about 1 hour.
Break into pieces and store in airtight container.

title: texas hot chili
directions: Put tomatoes in large pot (8 quart or larger).
Cook beef in frying pan until well done.
Add chopped onion and pepper.
Add chili powder.
Add 1/2 cup water.
Add this mixture to tomatoes; start heating.
Add beef bouillon to tomatoes.
Add frying pan mixture.
Add chili beans.
Cook for about 1/2 hour, or until mixture is heated well.
Add Tabasco sauce, if desired.

title: green salad
directions: For crust:
Mix together graham cracker crumbs, butter and 2 tablespoons sugar.
Pat into 11 x 6-inch pan.
Freeze until hard.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Cook cranberries, sugar and water for 5 minutes.
Pour over the Jell-O and marshmallows.
Stir until dissolved.
Cool slightly, then add remaining ingredients.
Refrigerate until jelled.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Add nuts if desired.
Mix with electric mixer.
Divide into 3 loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Freezes well.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Combine ingredients in order.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto plain cookie sheet (I spray sheet with Pam).
Press flat with a glass dipped in sugar.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Cool on newspaper!

title: honey bun cake
directions: Mix well and sprinkle over batter in pan.
Pour remaining batter over sugar-cinnamon mixture and bake in a preheated 350° oven for 20 to 25 minutes or until done.

title: cherry dream pie
directions: Roll crackers; add sugar and melted butter. Line pan with crackers. Add cherries. Prepare Dream Whip as package says; fold in cream cheese and powdered sugar. Put on top of cherries. Sprinkle graham crackers on top. Chill 2 hours.

title: pineapple tapioca cream
directions: Scald milk.
Add beaten egg yolks.
Cook sugar and water until mix spins a thread.
Pour slowly into egg whites.
Add to milk and egg mix.
Add 1 small can grated pineapple and some small marshmallows.
Make a meringue of egg whites.

title: pineapple chess pie
directions: Combine sugar and butter. Cream well. Add eggs. Beat well. Stir in pineapple and vanilla. Pour mixture into pastry shell. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until a knife inserted halfway between center and edge comes out clean. Cool before serving. Yields one 9-inch pie.

title: cinnamon rolls or buns
directions: Put cinnamon in bag with rolls; shake.
Put rolls in greased, high-sided pan (Turk's head).
Sprinkle dry pudding mix on rolls and sprinkle sugar on top.
Pour melted butter over rolls.
Cover with foil for 8 hours at room temperature, then bake 35 minutes at 350°.

title: angel mallow white frosting
directions: Combine sugar, egg whites and water in double boiler; beat with electric mixer over boiling water until soft peaks form. Remove from heat; beat in vanilla.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Blend spinach with cream cheese, 2 tablespoons butter, salt and pepper.
Pour into a buttered 2-quart casserole.
Combine 4 tablespoons melted butter with bread crumbs and sage.
Sprinkle mixture on top of spinach.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly.

title: stew fried beans
directions: Prepare fresh green beans by snapping into 1/2-inch pieces. Pour oil to cover bottom of iron skillet.
Sprinkle about 1 teaspoon of sugar and salt (enough to season beans) over the oil in skillet.
Heat over medium heat until sugar begins to dissolve and crystallize.
Place beans in oil and cover with tight lid. Water in beans will cook out.
If beans begin to fry, add small amount of water and stir to prevent browning.
Takes about 30 minutes to cook tender.

title: friendship tea mix
directions: Combine all ingredients in large bowl, stirring and mixing well.
Store mix in airtight containers.
Makes 50 servings.

title: chinese chews
directions: Cut butter into flour and sugar as in pie crust and pat into bottom
of	8
x
8-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes. Mix
eggs,
brown
sugar,
coconut,
walnuts
and cherries. Pour
over top of baked crust.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cut into squares while hot.
Yields 24 squares.

title: broccoli in sour cream
directions: Cook broccoli in vegetable steamer.
Drain and place in a casserole dish.
Combine sour cream, onion, salt, pepper, dry mustard and garlic.
Mix well.
Pour sauce over broccoli.
Top with mixture of bread crumbs and butter.
Bake at 375°
for 30 minutes.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Brown the ground beef, onions and pepper together.
Add the mushrooms.
Stir in the cheese soup and pizza sauce.
Cook the spaghetti until tender; drain and mix with the previous mixture and spread in a rectangular baking dish.
Sprinkle on the Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Let set for 5 minutes before serving.

title: chicken sorrento
directions: For Sauce:
Heat 1/2 cup oil in large saucepan to hot.
Add garlic; stir lightly and do not brown.
Add mushrooms, parsley, pinch of oregano, 1/2 cup white wine and tomatoes; bring to a boil. Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Cover; let simmer for 20 minutes.

title: oven barbecued chicken
directions: Season chicken with pepper.
Combine all other ingredients. Preheat oven to 350°.
Place chicken in a shallow pan.
Cover with 1/3 sauce.
Bake 1 hour.
Turn and add more sauce.
Bake 1 hour more and add remaining sauce.
Watch carefully.
If sauce brown too much, add a little water.
Reduce heat to hold until chicken is done.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: vegetable lasagna
directions: Cook broccoli, carrots, Italian seasoning and garlic powder with just 2 tablespoons of water. Bring to a quick boil and reduce heat to low. Cover and cook about 10 minutes, until carrots are crisp-tender. Drain. In a medium bowl, combine 1/2 of Parmesan cheese, the Ricotta cheese and Mozzarella cheese. Of this cheese mixture, reserve 1 cup. To the remaining cheese mixture, add the soup and stir in the vegetables. Layer in a 9 x 12-inch baking dish 3 noodles. Spread with 1/2 of cheese-soup-vegetable mixture, adding another layer of noodles and another layer of cheese-soup-vegetable mixture. Top with remaining 3 noodles. Add reserved 1 cup of cheese mixture and balance of Parmesan cheese sprinkled on top. Cover with foil and bake at 375° for 30 minutes. Uncover; bake another 10 minutes.

title: butterscotch pie
directions: Mix well.
Cook until thick.
Pour into baked pie shell and cover with meringue and brown.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Place chicken, uncooked, in bottom of casserole.
Combine rice, soup, water and onion soup and pour over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes, covered and 30 minutes, uncovered.

title: zucchini cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Generously grease and flour 2 bread pans.
Put all ingredients in a large bowl and blend until moist. Beat 2 minutes at high speed.
Pour into prepared bread pans. Bake 60 to 70 minutes, until toothpick doesn't stick when inserted in the middle.
Cool 30 minutes before removing from pans.
tags: Betty Crocker coconut pecan frosting mix

title: frozen date salad
directions: Cream the cream cheese until very soft.
Add syrup a little at a time to blend.
Add dates, bananas or pineapple and nut meats. Whip cream; fold in.
Put in freezer.
(Keeps well in freezer 4 to 6 weeks.)
I take out of freezer (if I remember) about 1 hour before serving.
Serves 8.

title: stuffed pasta shells
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Brown hamburger, season with salt and pepper to taste.
Drain.
Mix Parmesan cheese, Mozzarella cheese, cottage cheese and 1/2 of spaghetti sauce into meat mixture. Stuff pasta shells.
Place in 12 x 8-inch baking dish.
Spoon spaghetti sauce over shells.
Cover with foil and bake for 30 to 40 minutes or until thoroughly heated.
Makes 4 servings.

title: cheese and strawberries
directions: Combine all ingredients except preserves.
Refrigerate.
One hour before serving, form into a ring mold and put strawberry preserves in the middle.
Serve with crackers.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Place eggs in a sauce pan and cover with cold water, at least one inch above eggs and rapidly bring to a boil
Reduce heat to a simmer and cook for about 15 minutes.
Don't over cook.
Cool at once in cold running water.
Peel the eggs under the cold running water.
This helps the peeling.
After the eggs are peeled, cut in half and place yellows in mixing bowl and whites on an egg platter.

title: cherry cream delight
directions: Add cream of tartar to the beaten egg whites; beat until stiff and gradually add white sugar and beat until peaks form.
Fold in soda crackers.
Add nuts and vanilla.
Put in a lightly greased 9 x 13-inch pan and bake for 25 minutes at 350°.
Cool until cold. Mix Dream Whip with no sugar.
Put over cracker mixture and cover with thickened cherries.
Let stand 4 to 5 hours.

title: black cherry jello salad
directions: Mix jello with 1 cup water.
Add pie filling and stir.
Add pecans and stir.
Chill.

title: toffee
directions: Ensure that you will have no interruptions while making toffee!!

title: fat-free fruit dip
directions: Mix well by hand and serve with fresh fruit.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Cook vegetables in broth until soft.
Add soup and cheese. Serve hot.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients except powdered sugar in order given. Drop from teaspoon onto cookie sheet.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.
Cool.
Roll in powdered sugar.

title: cape cod oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix flour, baking soda, cinnamon and salt.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Drop by teaspoonful onto a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.

title: fried cookies
directions: Blend the ingredients, except oil and powdered sugar, well. Roll into thin dough.
Cut into strips.
Fry; drain.
Dust with powdered sugar.

title: dove pie
directions: Drop doves into boiling water, using only enough water to cover, and season with salt, pepper and margarine.
Use 1/2 stick of margarine per 8 doves, and increase the amount of margarine accordingly.
Boil until tender.
Remove doves and bone them; set aside.

title: strawberry pretzel salad
directions: Combine oleo with sugar.
Mix in crushed pretzels and pat into 9 x 13 pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Cool.
Dissolve jello in water.
Add strawberries.
Chill until almost set.
Cream white sugar with cream cheese.
Fold in Cool Whip and spread over cooked and cooled crust.
Pour jello mixture over this.
Chill until firm. Also, can be used as a dessert.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Blend sugar, spices and salt together.
Beat eggs with milk; combine with sugar, spices and pumpkin until smooth.
Pour filling into unbaked pie shell.
Bake in hot oven at 425° for 15 minutes. Reduce heat to moderate 350°.
Bake until knife inserted in pie comes out clean.
Cool before slicing.

title: oklahoma pecan pie
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
For filling, combine eggs, syrup, brown sugar, granulated sugar, butter, Crisco, vanilla and salt in large bowl.
Mix until well blended.
Stir in nuts.
Spoon into unbaked pie shell.
Bake for 10 minutes.
Reduce temperature to 350°. Bake for 30 to 45 minutes.
Cool to room temperature before serving.

title: magic muffins
directions: Add boiling water to 100% bran and set aside.
Cream margarine and sugar; add eggs and buttermilk.
Stir in dry ingredients just until moistened.
Fill muffin tins 2/3 full.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Baked muffins freeze well.
Uncooked batter keeps well for several weeks in covered jar in the refrigerator.
When baking the refrigerated batter, allow extra time for baking.
Chopped nuts, dates, raisins, etc. may be added to the batter.

title: turkey crunch casserole
directions: Place beans in a 11x17 inch pan.
Combine turkey with soup, half and half and mushrooms including liquid.
Spoon over beans. Combine noodles and onion rings.
Sprinkle over turkey mixture. Heat for 30 minutes in a 350° oven.
Turkey gravy may be used instead of soup.

title: our best southern fried chicken
directions: Combine 3 qt. water and 1 Tbsp. salt in a large bowl; add chicken.
Cover and chill 8 hours.
Drain chicken; rinse with cold water, and pat dry.
Combine 1 tsp. salt and pepper; sprinkle half of mixture over chicken.
Combine remaining salt and pepper mixture and flour in a large heavy-duty zip-top plastic bag. Place 2 pieces of chicken in bag; seal.
Shake to coat.
Remove chicken; repeat procedure with remaining chicken, 2 pieces at a time.

title: low-fat dessert mousse
directions: *The original recipe called for lemon jello and lemonade concentrate.
Strawberry jello with orange-strawberry-banana concentrate can be used, also.

title: beautiful fruit
directions: Drain juices and save.
Put fruit in another bowl and set aside.
Cut bananas into juice and let set for five minutes. Remove bananas and dissolve vanilla pudding in juice.
Stir in fruit and refrigerate.
Can be eaten on slice of plain cake or vanilla ice cream.
Keeps well in covered container.

title: pudding and chip cake
directions: Make pudding as directed on box. Remove from stove. Add cake mix directly from box into pudding, stirring all the time. Beat well. Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13 x 2 pan. Sprinkle top with nuts and chips. Bake in 350° oven until cake tests done, about 30 minutes.

title: veal marsala
directions: Salt and pepper both sides of veal cutlet, then lightly flour veal.
Take a large frying pan; add 1/4 cup of vegetable oil and heat the oil on high until it's very hot.
Cook veal cutlets quickly, 30 to 45 seconds per side.
Add mushrooms to oil after veal is removed.
Saute a couple of minutes.
Remove mushrooms; drain oil.
Add Marsala wine, then add veal and mushroom.
Add a couple of pieces of butter on top.
Cook a couple of minutes. Serve cutlets with mushrooms and sauce on top.

title: pound cake supreme
directions: Cream butter, margarine and cream cheese.
Add sugar, vanilla and eggs (one at a time), beating well after each.
Add flour; beat until well mixed.
Pour into tube pan which has been greased, floured and the bottom lined with waxed paper.
Bake in a 325° oven for 1 hour and 35 minutes, or until done.

title: pat's barbecue chicken
directions: Brown onion in oil.
Prepare chicken and drop in pot of barbecue sauce.
Serve with rice.
Cook until chicken is tender. Cook on low to prevent burning.

title: gabrielle's crispy potato wedges
directions: Cut potatoes into large wedges and place in large bowl; add cold water to cover.
Let stand for 15 minutes.
Preheat oven to 425°.
Spray a nonstick baking sheet with vegetable cooking spray. Set aside.
Drain potatoes in a colander.
Spread on a double layer of paper towels.
Cover with a second layer of paper towels. Press down on the towels to dry potatoes.
Transfer potatoes to a clean large bowl.
Sprinkle with oil, pepper and salt.
Toss gently to combine.

title: lise's chicken
directions: Mix soup, mayonnaise and curry.
Put broccoli in baking dish, then the chicken on top.
Cover with soup mixture.
Top with basil, parsley or paprika.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Cover while baking.

title: ranger cookies
directions: Cream the sugars and shortening.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Beat until fluffy.
Add flour which has been sifted with salt, soda and baking powder.
Mix thoroughly and add oatmeal, Rice Krispies and coconut.
Dough will be quite crumbly.
Form into balls.
Place on greased cookie sheet and press flat.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes 5 dozen 2-inch cookies.

title: smash 'em and forget 'em cookies
directions: Preheat oven
to 350°.	Mix ingredients together.
Roll into balls and smash 'em on a greased cookie sheet.
Put into oven. Turn
off oven and forget 'em for 5 to 10 minutes.	Eat 'um.

title: spanish rice
directions: Spray skillet with nonstick cooking spray and lightly brown the rice.
Add picante salsa, cumin and chicken broth and refill the can twice with water.
Bring to a full boil.
Reduce heat and cover until rice is tender and liquid absorbed.

title: broccoli cheddar cups
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Between 2 sheets wax paper, roll each biscuit into a 4-inch circle.
Put one biscuit into a nonstick muffin tin and push biscuits up on sides of tin to make a cup. Spoon a mixture of the other ingredients into each cup.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes 10 servings.
