Contains 1/2 protein, 1 bread, 1/2 vegetable and 1/2 fat.

title: lemon jello mold
directions: Mix first 2 ingredients; cool and partially set.
Then add the last 3 ingredients.
Dress the mold with sliced fruit.

title: dandelion dressing
directions: Beat the first 3 ingredients well.
Thin with vinegar.
Add milk; taste (more sugar?).
Fry bacon; don't put in ingredients if too hot.

title: m&m cookies
directions: Cream butter
and
sugars.
Beat in eggs one at a time. Mix in vanilla.
Stir in flour.
Add M&M's.
Bake at 350° for 8 to
10 minutes
or
until	light
brown on ungreased cookie sheet.

title: chocolate mousse cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Prepare cake mix for 2 (9-inch) layers. Bake; remove from pans.
Cool.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add egg, then salt, soda and flour to mixture.
Add bananas and mix well.
Stir in nuts.
Pour into glass baking dish.
Bake at 325° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: "melt-in-your-mouth" pumpkin bread
directions: Mix oil, eggs and pumpkin.
Combine remaining ingredients. Add to pumpkin mixture.
Divide into two 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans. Bake at 325° for one hour or until done.

title: nancy mccorkle's caramel ice cream
directions: Caramelize the Eagle Brand milk (simmer 4 hours).
Make a custard of the eggs, milk, sugar and brown sugar, then cool this mixture.
Then mix the whipping cream and half and half with the Eagle Brand milk into custard.
Churn for 30 to 40 minutes.
This makes 1 gallon.

title: glazed fruit salad
directions: Drain pineapple and pudding mix.
Place fruit, coconut, marshmallows, sour cream and pudding all in a large bowl.
Chill until serving time.

title: easy chicken and noodles
directions: In a Dutch oven or large pot, place chicken with enough water to cover.
Simmer about 1 to 1 1/2 hours or until tender and cooked through.
Remove chicken from stock; set stock aside. Remove chicken from bones.
Discard bones and set chicken aside. Bring stock to a boil.
Add noodles and grated carrot.
Boil until noodles are tender.
Add chicken.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
It's even better the next day.

title: beef stroganoff for buns
directions: Brown bacon first and add meat.
Brown.
Add onions.
Blend in flour and seasonings.
Stir in soup.
Cook, uncovered, 20 minutes.
Stir and add sour cream and heat.

title: mexican bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix in order and bake at 350° until brown.
Bake in 2 greased iron skillets.

title: nacho casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. Stir soup and milk in pan. Top with 1/2 salsa and 1/2 chips; spread on beans. Top with salsa and chips. Sprinkle with chiles and cheese. Bake 20 minutes.

title: wild rice casserole
directions: Pour boiling water over rice and set stand for 30 minutes. Brown hamburger and add to rice. Mix in remaining ingredients. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: broccoli puff
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions, omitting salt. Drain well and place in a 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Stir together soup and cheese.
Gradually add milk, mayonnaise and egg to soup mixture, stirring until well blended.
Pour over broccoli and sprinkle with mixture of bread crumbs and margarine.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: potato bread
directions: Boil potatoes and let water cool. Dissolve yeast in 1/2 cup warm water. Beat eggs and set aside. Cream shortening, sugar and salt; add potatoes, eggs, yeast, and potato water. Add flour 2 cups at a time and mix well. Knead on floured surface. Refrigerate covered for several hours (preferably overnight). Knead before making up. Bake at 350 degrees for loaf bread and 325 degrees for dinner rolls for 20-25 minutes.

title: french shellfish mornay
directions: Saute mushrooms, onion, celery and pepper in margarine or butter.
Stir in flour, peppers, herbs and salt.
Add milk all at once, cook and stir until thick and bubbly.
Lower heat and add cheese and grape juice.
Cook until melted and smooth; do not boil. Slice bread and toast it.
Place cooked seafood on toast and top with sauce.
Garnish with paprika or sprigs of fresh parsley.

title: graham crispies
directions: Melt the butter and margarine.
Add the sugar.
Bring to a boil and simmer 2 minutes.
Put aluminum foil on a 10 x 15-inch cookie sheet and spray with Pam.
Place graham crackers (broken on dotted lines) on sheet and pour liquid over them.
Sprinkle with the nuts. Bake at 350° for 11 to 12 minutes.
(Hardens within 30 minutes or so after cooking.)
Break apart.

title: sausage dip
directions: Drain tomatoes and reserve liquid.
Chop tomatoes very fine. Cream the cheese, chopped tomatoes and sausage.
Add a little juice from Ro-Tel to get right consistency for dipping.
Serve with crackers or tortilla chips.

title: hot fudge pudding cake
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, salt, sugar and cocoa together. Stir in milk and shortening; mix until smooth.
Add nuts.
Spread in a greased 8 x 8-inch square pan.
Sprinkle with combined brown sugar and cocoa.
Pour hot water on top.
Bake in 350° oven for 40 minutes.
Serve upside down while hot.
Top with whipped cream or vanilla ice cream.

title: applescotch pie
directions: Mix apples, brown sugar, water and lemon juice in saucepan. Cover and cook slowly until apples are just tender, 7 to 8 minutes.
Blend flour and granulated sugar.
Add to apples.
Cook, uncovered, stirring, until syrup thickens (about 2 minutes). Remove from heat, add vanilla, salt and butter.
Cool.
Pour apples into pastry lined pie pan; cover with top crust, which has slits cut in it.
Seal and flute.
Bake at 425° for 40 to 45 minutes or until crust is nicely browned.

title: beef burgundy
directions: Place meat in large casserole.
Slice mushrooms on top.
Mix all other ingredients and pour over top of meat.
Cover and bake 4 hours at 300°.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: swiss carrot cake
directions: Combine margarine and sugar.
Add vanilla and egg yolks.
Stir in carrots and nuts.
Sift dry ingredients twice and add alternately with water to creamed carrot mixture.
Spread in a greased waxed paper lined 12 x 9 inch pan.
Bake in preheated 350° to 375° oven for 30 to 35 minutes or until done.
Cool and ice.

title: pastry tarts
directions: Mix cream cheese and margarine until light and fluffy.
Mix with flour.
Shape into small balls and press out into small cupcake pan.
Bake at 350° or 375° for 6 to 7 minutes.

title: meat loaf
directions: In large bowl, combine all ingredients; mix well.
Place in (4 1/2 x 8-inch) loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Drain well. Serves 6.

title: heavenly pie
directions: Bake pastry shell or graham cracker crust.
Sprinkle almonds on crust.
Mix milk, lemon juice and flavorings and blend thoroughly.
Fold into whipped cream and pour into pastry, keeping from edge.
Cover to edge with pie filling.
Refrigerate until firm.
If using blueberry or strawberry pie filling omit almonds and almond flavoring.

title: orange juice frizz
directions: Crush ice in blender.
Mix above ingredients in blender with ice.
Serve in glasses with fresh fruit on top.

title: noodles with onions and cabbage
directions: Peel and thinly slice onion to measure
1 1/2 cups.
Melt butter in large skillet.
Stir in onion, cabbage, sugar, pepper and salt.
Cook over low heat for 45 minutes, stirring occasionally, until onions and cabbage are browned.
Add noodles, tossing to blend.
Cook until heated through.

title: triple layer brownie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
In large bowl, stir together sugar, flour, cocoa, baking powder and salt.
With pastry blender, cut in butter until mixture resembles coarse crumbs; set aside.
In another large bowl, lightly beat eggs and vanilla.
Add dry mixture to egg mixture; beat until ingredients are well blended.
Spoon batter into prepared pan. Bake 25 minutes.
Remove from oven and sprinkle marshmallows evenly over brownies, covering entire surface.
Return to oven and bake 5 minutes; remove from oven.
Cool in pan 10 minutes.
Combine peanut butter chips and shortening in top of double boiler over hot, not boiling, water.
Stir until melted.
Add cereal; stir until thoroughly coated.
Immediately spread over top of marshmallows. Cool until set.
Cut into squares.

title: roasted root vegetables
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Scrub vegetables and peel (as desired). Cut into 1 to 2 inch pieces (all of similar size).
Place butter in roasting pan and heat in oven until melted.
Add vegetables, 1/4 cup of stock, salt and pepper.
Stir well to coat and return to oven.
Cook vegetables for 1 to 1 1/2 hours, stirring occasionally, and adding more stock as needed to keep vegetables moist. Vegetables are done when tender and golden.
Great for Thanksgiving and Christmas dinner.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion in salt water until tender.
Drain. Beat egg lightly.
Add remaining ingredients reserving 1/3 of cheese and bread crumbs for a topping.
Turn into a buttered casserole dish and top with cheese and bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° until cheese is melted and top is browned.
Makes 6 servings.

title: pecan cream cheese pie
directions: Blend 1
cup sugar, 1 teaspoon vanilla and cream cheese until smooth.
Stir
in
chopped
pecans and spoon into crust. Bake at 325°
for
minutes.
Combine sour cream, 2 tablespoons sugar and
1 teaspoon vanilla.
Spoon over top of pie. Return to
oven and bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Garnish with pecan halves and chill.

title: vidalia onion souffle
directions: Place bread in 1 1/2 quart souffle dish.
Melt butter in large skillet and saute onion rings until tender-crisp.
Pour over bread.
Top with thyme and cheese.
Beat the eggs and blend in cream, salt and pepper.
Pour over the bread, onions and cheese, pressing with spatula to be sure bread is soaked.
Can be done ahead and refrigerated at this point.
Bring to room temperature before baking.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until puffed and golden.

title: lemon filling for cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add egg yolks, juice and grated rinds of lemons and water.
Cook over water until thick and add butter. Spread on cake.

title: lime jello salad
directions: Add 2 cups of boiling water to jello.
Add all pineapple and juice (the juice makes up remaining water).
Let stand until ready to set.
Whip cream, then add it and cottage cheese.
Mix well. Put in dish and refrigerate.

title: layered nacho dip
directions: Mix beans and taco seasoning mix. Place on round dish or pan. Layer the rest of the ingredients in order.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: mushroom spread
directions: In a large skillet, heat oil over medium heat. Add onion and garlic and saut until onion is dark brown. Add mushrooms and cook until soft. Add cream cheese, stirring until melted and blended with mushrooms. Add sauces and cayenne pepper. Add sour cream and heat gently. Do not bring to boil. Serve warm with crackers or slices of French baguettes.

title: chocolate banana bread
directions: Place all dry ingredients into a large mixing bowl.
Cut in shortening.
Add bananas and eggs; stir just until blended. Spread evenly into a greased and floured loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.
Cool in pan for 10 minutes.
Remove from pan.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: crescent wrapped gouda
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cut cheese round in half crosswise to form 2 circles.
Remove wax.
Separate dough into 4 rectangles.
Firmly press perforations to seal.
Place one rectangle on top of a second, repeat with remaining rectangle.
Press each into a 6-inch square.
Place cheese circle in center of each.
Pull corners to center top of cheese.
Press tightly against cheese twist dough in center to seal.
Twist off excess dough.
Press seams to seal.
Cut out decorative shapes from leftover dough.
Place on top of Gouda. Brush with egg.
Place 3 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 18 to 20 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes before serving. Yields 8 servings.

title: payday cake
directions: Mix together the first 3 ingredients and spread evenly in ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Press it out.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.
When taken out of the oven, put the marshmallows on the cake. Mix the peanut butter chips, Karo syrup and butter in pan and melt. Stir constantly. When smooth, put in the Rice Krispies and peanuts.
Mix together and spread over the marshmallows.

title: vanilla wafer fruit cake
directions: Mix well.
Press into loaf pans lined with waxed paper.
When set, slice into thin slices.

title: hot spinach dip
directions: Microwave spinach in box about 4 minutes on full power or until thawed.
Drain.
Microwave 6 slices bacon on paper towels 5 to 6 minutes on full power or until crisp.
Drain.
Place cream cheese in medium glass bowl and microwave on 70% power about 2 minutes or until softened.
Add drained spinach, crumbled bacon, mayonnaise, onions, dill weed, Parmesan cheese and lemon juice.
Mix thoroughly.
Microwave 3 to 4 minutes on 70% power or until hot.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Combine first seven ingredients and add the salmon and crumbs. Bake in greased 8 x 4 x 2 1/2-inch or 8 x 8 x 2- inch pan for one hour at 350°.
Garnish with lemon wedges and cucumber twists (optional).
Let set for 10 to 15 minutes before serving.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream shortening, brown sugar, sugar and vanilla until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and beat well.
Combine flour, soda and salt.
Add to creamed mixture.
Stir in nuts and chocolate chips. Drop by teaspoon.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: pearl's pecan drops
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease baking sheet with butter flavor Crisco.
Combine sugar, Crisco and vanilla in a large bowl.
Beat at medium speed of electric mixer until blended and crumbly. Combine flour, baking soda and cream of tartar.
Add to creamed mixture alternating with buttermilk, mixing thoroughly after each addition at low speed. Stir in nuts with a spoon. Drop by teaspoonfuls onto baking sheet 2-inches apart.
Bake at 375° for 9 to 11 minutes or until lightly browned. Cool 2 minutes on baking sheet before removing to rack.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: island collards
directions: Stack 4 to 6 leaves and roll them up diagonally.
Thinly slice the leaves crosswise.
Reserve.

title: brown sugar peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream butter with sugar and peanut butter.
Add vanilla and egg; beat until fluffy.
Stir in baking soda and salt.
Blend in flour.
Mix until a stiff dough forms.
Shape into walnut sized balls.
Place on lightly greased cookie sheets.
Press with fork to flatten.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: spiced tea mix
directions: Mix thoroughly; put in jar.
Use 2 teaspoons per cup and pour boiling water over.

title: easy beef 'n noodles
directions: Cut meat into small pieces.
Cook meat, soup, water, onion and pepper in crock-pot on low for 2 to 3 hours until meat is done.
Add noodles.
Stir and cook, covered, 15 minutes longer. (Can also be cooked on stove.)

title: italian spaghetti sauce
directions: In hot butter in Dutch oven saute onion, garlic and celery, stirring, for 5 minutes.
Add salt, pepper, green pepper, water, tomatoes, tomato paste and oregano.
Mix well.
Bring to boiling, stirring.
Reduce heat; simmer, covered, 2 to 3 hours, stirring occasionally.

title: quiche
directions: Take crust out of freezer.
Saute onions and mushrooms in shortening.
Put in crust.
Mix eggs, milk and cheese. Pour into crust over onion mixture.
Put chopped pecans and parsley flakes on top.
Bake at 350° until knife comes out clean.

title: jello pudding
directions: Add hot water to sugar and jello, mix until cool, then add cream and stir until thick.
Add cookies to bowl and the jello mixture over them.
Chill before eating.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Grind cranberries when frozen; cover with sugar.
Let stand awhile to bring out the juice.

title: cranberry cream salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in hot water.
Add cold water; let chill until slightly thickened.
Break up cranberry sauce with a fork. Stir into gelatin with celery and nuts.
Fold in sour cream.
Pour into oiled 1-quart mold dish and chill until firm.
Good with turkey and dressing.

title: strawberry jello salad
directions: Mix jello using only 2 cups boiling water.
Add other ingredients.
Chill.

title: chicken parmesan
directions: Melt butter; add garlic and simmer.
Mix crumbs, cheese and seasonings.
Dip chicken in butter mixture and roll in crumb mixture.
Place in pan and bake for 1/2 hour at 350°, then at 300° for another 1/2 hour.

title: stuffed cornish hens
directions: Prepare long grain and wild Rice-A-Roni with only 2 cups water and 2 tablespoons soy sauce. Add diced celery and the mushrooms (drained). Cool. Stuff and truss Cornish hens. Bake 1 1/4 hours at 350°. Baste 4 times with mixture of 1/2 cup soy sauce, orange marmalade and dry mustard.

title: great pink punch
directions: Mix ingredients with enough water to make a gallon.
Freeze in large freezer bags.
Add cold ginger ale to thawed punch (slushy), about a 2 liter bottle to a gallon and a half of punch.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Brown sausage and drain.
Set aside.
Line greased 13 x 2 x 9-inch Pyrex dish with crescent rolls.
Crumble sausage over rolls.
Mix eggs with milk, salt and pepper, as if making scrambled eggs.
Pour mixture over sausage.
Top with cheese. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until done.

title: oniony tuna casserole
directions: Combine tuna and soup in a 2-quart glass casserole. Stir in remaining ingredients, except onion rings. Cover. Microwave for 16 to 21 minutes or until hot, stirring twice. Let
stand, covered, for 3 minutes. Top with onion rings before serving. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: one dish microwave supper
directions: Place all the ingredients in a 6-quart covered casserole. Microwave on High for 30 minutes. Remove from microwave and turn chicken pieces over.

Put back in microwave and microwave on High for 30 minutes more. Remove from microwave and add 1/3 of a bag of no egg noodles. Put back in microwave for 15 to 20 minutes. Remove from microwave and let stand 5 minutes. Ready to serve 4 to 6 people.

title: borden's pie
directions: Fold lemon juice into condensed milk.
Add drained fruit cocktail and 1/2 of cherries.
Pour into baked crust and chill. Garnish with remaining cherries.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: pina colada cake
directions: Bake cake mix according to box, then spread in a 9 x 14-inch pan.
Let cool.
Slice in serving squares.
Combine coconut cream and condensed milk; pour over cake.
Cover with Cool Whip. Sprinkle with fresh or canned coconut.
Chill before serving. Delicious!!

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: Sift sugar and flour together in a bowl.
In a saucepan, bring oleo, cocoa, water and buttermilk to a rapid boil.
Pour over ingredients and mix well.
Blend in eggs, cinnamon, soda and vanilla.
Pour into greased 11 x 16-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.
Ice as soon as cake is out of oven while still hot.

title: knock out punch
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients in a large container.
Pour 1/2 into punch bowl and add ginger ale and water, if needed.
Makes enough for 2 large punch bowls.

title: forgotten kisses
directions: Beat egg whites until peaks form.
Slowly add sugar.
Continue beating until stiff meringue forms.
Fold in chocolate bits.
Drop by tablespoonfuls onto cookie sheet sprayed with Pam.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Place cookies in oven.
Turn off heat and close oven door.
Melt kisses in warm oven.

title: raspberry-cranberry jello
directions: Put jello in bowl. Add hot water.
Stir until dissolved.
Add 7-Up.
Add the cranberry relish (defrosted) and the raspberries (defrosted). Refrigerate until set.

title: my grandmother's rice pudding
directions: Combine milk, boiled rice, sugar, salt, 1/4 teaspoon of nutmeg, vanilla, beaten eggs and raisins in a 1 1/2 to 2-quart ovenproof casserole dish. Sprinkle nutmeg on top.
Bake in 325° oven for 1 hour or until knife comes out clean.

title: child easy peanut butter cookies
directions: Combine ingredients; drop by spoonfuls on ungreased cookie sheet.
Score with fork.
Bake 12 minutes at 375° or until light brown.

title: never fail caramel icing
directions: On top of stove, cook brown sugar, milk and butter for 3 minutes.
Take off stove and add baking powder and vanilla.
With mixer, while hot, start adding 4x sugar until the icing is just right.

title: walnut toffee
directions: Butter 9-inch square pan.
Melt butter in bowl.
Stir in sugar gradually.
Add syrup and water.
Cook over medium heat to 290°. Add 1 cup walnuts and cook for 3 minutes.
Pour into buttered pan. After mixture has hardened, take out of pan and place on wax paper.
In a separate pan, melt the chips and spread 1/2 on top of toffee.
Sprinkle 1/2 of the remaining walnuts on top of chocolate.
After chips harden, turn over and repeat this process. Break toffee into pieces.

title: king ranch chicken
directions: Line bottom and sides of well-greased 3-quart casserole with 6 tortillas torn up.
Sprinkle with 2 plus tablespoons of chicken stock.
Combine chicken, soups, green pepper, onion and chili powder.
Pour 1/3 mixture and sprinkle with cheese and tomatoes. Repeat layers, ending with cheese, tomatoes and chilies.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour until hot and bubbly.

title: pineapple cheese casserole
directions: Drain pineapple; place in 9 x 12-inch pan.
Mix cheese, flour and sugar; sprinkle over pineapple.
Mix butter and Ritz crackers (crushed) together and spread over pineapple and cheese.
Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: plum cake
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Add 1 cup chopped pecans.
Pour into a Bundt pan and bake for 1 hour in 350° oven.

title: teriyaki
directions: Over medium heat bring to a boil. Stir often-set aside to cool.
After cooled pour over chicken or beef to marinate 1 1/2 to 3 hours.
Cook meat on grill-turn often and baste with mixture often.

title: best macaroons
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Mix coconut, sugar, flour and salt in a large bowl.
Stir in egg whites and almond extract until well blended.
Drop by teaspoon onto lightly greased cookie sheets. Cool on wire racks.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: crabmeat salad
directions: Combine crabmeat and all seasonings.
Season to taste and chill.
Drain and add enough mayonnaise to moisten.
Serve in tomato, avocado or lettuce cups.
Top with strips of pimiento. Garnish with wedge of lemon.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: barbecued baked chicken
directions: Clean peppers by hollowing out the seeds.
Keep peppers whole. Slice so you have rings of peppers.
Place on bottom of a large casserole pan.
Slice onions in rings.
Place on top of peppers. Place quarters of chicken on top of vegetables.
Add oil to bottle of Open Pit barbecue sauce.
Pour this over the top of the chicken. Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: strawberry pretzel salad
directions: Cream 3 tablespoons sugar and butter together.
Add pretzels; mix well.
Press in 9 x 14-inch pan and bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Let cool.
Combine cream cheese and 1 cup sugar.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Spread on cooled crust and refrigerate to chill.

title: lazy lasagna
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In a large saucepan, cook lasagna noodles as package directs; drain noodles.

title: lime congealed salad
directions: Dissolve
jello in boiling water.
Melt marshmallows in jello water by stirring until dissolved; cool until it begins to
set. Combine
the
rest
of the ingredients and fold into jello mixture.
I
usually
put this into a mold.
It makes it more decorative.

title: flan pnertoriqueno
directions: Combine milks, salt and sugar.
Carefully beat eggs to avoid bubbles.
Add eggs to milk mixture.
Strain the mixture.

title: graham cracker pie
directions: Roll graham crackers very fine and add with flour, sugar and butter.
Pat mixture into pie pan and up sides.
Stir egg yolks and add to milk, stirring fast.
Pour in juice and stir.
Pour into pie shell.

title: coconut-pineapple cake
directions: Cream butter; gradually add sugar, beating well at medium speed of an electric mixer.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with milk, beginning and ending with flour mixture.
Mix after each addition.
Stir in flavorings.

title: easy chili
directions: Brown the ground beef and drain the fat.
Place the ground beef, tomatoes, kidney beans and tomato sauce in a large pot and add seasonings.
(Note:
Seasoning amounts are approximate; increase or decrease to suit your taste.)
Cook over low heat for about one hour.
Serve over rice.
Don't forget the corn bread!

title: nasi goreng
directions: Cook chicken and dice.
Brown beef.
Chop ham.
Fry bacon. Mix all of these together.
Add beans and corn.
Chop onions and saute in 1 stick of butter.
Add curry and mix well.
Pour into pan with meats and vegetables.
Mix in cooked rice.
Garnish with celery.
Serve hot.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix cut up broccoli, fried bacon, chopped onion and grated cheese in a bowl.
Set aside.
Mix together salad dressing, vinegar and sugar.
Pour over salad and mix well.

title: meat balls
directions: Combine meat, rice, onion, 1/4 cup water, salt and pepper. Shape into 15 (1-inch) balls.
Blend soup and chili powder.
Stir in 1/2 cup water and bring to a boil.
Add meat balls.
Cover and simmer gently for 1 hour.

title: chicken and rice supreme
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix soups, wine and water.
Pour 1/2 mixture in baking dish.
Spread rice evenly over it.
Pour rest of mixture over rice.
Lay chicken, skin side up, on top.
Sprinkle salt and pepper on top.
Bake, uncovered, 1 1/2 hours.

title: chocolate chip shortbreads
directions: Note:
May substitute colored jimmies for walnuts.

title: italian squiggles
directions: Brown ground beef; drain.
Cook pasta according to directions; drain.
Mix all together.
Microwave 3 to 5 minutes.

title: pie crust
directions: Mix salt and flour.
Cut in shortening (with fingers).
Beat egg.
Add water and egg.
Blend into dough.
Add vinegar.
Blend. Makes 2 large or 3 small crusts.

title: skillet fried corn
directions: Fry bacon until crisp; drain and crumble.
Add vegetables to drippings.
Cover and cook over medium heat 5 to 10 minutes or until tender.
Season to taste and serve with crushed bacon over top.

title: bean casserole
directions: Fry bacon crisp and remove brown onions.
Drain fat, except for 3 or 4 tablespoons.
Add brown sugar and vinegar.
Simmer 20 minutes.
Add to beans in casserole and bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: crab meat pizza
directions: Cream first 5 ingredients together and spread in circle on a 12 inch plate or platter.
Pour chili sauce on top and spread over surface.
Sprinkle crab meat on top of sauce.
Then sprinkle entire pizza with parsley.
Refrigerate 3 hours before serving.

title: meatballs
directions: Place all ingredients in a large bowl; mix thoroughly.
Let stand 1/2 hour.
Shape into medium size meatballs.
Fry gently in olive oil until lightly browned, or place on foil on a cookie sheet and bake for 1/2 hour at 350°.
Put in your favorite spaghetti sauce; cook on medium-low heat for 1 hour.

title: sour cream cookies
directions: Mix butter and sugars together with electric mixer until well blended.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Mix with mixer.
Add sour cream; mix with mixer.
Add baking soda, baking powder and flour.
Add flour a little at a time.
Mix by hand (batter gets too thick when flour is added to use mixer).
Chill dough overnight or up to a week.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Pour melted margarine over croutons.
Put 1/2 of croutons in bottom of casserole dish.
Mix all other ingredients and pour over croutons.
Top with rest of croutons.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes covered, then 15 minutes uncovered.

title: southern pound cake
directions: Heat oven to 300°. Grease and flour tube pan. Measure butter, sugar, eggs and flavorings into large mixing bowl. Blend one minute on low speed, scraping bowl. Beat 5 minutes on high speed. On low speed, mix in flour, baking powder and salt, alternately with milk. Pour into pan and bake 1 hour or until wooden tooth pick comes out clean. Cool in pan 20 minutes. Remove from pan. May sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: tomato soup(canned)
directions: Put tomatoes, celery, bell pepper and onions in a large pan and cook until celery and pepper are soft (about 2 1/2 hours). Run through colander and add sugar, salt and cornstarch.
Bring to boil and cook for 5 minutes.
Put in jars and seal.

title: plain muffins
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, sugar and salt.
Add eggs, milk and melted and cooled shortening to make a stiff batter, stirring only until well blended.
Half fill greased muffin tins and bake in 400° oven 18 to 20 minutes.
Makes from 12 to 15 muffins.
This makes a very nice, soft muffin.

title: dump cake
directions: Do not mix ingredients.
Put ingredients in order in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pineapple in bottom, then cherry pie filling. Sprinkle dry cake mix over fruit.
Cut butter in pieces and lay on top of mix.
Sprinkle nuts on top.
Bake 1 hour in 350° oven.

title: loretta lynn's dumplings
directions: Place dry ingredients in a bowl.
Cut butter into flour mixture.
Combine eggs and milk.
Stir into butter and flour mixture to make a firm dough.
Roll dough on floured board.
Cut or break into small pieces.
Drop a few at a time into simmering chicken broth.
Cook 2 or 3 minutes.

title: eggnog christmas salad
directions: Drain pineapple juice into saucepan; heat to boiling.
Soften gelatin in lime juice; dissolve in boiling pineapple juice.
Cool. Add eggnog and chill until partially set.
Fold in drained pineapple and celery.
Pour into mold; chill until firm.
Dissolve raspberry gelatin in boiling water.
Add cranberry-orange relish, stirring the mixture until relish is thawed.
Chill until mixture begins to thicken.
When eggnog mixture is almost firm, pour raspberry gelatin mixture on top.
Chill until set.
Unmold on salad greens.

title: chris austin's mazetti
directions: Saute pepper and onion in small amount of oil.
Add ground beef; stir and cook until meat is no longer pink.
Drain grease. Add rest of ingredients, except cheese.
Place in casserole dish that has been sprayed with Pam.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: raisin sauce for ham
directions: Mix water, sugar and cornstarch.
Boil on low until clear (thickens).
Add raisins, orange rind and orange juice.
Serve with ham.

title: homemade salve
directions: Heat all but
flax seed oil.
When melted, stir in flax seed oil, take
off stove and put in small jars.
This is very good salve for cuts and sore spots.

title: clam chowder
directions: Cook all vegetables and juice for 30 minutes or until vegetables are done.
Add clams last 2 minutes of cooking.
May add salt and pepper to taste.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour pans.
Mix pumpkin, eggs, oil and water.
Sift the flour, sugar, pumpkin spice, soda and salt.
Add dry ingredients to pumpkin mixture a little at a time.
Mix well.
Place in greased and floured loaf pans.
Makes 2 regular loaves or 3 small loaves.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour to 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: date loaf
directions: Mix sugar, milk and dates.
Cook to soft ball stage, boiling slowly.
Remove from fire and add butter and vanilla.
Beat until cool.
Add nuts.

title: caramel corn
directions: Big bowl of popped corn.

title: low-fat oven baked fried chicken
directions: Use a rolling pin and crush the crackers and Melba toast on a piece of waxed paper.
Place the flour on a small plate.
Pour the Egg Beaters on another small plate.
Pour the liquid Butter Buds into a large nonstick frying pan.
Turn stove on low to medium heat.
Coat the chicken breasts with flour.
Next dip them in Egg Beaters.
Next roll them in cracker crumbs to coat well.
Place them in the frying pan and cook until golden.
Cook on both sides. Remove from frying pan and place on a cookie sheet that has been sprayed with a nonfat cooking spray.
Turn oven to 350° and bake about 15 to 20 minutes or until crisp.

title: miniature cream cheese cakes
directions: Mix the ingredients together.
Put vanilla wafer in bottom of cupcake liner.
Fill with cream cheese filling 2/3 full.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool.
Put a spoonful of cherry pie filling on top.

title: hungarian goulash
directions: Place steak cubes, onions and garlic into crock-pot.
Stir in flour to coat.
Add in all other ingredients, except sour cream; cover.
Cook on low heat 8 to 10 hours.
Add sour cream about 30 minutes before serving; stir well.

title: crab imperial
directions: Mix the first 8 ingredients.
Put in buttered casserole and top with crumbs and paprika.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.

title: cream delight fruit salad
directions: Drain fruit cocktail juice and Mandarin orange juice.
Into separate cup, drain pineapple juice.
Keep separate.
Mix fruit cocktail, Mandarin oranges and pineapple chunks together.
Add sour cream.
Add marshmallows.
Mix well.
Add pineapple juice to consistency.
Add optional ingredients.
Chill 1 hour.

title: old fashion peanut brittle
directions: Bring 1/2 cup water to a boil.
Add sugar and syrup.
Stir until dissolved and boil it until it will spin a thread.
Now add peanuts and cook slowly until it turns golden brown.
Remove from heat and add butter, soda and vanilla.
Stir quickly and spread on large cookie sheet well buttered.
Cool and break and eat.

title: stir cookies
directions: Bring sugar, milk, butter and cocoa to a boil.
Boil for 1 1/2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and stir in oats and vanilla until well blended.
Spoon into sprayed muffin tins.
Let cool then remove with fork.
Store in air tight container.

title: cornflake candy
directions: Melt peanut butter and butterscotch tidbits over low heat. Pour over cornflakes and stir.
Drop by tablespoon onto waxed paper and chill for 10 to 15 minutes.
Place in container.

title: citrus poppy seed cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Spray Bundt pan with cooking spray. Use electric mixer and beat together orange juice, oil and eggs. Add cake mix to batter; mix until moistened. Continue to mix on high for 2 minutes. Fold in poppy seeds. Pour batter into Bundt pan. Bake 30 to 35 minutes. Invert cake onto cake plate; cool completely. Spoon icing over cake.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix sugar, flour and egg yolks together.
Mix well.
Add milk. Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Add vanilla.
Bring to a full boil.
Remove from heat.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Mix meat, onion, bread crumbs, parsley, seasonings, egg and milk together, then shape into walnut size balls.
Brown in hot skillet; remove from pan.
Stir flour, paprika, salt, and pepper into hot pan.
Add water and cream.
Return meatballs to gravy. Cook for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Boil oleo, milk and sugar for 2 minutes.
Add peanut butter, oatmeal and nuts.
Drop on greased plate or waxed paper.

title: easy chocolate cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large saucepan, cook chocolate pudding as directed on package.
Blend dry cake mix thoroughly into hot pudding for 1 to 2 minutes.
Pour into 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan, greased and floured, and sprinkle with chips and nuts.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: chicken wings
directions: Combine dressing, soy sauce and ginger.
Pour over chicken. Marinate in refrigerator several hours or overnight.
Place wings on broiler pan.
Broil 15 to 20 minutes, turning once.
Brush occasionally with marinade.
Makes 36 appetizers.
Serving suggestion:
serve chicken wings with horseradish or sweet and sour sauce.

title: chili
directions: Cook and drain hamburger in separate pan.
In large cooking pot, saute 1 tablespoon olive oil, onions and peppers.

title: mom's apple cobbler
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Melt butter in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
In a saucepan heat sugar and water until sugar melts.
Cut shortening into flour.
Add milk and stir with a fork only until dough leaves the side of the bowl.
Turn onto lightly floured board and knead just until smooth.
Roll dough out into a large rectangle, about 1/4-inch thick.
Sprinkle cinnamon over apples. Then sprinkle apples evenly over the dough.
Roll up dough like a jelly roll.
Slice dough into about 16 slices, 1/2-inch thick. Place in pan with melted butter.
Pour sugar syrup carefully around rolls (this looks like too much liquid, but crust will absorb it).
Bake for 55 to 60 minutes.
Makes 8 servings.

title: german fruit cake
directions: Cream together butter or oleo and sugar.
Add eggs to mixture and cream again.
Sift together flour, cinnamon, nutmeg and allspice.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with buttermilk and soda added to milk.
Fold in preserves, vanilla and pecans.

title: raisin scones
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine flours, sugar, baking powder, allspice, soda and salt. Cut butter into small pieces and work into flour with a pastry blender.
Beat eggs with buttermilk and stir into mixture along with raisins.
Turn dough out onto a floured board and knead for 2 minutes.
Shape into 2 thick circles, 5 inches each in diameter.
Cut each into quarters and place together in circles on a lightly greased baking sheet.
Bake in a preheated 400° oven for 20 to 25 minutes or until nicely browned. Makes 8 scones.

title: mary frances' christmas candy
directions: Melt margarine; add milk, coconut and sugar.
Mix with hands; roll into balls and chill.
After mixing by hand, it might need chilling just a little to roll.
Makes about 6 dozen small balls.

title: orange-raisin bran bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix flour, sugar, baking powder and salt in a large bowl.
Beat egg whites in small bowl; stir in milk, orange juice, oil and orange peel.
Add to flour mixture, stir until just moistened.
Stir in cereal and raisins.
Pour into greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Bake 1 hour or until toothpick comes out clean.
Cool 10 minutes.
Remove from pan.
Cool completely, cut in slices.

title: tuna casserole
directions: In large skillet, saute onion
and celery in butter or margarine.
Stir in tuna, soup, mayonnaise, milk, mushrooms and pimento.
Meanwhile, cook noodles and drain in colander.

title: veal olympic
directions: Pound the veal slightly.
Season with salt and pepper.
Flour the veal lightly.
Melt the butter in a skillet.
Brown the veal in the melted butter.
Add mushrooms and onions; simmer 3 minutes. Add cognac and flame.
Add sherry and simmer 2 minutes.
Add cream sauce and blend.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix corn meal, eggs, meat drippings, buttermilk and cream-style corn for corn bread mixture.

title: oven fried potatoes
directions: Scrub potatoes and cube (about size) for potato salad.
Put all ingredients in bowl and mix together.
Pour in 11 x 13-inch pan and bake at 450° for 35 to 45 minutes.
Stir about every 15 to 20 minutes.

title: boerenjongens cocktail
directions: Cook raisins, water and cinnamon stick about 20 minutes.
Add sugar and brandy.
Cook until dissolved.
Fill sterilized container with the mixture.
Seal tightly and let stand 3 months for best results.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all together; pour in 2-quart baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Sprinkle cheese on top.

title: oven eggs
directions: Melt butter in pan.
Combine salt, milk, pepper and flour. Put eggs into pan.
Cook until creamy in a 250° oven, stirring often.
Lower temperature.
May hold eggs up to 2 hours.
Serves 6 to 8 people.

title: fresh peach tarts
directions: Thoroughly
crush 1 cup peaches in saucepan.
Add water and cook 5 minutes.
Combine corn syrup, cornstarch and salt.
Add to cooked juice.
Cook until thick and clear (5 minutes).
Add butter and cool slightly.
Arrange the rest of the peaches in tart shells or pie shell and pour thickened mixture over fruit, coating thoroughly.
Chill; serve with whipped cream.
(Can add red food coloring to cooked mixture for color.)

title: egg nog(makes 2 gallons)
directions: Beat eggs and sugar until lemon colored.
Add milk and flavorings and beat well.
Whip the cream until stiff and fold into first mixture.
Add commercial egg nog; stir.
Sprinkle with nutmeg; chill and serve.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Mix dough by mixing the first 3 ingredients.
Sift remaining ingredients and add to mixture.
Roll into balls and then roll into mixture of 2 tablespoons sugar and 2 teaspoons cinnamon.
Flatten with fork.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes approximately 5 dozen.

title: chiffon berry pie
directions: Mix lemon juice and sweetened condensed milk with electric mixer.
Fold in Cool Whip and fresh berries.
Pour into pie crust. Refrigerate.

title: zucchini pineapple bread
directions: Combine eggs, sugar and oil.
Add flour, baking powder, salt and soda.
Add vanilla, drained pineapple and zucchini.
Grease and flour pans well.
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes at 325°.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream butter, shortening and sugar well.
Add eggs, one at a time, and blend.
Sift together flour, cocoa, salt and baking powder.
Add flour and milk alternately, starting and ending with flour.
Add flavoring.
Bake in large 10-inch tube pan, well-greased and floured.
Bake at 315° for 1 hour and 15 minutes. Let cool 10 minutes in pan and cool on rack for 5 minutes.
Then turn out onto plate.
Leave out the cocoa and add a little more flour if you want a plain cake.

title: dog or puppy chow snack
directions: Mix well. Healthy snack.

title: pot roast
directions: In roaster, place green beans in bottom.
Place roast in center of pan.
Arrange carrots and potatoes around the roast. Mix in small bowl the onion soup and cream of mushroom soup; spread over the roast.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Place in oven at 350° for 2 to 3 hours.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix well and chill at least 2 hours before serving.

title: oh henry!
directions: If you're tired of plain old Rice Krispies Treats, here's something different!

title: shrimp and rice
directions: Fry bacon and set aside.
Melt butter in drippings.
Add mushrooms with water, chopped green onions, shrimp and Worcestershire sauce.
Saute until done and add hot cooked rice. Put crumbled bacon on top and mix.
Serve with salad and rolls.

title: chinese pork and rice
directions: Cook rice in hot oil until golden brown. Add salt, water, bouillon cube and soy sauce. Cover and cook 20 minutes. Add rest of ingredients and 1/4 cup more water if necessary.
Cover tightly.
Cook 10 minutes more.
Makes 4 servings.

title: pimento cheese spread
directions: Grate cheese (room temperature).
Add sliced pimientos (juice also)
Add relish and olives and mayonnaise.
Use to stuff celery or for sandwiches.

title: raw apple cake
directions: Combine all ingredients and stir well, bake in 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: fresh coconut cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar together.
Add vanilla.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt together.
Add to creamed mixture, alternately with milks, beating well after each addition.
Stir in coconut.
Fold in beaten egg whites.
Pour into greased and floured 9-inch cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until done.
Cool before frosting.
Ice with 7 Minute Frosting and coconut.

title: chicken artichoke(low-fat)
directions: Mix salt, pepper and paprika.
Rub into chicken breasts.
Brown in 4 tablespoons butter.
Put into casserole and place artichokes around chicken.

title: red cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream shortening, sugar and eggs. Combine coloring and cocoa, mixing well.
Add cocoa mixture to creamed shortening.
Add salt, buttermilk, flour and vanilla, beating constantly.
Mix vinegar and baking soda.
Stir, do not beat, the vinegar mixture into the batter.
Bake in two (9-inch) greased and floured cake pans for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool.
When the cake is thoroughly cool, cut each layer in half to form 4 thin layers.
Put the following filling between the layers and on top of the cake.

title: butterscotch torte
directions: Beat together flour and margarine; add pecans and press into pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool.

title: impossible vegetable pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Lightly grease a pie plate (10 x 1 1/2-inch).
Heat 1-inch salted water (1/2 teaspoon salt to 1 cup water) to boiling.
Add broccoli; cover and heat to boiling.
Cook until almost tender, about 5 minutes.
Drain thoroughly.
Mix broccoli, onion, green pepper and cheese into pie plate.
Beat remaining ingredients until smooth (15 seconds in blender on high, or 1 minute with hand beater).
Pour into pie plate.
Bake until golden brown and knife inserted halfway between center and edge comes out clean.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes. Makes 6 servings.

title: mixed vegetable casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and place in a baking dish.
Top with crushed Cheez-It crackers.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: mini meatball soup
directions: In a deep pot over medium heat, add oil, chopped carrots, celery, onions and bay leaves. Season with salt and pepper. Cover pot and cook veggies 5 or 6 minutes, stirring occasionally. While the veggies cook, combine meat, egg, garlic, grated cheese, bread crumbs, salt, pepper and nutmeg.

title: dirt cake (in flowerpot)
directions: You will need a new plastic flowerpot, gummy worms, artificial flowers and a new small garden trowel.

title: fruit salad
directions: Let all fruits drain for 30 minutes.
Mix pudding and Cool Whip.
Add fruits, marshmallows and coconut.

title: chocolate sheath cake
directions: Put in 2-quart saucepan the oleo, cocoa, Crisco and water; bring to a boil.
Then add sugar and flour and stir.
Add eggs, buttermilk, soda and vanilla.
Mix and bake 20 minutes at 400°. Start frosting 5 minutes before cake is done.

title: fresh apple bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In mixing bowl, cream Crisco and 3/4 cup sugar.
Add eggs and beat well. Combine flour, salt, baking powder, soda, nutmeg and ginger.
Blend into creamed mixture; mix well.
Stir in the apples.
Spread in greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Sprinkle with a mixture of 2 tablespoons sugar and 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool, cut into bars.
Yields 36 bars.

title: apricot salad
directions: Boil pineapple (with juice), sugar and Jell-O 3 minutes. Cool.
Pour into bowl.
Add remaining ingredients to boiled mixture; mix.
Cover and refrigerate several hours.

title: smooth butter frosting
directions: Blend together butter and sugar.
Stir in milk and vanilla. For a thinner frosting, thin with more milk.

title: cowboy butter
directions: Mix together well with a mixer. Serve with bread or other desired foods.

title: sausage and egg casserole
directions: Brown sausage; break into pieces. Beat eggs with milk, bread, cheese, sausage, salt and mustard. Pour into 13 x 10 greased baking casserole. Put in refrigerator overnight. Take out 1/2 hour before baking. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Let stand and cool 10 minutes.

title: orange-lemon glaze
directions: Combine sugar, fruit rinds and juices.
Stir until well blended.
Spread over top and sides of cake.
Very good on pound cakes.

title: our family birthday cake
directions: Beat together.
Boil until a custard; set aside to cool.

title: veggie bars
directions: Chop green peppers, cauliflower, carrots, broccoli and green onion into small pieces.
Heat oven to 375°.
Place dough into 4 long rectangles.
Place rectangles crosswise into ungreased 15 x 10-inch jelly roll pan.
Press over bottom of pan to form crust. Seal perforations by pressing together with fingers.
Bake at 375° for 14 to 19 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool completely.

title: ham, egg & cheese bake
directions: Remove crusts from bread.
Grease 9x13-inch pan.
Line pan with 7 slices of bread.
Sprinkle grated bar of cheese over bread. Cover with diced ham then with rest of bread slices.
Beat together eggs, milk, dry mustard and salt.
Pour over top of bread.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Mix thoroughly shortening, sugar (3/4 cup) and egg.
Sift together and stir in flour, cream of tartar, soda and salt.
Roll into balls the size of small walnuts.
Roll balled cookies in mixture of 1 tablespoon sugar and cinnamon.
Place 2 inches apart on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake until lightly browned but still soft.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes about 2 1/2 dozen 2-inch cookies.

title: asparagus and green bean casserole
directions: Butter casserole dish.
Add asparagus and green beans.
Spread cheese over the vegetables.
Spoon cream of mushroom soup on top. Cook at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Take out of oven and place biscuits on top.
Return to oven, increase oven temperature and cook until biscuits are brown.

title: pickled green tomatoes(kosher style)
directions: Use small, firm, freshly-gathered green tomatoes.
Wash, dry and pack in sterilized jars.
Add a bud of garlic, 1 stalk celery and 1 green pepper (cut in fourths) to each quart jar.
Combine water, vinegar, salt and dill.
Boil together for 5 minutes.
Pour hot vinegar mixture over tomatoes to within 1/2-inch of the top of the jar.
Adjust screw band firmly tight.
*Process in boiling water bath 15 minutes.
Liquid enough to fill 6 quarts.
Tomatoes will be ready for use in 4 to 6 weeks.

title: raisin pie
directions: Line pie plate with pastry.
Simmer raisins in 1/4 cup water and orange juice for 5 minutes, covered.
Combine brown sugar, cornstarch, cinnamon, grated orange rind, salt and 1/4 cup water. Add to the raisins; bring to a boil, stirring well.
Remove from heat.
Add vinegar and butter.
Pour into pie shell; cover with top crust.
Sprinkle lightly with a mixture of cinnamon and sugar, if you wish.
Bake at 425° for 25 minutes.
Serve warm.
Serves 6.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Heat all ingredients to a boil.
Simmer on low heat until onion is tender.
Keep refrigerated until ready to use.

title: salmon dip
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Add the rest of the ingredients and mix well.
(Fingers work best!)
Chill and serve with Ritz crackers.

title: banana cake
directions: Cream shortening or oleo, brown sugar and white sugar together.
Add eggs, then flour, baking powder, baking soda, buttermilk and bananas.
Add nuts and vanilla.
(If chocolate chips are desired, mix into batter by hand.) Bake in large pan at 350°.
Cool and ice.

title: bailey's irish cream
directions: Put milk, eggs and cream into a blender and blend on high for 1 minute.
Add remaining ingredients and blend 1 more minute.

title: eloise's mincemeat
directions: Pour boiling water over tomatoes and drain.
Mix together with other ingredients.
Add spices and bring to a boil.
Let simmer 3 hours.
While hot, pack in hot sterilized jars and seal.
Process 20 or 30 minutes, if desired.
Can or freeze.

title: herbed crabmeat
directions: Pick over crabmeat to remove all shells and cartilage.
Heat the margarine until it bubbles and cook crabmeat in it until just heated through.
Season crabmeat with salt, pepper, lemon juice and herbs.
Serve on toast points and garnish with lemon wedges. Serves 4.

title: jungle bread
directions: In a large bowl, stir together the first nine ingredients. In a medium bowl, mix bananas, pineapple, oil and eggs.
Add all at once to oat mixture and stir until liquid is absorbed and mixture is thoroughly moistened (do not overmix).

title: shrimp dip
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Add rest of ingredients.
Pour into mold and chill.

title: barbecued ribs
directions: Flour and brown
ribs.	Put all ingredients in saucepan and boil; pour over ribs.
Bake at 325°, uncovered, 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: twice-baked potatoes(low-fat)
directions: Potatoes should be hot.
Cut a large oval out of the top of each potato skin; discard skin top.
With a small spoon, scoop out potato and place in a bowl with yogurt, margarine and 3 tablespoons cheese.
Mash together until smooth.
Mix in Italian seasoning, chives, salt and pepper to taste.
Stuff skins with potato mixture and top with remaining cheese.
Reheat at 400° about 5 minutes until cheese is melted but not brown.

title: taffy apple salad
directions: Mix marshmallows in drained pineapple; set aside.
In saucepan, mix juice, egg, sugar, flour and vinegar.
Cook until slightly thickened. When mixture has cooled, fold in the Cool Whip. Fold all into the pineapple mixture.
Add apples and peanuts.
Mix together.
Place in a glass serving bowl.
Add chopped peanuts to top for garnish.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Add all ingredients to whipped cream.
Freeze in paper baking cups in muffin tin.

title: corn bread dish
directions: Mix in pan you're baking in (9 x 13-inch).
Bake uncovered for 45 minutes at 325°.

title: chicken flautas
directions: Combine chicken, picante, onion and cumin; mix well.
Heat 1/2-inch oil in small skillet until hot.
Quickly fry each tortilla in oil to soften, about 2 seconds on each side.
Drain on paper towels.
Spoon 1 tablespoon chicken mixture and 1 tablespoon cheese down center of each tortilla.
Roll tightly; secure with wooden toothpick.
Place seam side down on baking sheet.
Bake at 400° for 18 to 20 minutes.
Remove toothpick.
Serve warm with guacamole and picante sauce.

title: green pea salad
directions: Drain peas.
Add onion, celery, pickle, eggs, salt, pepper and sugar.
Mix with mayonnaise and mustard; stir until creamy.
Good to eat with anything!
Sprinkle top with paprika.

title: deeeelicious apples
directions: Mix cheese, margarine, sugar and flour until well blended. Spread over drained apples in a 9 x 13-inch pan and bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Wonderful with beef, pork or poultry.

title: green salsa
directions: Put tomatillas and chilies in saucepan.
Add about 1 cup water and bring to a boil.
Boil, covered, until tomatillas and chilies are tender.
Drain.
Place in blender with sliced onions and cilantro.
Blend until pureed.
Salt to taste.

title: mezzeti
directions: Cook noodles and cool.
Cook pepper, onion and hamburger in a small amount of butter until tender.
Add soup and mushrooms and fold in noodles.
Place in casserole dish and put cheese on top. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: sausage bit
directions: Mix together; make into small balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 10 minutes or until lightly brown.
Serve hot, delicious for a coffee party.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Crush half of berries.
Add sugar and cornstarch; cook until clear.
Put other 1/2 of berries (drained) into shell.
Let cooked mixture cool.
Pour over berries in shell.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: apple pound cake
directions: Sift together flour, baking soda, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg. Set aside.

In a large bowl of electric mixer, beat together at medium speed the oil, sugar, eggs and vanilla until thoroughly combined. Gradually beat in flour mixture until smooth. Fold in apples, nuts and raisins.
Turn into greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until cake tests done.
Cool in pan on wire rack for 10 minutes.

title: diabetic cake
directions: Cream the butter and egg.
Add Sweet 'N Low and vanilla.
Sift dry ingredients together and add to the creamed mixture. Add applesauce.
Mix 4 minutes on medium speed.
Add nuts and dates. Pour in loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: sweet potato salad
directions: Place potatoes in large sauce pan, cover with water and boil gently until potatoes can be easily pierced with sharp knife (about 30-45 mins).
Drain.
When potatoes are cool, peel and dice.
In large bowl combine mayonnaise, mustard and salt.
Then stir in eggs, celery and onions.
Add potatoes stirring gently to mix. Cover and refrigerate for 2 to 4 hours.
Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: korean pulgogi
directions: For easy slicing, partially freeze meat.
Slice in 1/4-inch pieces.
Mix all ingredients, except rice, and toss with meat to cover.
Put foil over all.
Refrigerate 6 hours to let meat marinate.

title: chicken stuffing mix
directions: Spread chicken mixture over the half stuffing mix in the pan, then top with the reserved half of the stuffing mix.
Beat 2 eggs; add 1 3/4 cups milk.
Pour over casserole and refrigerate overnight or several hours.
Spread 1 can cream of chicken soup (undiluted) over top.
Bake at 325° for 40 minutes.
Sprinkle with grated cheese for last 10 minutes of baking time.

title: cottage pie
directions: *Could use half beef and turkey.

title: german chocolate pie
directions: Melt butter and chocolate together.
Beat eggs, sugar and flour at high speed for 3 minutes.
Add chocolate and beat 1 minute more.
Add vanilla and pecans.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Serve with whipped cream or topping.

title: easy chicken casserole
directions: Stir Cheddar cheese soup in a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish until smooth.
Gradually add milk.
Mix in remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: sweet potatoes delight
directions: Peel and slice potatoes about 1/2-inch thick.
Heat the oil in a heavy skillet.
Brown the potatoes quickly on both sides.
Pour off the oil.
Put all the potatoes in the hot skillet.
Sprinkle on the sugar, dot on the butter and pour the water over all. Cover and cook over medium heat until tender and the liquid is syrupy.

title: chow-chow
directions: Chop all vegetables like kraut.
Pour salt over and soak 2 hours in ice cubes.
Drain in colander.
Boil 3 cups vinegar, 2 cups water, 5 cups sugar, 1 tsp. turmeric, 1/2-box pickling spices. Put chow-chow in mixture until color changes.
Pack in jars and seal.

title: north beach rigatoni
directions: Brown whole sausages in 4-quart pot until thoroughly cooked. Remove sausages, cool and slice in 1/4-inch slices.

title: hot pineapple salad
directions: Drain pineapple; reserve juice.
Combine sugar and flour; stir in 3 tablespoons of the juice.
Add pineapple and cheese, mixing well.
Turn into well-greased 1-quart casserole dish.
Top with crushed crackers.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Remove stems from mushrooms to hollow the caps.
Chop the stems and green onions and saute in olive oil.
Mix stuffing mix according to package directions and add to sauteed mixture.
Fill mushroom caps with all the mixture; top with cheese and bake at 375° until cheese is melted.
Serve piping hot.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except green beans in double boiler until melted. Stir green beans into mixture and pour into casserole. Add French fried onion rings on top just before it is finished cooking. Bake at 300° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: gourmet potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes in skins until cooked, but not too soft.
Peel and shred.
In saucepan, melt cheese and butter.
Remove from heat and add sour cream, onion, salt and pepper.
Fold in potatoes. Put into greased 2 quart casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until heated.

title: mushroom-barley soup
directions: In
soup
kettle cook barley in 1 1/2 cups of the water until tender.
Add
the
remaining stock or water, tamari and sherry. In a separate pan
saute onions and garlic in butter. When they soften, add
mushrooms
and 1/2 teaspoon salt.
When all
is tender, add to
barley,
being
sure
to
include
the liquid. Add a generous grinding of black pepper and simmer 20 minutes, covered, over the
lowest
possible
heat.	Taste
to correct seasoning.

title: horseradish-ham filling(sandwich spread)
directions: Combine all ingredients, mixing well.
Chill.
Yields about 2 cups.

title: picante sauce
directions: Peel, core and chop tomatoes.
Combine tomatoes, onion, hot pepper, sugar and salt; cook gently for 45 minutes.
As mixture thickens, stir frequently.
Add vinegar and cook slowly until as thick as desired.
Pour boiling hot sauce into hot pint jars. Adjust lids.
Process 15 minutes in boiling water bath.

title: hamburger noodle casserole
directions: Brown the ground beef; drain.
Add remaining ingredients (except noodles and cheese) and mix well; set aside.
Cook noodles, drain and gently mix in with beef mixture.
Pour mixture into a casserole dish; top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: new england clam chowder
directions: Drain clams; reserve liquid.
Add enough water to liquid to measure 2 cups.
In large saucepan, cook pork or bacon until crisp.
Remove and set aside.
Add reserved clam liquid, potatoes and onion to drippings in pan.
Cover and cook for 15 minutes, until potatoes are tender.
Stir in clams, 2 cups milk and the cream.
Combine remaining milk and flour; stir into chowder. Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly.
Add Worcestershire sauce, 3/4 teaspoon salt and dash of pepper.
Sprinkle salt pork or bacon on top.

title: tiffany's attic green beans hollandaise
directions: Cook green beans and onion.
Drain.
Mix Hollandaise Sauce according to package directions.
Put beans and onion into casserole.
Gently stir in sauce to cover beans.
Serve warm.

title: chicken and bread crumbs
directions: Mix bread crumbs, garlic, parsley, salt and pepper. Dip chicken pieces into mixture. When coated, lay it in a pan sprayed with Pam. Sprinkle a little oil over each piece.
Bake at 350° for 2 hours.

title: snack pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Pat each biscuit on greased cookie sheet. Mix tomato sauce and oregano.
Spoon sauce on each biscuit. Sprinkle onions and cheese over tomato sauce. Bake 15 minutes or until crust is lightly brown.

title: pineapple passion
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender container.
Cover and blend at high speed until pineapple is finely crushed.
While blender is running, add 6 ice cubes one at a time.
Trim glasses with lime wedges.
Serves 4.

title: zucchini relish
directions: Cover zucchini, peppers, onions and salt with cold water and let set for 3 hours. Drain and add remaining ingredients. Mix and boil 5 minutes. Seal in sterile jars.

title: pineapple cheesecake squares
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix with fork until crumbly and press firmly and evenly in bottom of ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Bake until set, 15 to 20 minutes.

title: country biscuits
directions: Mix flour, sugar, baking powder and salt into bowl.
Cut in shortening thoroughly.
Stir in enough buttermilk to make a soft, fluffy dough.
Form dough into a ball on floured board.
Knead several times (do not overknead, just until smooth).
Roll out 3/4 to 1/2-inch thick.
Cut with biscuit cutter or glass.
Bake 10 minutes at 500°.
Yields about 1 1/2 dozen biscuits, depending on how large you make them.

title: frozen cream cheese dessert
directions: Beat cottage cheese at high speed until smooth.
Add sour cream, sugar and vanilla.
Pour into 8 paper cupcake size liners. Freeze until firm, at least 2 hours.
To serve, remove from liners; turn onto serving dishes.
Let stand for ten minutes.
Top as desired.
You may use chocolate sauce, strawberries, blueberries or cherries.

title: hamburger beans
directions: Brown hamburger and onion and drain.
Add pork and beans, sugar, tomato sauce and margarine.
Stir and simmer about 20 minutes.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix bananas and eggs in a large bowl; stir in flour, sugar, salt and soda.
Place batter in loaf pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Best if served warm and topped with cream cheese.

title: no roll sugar cookie
directions: Cream mixture until fluffy.
Add 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Sift 4 cups flour plus 2 tablespoons flour, 1 teaspoon salt, 1 teaspoon soda and 1 teaspoon cream of tartar.
Chill several hours and roll into balls teaspoon size.
Flatten with a glass.
Sprinkle each cookie with granulated sugar.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: blueberry cream salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Set aside to cool.
Stir in pie filling and lemon juice.
Chill 4 to 5 hours or overnight to set.
Top with combined 1/2 cup dairy sour cream and 1 tablespoon sugar.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Crumble and cook sausage; drain.
Beat eggs with milk.
Grease pan and place rolls in pan sealing edges together, creating a "pizza" crust.
On the crust (which is uncooked) place the rest of the ingredients in the following order: cooked sausage, hash browns, cheese, eggs (beaten and raw), Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: corn fairfax
directions: Simmer onion and celery in butter for 5 minutes. Add corn, green beans and parsley. Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, for 5 minutes. Add flour and seasonings. Blend in evaporated milk. Cook slowly for 4 minutes. Add eggs and mix well. Pour into shallow baking dish. Mix crumbs, butter and cheese. Sprinkle on top and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Melt oleo and stir into the stuffing mix.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Spread 1/2 the stuffing mix in bottom of casserole dish.
Pour remaining mixture of ingredients over and top with remaining stuffing mix.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: hawaiian rice
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in a heavy saucepan; bring to a boil.
Cover; reduce heat and simmer 15 to 20 minutes or until rice is tender and liquid is absorbed.
Set aside.
Bring 1/4 cup water to a boil in a saucepan.
Add peas.
Cover; reduce heat and simmer 5 minutes or until tender.
Drain; set aside.

title: apple cobbler
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Melt butter in 13 x 9-inch pan.
In saucepan, heat sugar and water until sugar melts.
Cut shortening into flour.
Add milk and stir with fork until dough leaves side of bowl.
Roll out and knead until smooth.

title: delicious hot chocolate
directions: Combine ingredients.
Use 1/3 cup mix to 1 cup hot water.

title: crunchy grape-nuts cereal
directions: Melt margarine, then add all other ingredients, except flour. Add flour last.
Bake in cake pans at 350° to 400° until done. When cooled, put through 1/4-inch Grape-Nuts screen.
Spread on cookie sheets and toast in slow oven until lightly browned and crisp.

title: sweet potato pone
directions: Mash potatoes with butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time. Whip or beat well.
Add spices and flavoring (vanilla first). Bake in no crust dish until firm and brown on top at 400°.

title: texas beans
directions: Brown hamburger with onion and pepper.
Drain.
Put all the beans in crock-pot with barbecue sauce.
Cook on high until bubbly.
Add hamburger mixture.
Turn on low and cook for at least 2 hours.
Do not stir until ready to serve.

title: pineapple cheese ball
directions: Combine first five ingredients in a mixing bowl and shape into a ball. Roll cheese ball in nuts. Serve with your favorite crackers.

title: pound cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: grandma furman's potato filling
directions: Brown onions in butter.
Add potatoes and torn bread.
Pour beaten egg over mixture.
Toss with spoon over medium heat until egg is completely cooked.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Pour boiling water over oats.
Let stand for 20 minutes. Cream white sugar, brown sugar, butter and eggs.
Stir in flour. Add vanilla and bake.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 60 minutes.

title: springtime layered dessert
directions: Dissolve lemon and orange gelatin separately in 1 cup of the boiling water each.
Add 1/2 cup cold water to each.
Pour each into separate 9 x 5-inch loaf pan; refrigerate until firm.
Cut into 1-inch cubes.
Layer 1/2 each of the gelatin cubes, marshmallows, strawberries and whipped topping in 2-quart serving bowl; repeat layers.
Refrigerate.
Garnish with additional marshmallows.

title: peanut butter treats
directions: Combine butterscotch chips and peanut butter in large saucepan.
Stir over low heat until smooth.
Remove from heat. Add Rice Krispies.
Stir until well coated.
Press mixture evenly into buttered 13 x 9-inch pan.
Chill until firm.
Cut into 2-inch squares.

title: grilled brats(with onion sauerkraut relish)
directions: Heat oil in a large skillet over medium heat.
Add sugar; cook, stirring constantly, until mixture turns a light caramel color, about 10 minutes (some sugar may harden).
Add onion, sauerkraut and salt; cook over medium heat for 15 minutes, stirring frequently.
Add vinegar and caraway seed; simmer for 30 minutes.
Use immediately or cover and refrigerate up to 3 weeks. Heat grill.

title: dirt cake
directions: In large mixing bowl, make pudding according to package, except use only 3 1/2 cups milk. In another bowl, combine cream cheese, butter and confectioners sugar.
Mix thoroughly and add to pudding mixture.
Mix completely, then add Cool Whip by hand. Crush cookies (I use my Salad Shooter).
Cookies will look like potting soil.
Start with a layer of cookies, layer of pudding and cookies, ending with cookies on top.
Make a couple of days ahead of time.

title: kona inn banana bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Grease and flour two 8 x 4-inch loaf pans.
Stir and toss together the flour, salt and soda.
Set aside.
In a large bowl, mix the shortening, sugar, mashed bananas, eggs and walnuts. Add the flour mixture and stir just until blended.
Pour into the prepared pans.
Bake for 65 to 70 minutes or until toothpick inserted into the center of bread comes out clean. Remove and allow to cool in the pans for about 5 minutes.
Turn onto wire racks to cool completely.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: salmon salad
directions: Refrigerate overnight (or at least several hours).

title: no bake - let dry molding clay
directions: Mix together; boil for 1 minute.
Stir constantly.
Let cool. Keep in airtight container.

title: old-time tomato bake
directions: Cut bread in 1/2-inch cubes. In skillet, cook bread in butter with basil until golden. Remove and wipe skillet clean.

title: tropical bread pudding
directions: Grease with butter an 11 3/4 x 7 1/2 x 3/4-inch baking dish. Mix pudding ingredients in order listed.
Put in baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Remove and cool at room temperature. Serve with Cool Whip.

title: baked cheese grits
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray 2-quart casserole with vegetable spray.
Set aside.

title: wine cake
directions: Beat together 5 full minutes. Bake in tube pan or Bundt pan at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: cheese stuffed mushrooms
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Line a large baking sheet with aluminum foil.
Lightly butter both sides of bread, using 4 tablespoons of oleo; arrange on prepared baking sheet.
Bake 5 minutes, turning once, or until lightly browned on both sides.
Remove from oven and set aside.
Use damp paper towels to wipe mushrooms, being sure to remove all dirt and sand.
Pat dry with paper towels.
Gently twist each mushroom stem to remove.
In a large bowl, toss mushroom caps in fresh lemon juice; drain.
Discard remaining juice.
Place 2 tablespoons melted oleo in bowl; add mushroom caps and toss again. Place one cap stem side up on each slice of toasted bread on baking sheet.
In a small bowl, beat egg with a fork; stir in cheese. Spoon cheese mixture into mushroom caps, dividing equally.

(At this point, mushroom caps can be covered lightly with plastic wrap and refrigerated for up to 1 hour before you broil and serve them.) Broil mushroom caps about 8 to 10 inches from heat source for 5 to 6 minutes or until golden brown.
Remove from broiler; use tongs to place on serving platter.
Place a walnut piece on top of each stuffed mushroom.

title: quickie rolls
directions: Combine the ingredients, mix well and spoon into greased muffin tin.
Bake in preheated oven at 400 degrees for about 12 minutes or until lightly browned.
Makes 6 large rolls.
Recipe may be doubled or tripled for more.

title: popcorn cake
directions: Melt butter and marshmallows.
Mix popcorn with marshmallow and butter mixture, add extras.
Press tightly into greased angel food pan.
Cool before serving.

title: banana split dessert
directions: Combine graham cracker crumbs and melted butter.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Combine powdered sugar, soft butter, vanilla and eggs.
Beat for 2 minutes.
Pour over prepared crust.
Top filling with sliced bananas, then sliced strawberries and lastly pineapple.
Frost with whipped cream and top with crushed nuts. Refrigerate at least 12 hours.
Serve with chocolate sauce and cherry if desired.

title: turkey potatoes
directions: Bake potatoes.
Meanwhile, saute turkey until cooked through. Add onion, pepper, Worcestershire, garlic, peppers and salt. Saute 3 to 5 minutes until onion is translucent.
Remove from heat.
Cut tops off potatoes and scoop out cooked potatoes, reserving shells.
Combine potatoes with milk and sour cream. Whip until smooth.
Spoon 1/4 of turkey mixture into each potato shell.
Top with whipped potatoes; sprinkle with bacon and paprika.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes or until hot and lightly browned.

title: zucchini boats
directions: Trim ends of zucchini.	Cook covered in boiling salted water for about 10 minutes.
Drain.
Cut in half lengthwise.
Scoop out center of each and chop.
Combine chopped zucchini, bread crumbs, onion, tomato, seasonings and margarine.
Toss lightly.
Fill each shell, place in shallow baking dish and bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes

title: cranberry salad(sugar-free)
directions: Place the gelatin in a medium bowl.
Pour boiling water over it, and stir until dissolved.
Add the cold water and stir in. Add the crushed pineapple (juice included) and stir in.
All the gelatin to chill slightly, then stir in remaining ingredients. Place mixture in serving bowl and allow to chill until set. Serves 6.

title: cinnamon-apple cornbread(a deliciously moist, noncrumbly cornbread.)
directions: Stir together the cornmeal, flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and cinnamon.
Blend the egg, applesauce and oil together and add to the dry ingredients.
Blend just until moistened.
Pour into a greased 8-inch baking pan and bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes. Serves 9.

title: irish soda bread
directions: Mix raisins and dry ingredients together.
Add eggs, margarine and buttermilk.
Mix well.
Put in a loaf pan.
Cut a cross on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes (until done).
Check with a knife by stabbing the center and knife comes out clean.

title: tortilla pinwheels
directions: Mix the cream cheese, dressing, garlic powder and onions. Spread on tortillas.
Spread equal amounts of the chiles, pimentos and olives on cheese.
Roll tortillas tightly; wrap in plastic wrap.
Chill at least 3 hours.
Slice rolls into 1-inch pieces. Enjoy!!

title: veal scaloppini
directions: Mix flour with salt and pepper.
Dredge veal and brown in butter, olive oil and garlic.
Add chicken stock and sherry. Cover and simmer 20 minutes or until veal is tender.
Add parsley, thyme and marjoram 10 minutes before cooking time is up. Mushrooms may be added.
Serve with rice.

title: pork chop bake
directions: Brown chops. Mix rest of ingredients.
Place in 8 x 10-inch casserole.
Top with pork chops.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: salmon croquettes
directions: Bone salmon and mix all until smooth and creamy. If dry, add juice from salmon. Mold into small croquettes. Roll in sifted meal and drop in deep boiling fat. Fry few at a time until done. Serve with Tartar Sauce.

title: chili no beans dip
directions: Grate the cheese.
Melt in saucepan the cheeses and chili (no beans).
Can be put in crock-pot on low heat to keep warm.
Stir occasionally. Serve with king size corn chips.

title: pineapple cream pie
directions: Mix flour and sugar.
Beat egg yolks and milk together.
Add egg mixture to flour and sugar mixture.
Add butter and pineapple; cook in double boiler until thick.
Pour into baked pie shell. Beat egg whites until stiff; put on top of pie and brown.

title: pistachio jello
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large mixing bowl, including the juice from the pineapple.
Put into cake pan.
Chill 2 hours. Top with miniature marshmallows.

title: dip
directions: Microwave first 2 ingredients until cheese is melted.
Add green onions, green peppers and green chilies.
Fold in hamburger.

title: brownies
directions: Melt chocolate and margarine in saucepan.
Remove from stove. Add rest of ingredients; stir until well blended.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch baking pan that has been greased and floured.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Cut into squares.

title: chocolate peanut butter squares
directions: Mix all ingredients except chips and press into a 13 x 9-inch pan. Melt chips in microwave and then spread on top of mixture. Refrigerate for about 25 minutes and then cut into squares.

title: nacho dip
directions: Blend the cream cheese and sour cream until smooth.
Add the remaining ingredients, but save some of the shredded cheeses as topping.
Mix well!
Pour into 12 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: italian bread
directions: Mix ingredients together. Then, mix in an additional 6 to 10 cups flour. Add extra water as needed. Knead until stiff. Coat lightly with oil; allow to rise until doubled. Form into 4 long rolls with hands and place on oiled pans, which have been sprinkled with corn meal. Allow to rise and then slit tops with serrated knife. Brush with melted butter or olive oil. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: chicken and spaghetti
directions: Stew and bone chicken (saving 1 1/2 cups broth).
Cook vegetables in broth until soft.
Mix vegetables, spaghetti and soup together.
Bake 30 minutes at 325°.
Pour on grated cheese and melt in oven.
If you use Velveeta, stir into spaghetti mixture and heat.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Chill at least 1 hour before serving.

title: italian spinach
directions: Cook spinach according to package directions.
Drain slightly. Add butter, cheese and egg.
Stir until well-mixed and egg is cooked.
Serves six.

title: moist 'n creamy coconut cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed on package, baking in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cool 15 minutes, then poke holes down through cake with a large fork.

title: chocolate chews
directions: In a saucepan, melt butter over medium heat.
Stir in corn syrup and cocoa; bring to a boil.
Remove from heat; stir in vanilla, 2 cups confectioners sugar and milk powder (mixture will be stiff).
Turn out onto a surface lightly dusted with confectioners sugar.
Knead in remaining confectioners sugar; knead 3 to 4 minutes longer or until stiff.
Divide into 4 pieces and roll each into an 18-inch rope.
Cut into 3/4-inch pieces. Wrap each candy in cellophane or waxed paper.
Store in refrigerator.
Yield: 8 dozen.

title: stuffed baked potatoes
directions: Bake potatoes for 1 hour (or longer) at 400° until soft.
Allow them to cool to the touch.
Cut potatoes in half lengthwise and carefully remove pulp, leaving a thin shell.
Place pulp in large bowl.
Saute green onions in 1/4 cup butter until soft, then add to bowl with the light cream, sour cream, salt, pepper and shredded cheese.
Beat until smooth.
Place stuffing in shells and sprinkle the paprika and remaining butter.
Place in a 13 x 9-inch baking pan and bake another 20 minutes or until heated through.
Potatoes may be stuffed ahead of time and refrigerated or frozen.
Reheat until heated through.

title: no name nut bar
directions: Mix
the
first
ingredients together.
Press into a jelly roll pan.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.
Melt the next
4 ingredients together.
Boil for 2 minutes.
Onto warm, baked mixture, pat 2 to 3 cups of cut up nuts (mixed is best). Spread boiled mixture over the entire mixture.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.
Do not overbake.
Loosen edges when warm, then cool and cut into squares.

title: cookies and cream cheesecake
directions: Combine cookie crumbs and margarine; press onto bottom and sides of 9-inch spring-form pan.
Soften gelatin in water.
Stir over low heat until dissolved.
Combine cream cheese and sugar, mixing at medium speed on electric mixer until well blended. Gradually add gelatin and milk, mixing until blended.
Chill until mixture is thickened but not set.
Fold in whipped cream.
