Reserve 1 1/2 cups cream cheese mixture; pour remaining cream cheese mixture over crust.
Top with cookies and reserved cream cheese mixture.
Chill until firm.

title: jonathan's favorite pound cake
directions: Cream together the butter and Crisco.
Add sugar, 1 cup at a time, beating well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating until yellow has disappeared.
Next, add flour, 1 cup at a time, alternating with milk.
Last, add vanilla and lemon extracts.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake in preheated oven at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Cool in pan for 10 minutes, then on wire rack.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: In a large pot, brown meat and chopped onion in olive oil. Add tomato sauce and wine.
I don't measure the spices, just sprinkle over entire top of sauce. Add garlic powder, pepper, basil, parsley and oregano to taste.
Add bay leaves, Worcestershire sauce and mushrooms.
Bring to a boil, turn down heat and simmer covered for 3 hours.

title: hot smokie links
directions: Cook links in a can of beer to which has been added red hot sauce.
Cook until liquid is about gone.

title: mexican fiesta omelet
directions: Spray a skillet with nonstick cooking spray.
Add bell peppers and onion; saute until onion in translucent.
Add tomato and basil and mix well.
Saute another minute.
Remove from pan and keep warm.

title: golden potatoes
directions: Peel, boil and slice potatoes.
Peel and slice onions.
Mix soup and sour cream.
Melt butter in large baking dish.
Layer potatoes, onions and soup mix and cheese.
Be sure to top with cheese.
Bake at 400° until golden brown.

title: hot shrimp dip
directions: Can be made ahead and heated in a double boiler.
Serve with crackers or chips.

title: easy fruit crumble
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease or spray with vegetable Pam spray, 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread pineapple with juice on bottom of pan.
Top with cherry pie filling.

title: round steak for crock-pot
directions: Cut steak into 5 to 6 serving size pieces.
Place in crock-pot.
Add dry onion soup mix, water and mushroom soup. Cover and cook on low 6 to 8 hours.
Good with mashed potatoes.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix ingredients.
Add seasoning salt to taste.
Will keep in closed container up to a week.

title: icebox fruit cake
directions: Combine ingredients in a large mixing bowl.
Mix well with your hand.
Fill a cracker box lined with foil and refrigerate for about 2 weeks.
Tear cracker box away from filling and you have a nicely shaped fruit cake.

title: tuna salad
directions: Cook the noodle macaroni until tender.
Mix together the macaroni, tuna, bell pepper, hard-boiled eggs, celery, cucumber and green olives in large bowl.
Add mayonnaise to taste. Sprinkle top with paprika.

title: chocolate covered peanut butter crackers
directions: Melt baking chocolate and paraffin.
Cool slightly.
Spread peanut butter on crackers.
Dip in chocolate, peanut butter side first, then, turn over and dip again.
Drain and place on waxed paper to set.
Makes about 35.

title: cream cheese ball
directions: Chop shallots into fine pieces.
Drain pineapple well.
Mix all together.
Can form into a ball or put in dish as a spread.

title: nancy's angel hair pasta
directions: Marinate sun dried tomatoes, artichoke hearts, black olives in juice of 1 lemon and olive oil for 3-4 hours.
Cook and drain angel hair pasta and toss marinade and veggies into pasta. Sprinkle with fresh tomato, onions, parsley and
parmesan cheese.

title: icebox bread and butter pickles
directions: You will also need 1 gallon glass jar.

title: cavatini
directions: Cook noodles in saltwater. Cook hamburger meat with onion; drain off all grease. Drain noodles. Put layer of noodles on bottom of large casserole dish, then put dots of cream cheese over noodles, then layer half the ground beef, then half the

spaghetti sauce, then half the Cheddar cheese. Sprinkle garlic salt and Italian seasoning to taste. Then repeat all layers. Top with Mozzarella cheese and seasonings. Cover with aluminum foil and bake at 350° about 30 to 40 minutes.

title: kahlua pecan pie
directions: Line a 9-inch pie plate with pastry and chill.
Preheat oven to 400°.
Cream together butter, sugar, flour and vanilla.
Mix well.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Stir in Kahlua, corn syrup, milk and pecans.
Mix well.
Pour into pie crust.
Bake for 10 minutes, then reduce heat to 325° and bake until firm (about 40 minutes).
Chill.

title: squash balls
directions: Cook
squash
dry,
adding salt, pepper and diced onion during last
five minutes.
Put mixture in refrigerator until cold.
Add egg and Ritz crackers;
roll in small balls.
Roll these into cornmeal and fry in hot oil until golden brown.

title: honey bear buns
directions: Cream butter and sugar in small bowl.
Blend in honey and vanilla.
Add eggs, 1 at a time; beat well after each.
Combine flour, cocoa and salt.
Gradually add to cream mixture.
Stir in nuts.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: friend ship
directions: Mix them up for 12 minutes.
Preheat the oven for 2 minutes and then put them in the oven for 5 minutes.
Set the oven for 150°.
Serve warm or cold.

title: best cutout cookies
directions: Cream the shortening and sugar. Add eggs and vanilla. Sift flour, baking powder and salt together.
Blend into creamed mixture.
Roll out small amount on floured board.
Cut out with cookie cutters. Bake at 350° until light brown. Do not overbake.

title: raspberry brownies
directions: Melt butter and chocolate. Add sugar, eggs, vanilla and almond. Stir flour into mixture just until combined. Spread in 9 x 13 baking pan. Drop jam into mixture by teaspoonful and run knife through. Bake 35 minutes at 350°.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Mix together first 3 ingredients and let stand in ice cubes 3 hours; drain.
Combine alum, sugar, vinegar, celery salt and turmeric; do not heat.
Add to cucumbers and onions.
Can be frozen.

title: good neighbor loaf
directions: Sift dry ingredients; blend all ingredients until thoroughly mixed.
Pour into greased 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for metal pan or 325° for glass pan for 1 hour.
Remove from pan; cool on rack.

title: oatmeal chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix sugar and shortening.
Add eggs, vanilla and water.
Then add flour, baking soda and salt, mixing well.
Add oatmeal and chocolate chips.
Drop on cookie sheet and bake at 375° until done.

title: quindim(brazil)
directions: Mix sugar and coconut.
Add unbeaten eggs, salt and margarine to coconut mixture and mix.
Bake in moderate oven at 325° in greased 8-inch square Pyrex, which has been placed in a pan of hot water.
Bake until set and golden brown.

title: spinach souffle
directions: Beat eggs with flour.
Add spinach, cottage cheese, Cheddar cheese, butter, nutmeg, salt and pepper.
Pour into a 1 1/2-quart greased casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes or until set.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Mix all, except cabbage leaves.
Roll mixture into softened cabbage leaves.
(Soak leaves 2 to 5 minutes in boiling water.) Fasten with toothpicks.
Wrap in foil and cook over coals until tender, about one hour.

title: sad cake
directions: Mix and pour into a 13 1/2 x 11-inch greased sheet cake pan. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Cut into delicious chewy bars.

title: pina colada cake
directions: Bake cake in square 9 x 12-inch pan.
When done, poke holes all around cake.
Then pour condensed milk all over cake.
Spread can of coconut on top of cake, then pineapple.
Let cool for about 2 hours and top with Cool Whip.

title: corn casserole (2)
directions: Mix all together and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix graham crackers and melted butter; press in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Beat at high speed for 15 minutes the following: confectioners sugar, eggs and 2 sticks of butter.
Pour over crust.
Slice banana over mixture, cover bananas with pineapple, then strawberries.
Cover with Cool Whip.
Chill and serve.

title: potato soup
directions: In a Dutch oven, place celery, onion and carrot.
Add 4 cups water and salt and pepper.
Cook until partially done.
Add diced potatoes (more water if needed) and bacon.
Cover and cook until potatoes are done.
Add 2 cans evaporated milk.
Add potato flakes. Stir and simmer.
Freezes real well.

title: deluxe pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs slightly.
Mix in the next 5 ingredients, then add the nuts.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake in a 400° oven for 15 minutes.
Reduce temperature to 350°.
Continue baking for 30 to 35 minutes.
(Filling should be slightly less set in center than around edges.)

title: crispy pork chops
directions: Trim fat from pork chops and score to prevent curling during baking; dip in milk; lay one side down on crushed corn flakes; place pork chops in foil lines pan with corn-flake side up. Sprinkle black pepper and any remaining crushed corn flakes over the pork chops.
Bake 45 to 60 minutes at 375°, depending on thickness of pork chops.

title: candy bars
directions: Put the first 3 ingredients in pan; heat to bubbling.
In separate bowl (large), mix flakes and Krispies with heated mixture.
Cool in refrigerator for 1 hour, then shape into balls or bars.
Melt chocolate bits and wax together.
Dip bars into melted chocolate.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Place bread in buttered casserole dish.
Sprinkle with cheese, then sausage.
Beat remaining ingredients and pour over mixture. Refrigerate overnight.
(This is required.)
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Let stand 5 to 10 minutes after coming out of the oven (this allows it to "gel").

title: dill bread
directions: If unable to find creamed cottage cheese, buy small curd and blend in blender.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Make a layer of soup, layer of asparagus and a layer of onion rings, alternating until all ingredients are placed in casserole. Top with cheese.
Cook at 350° until heated through.

title: orange julius
directions: Put all ingredients in a blender.
Blend well until smooth and fluffy.
Pour into glasses.
Enjoy!

title: chicken salad supreme
directions: Combine all ingredients and toss lightly.

title: pea casserole
directions: Cook frozen peas in boiling salted water for 3 minutes. Drain.
Saute onion and butter.
Add pimentos, water chestnuts and mushroom soup.
Add drained peas and cover the top with onion rings.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes in 350° oven.

title: cornmeal biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease baking sheet; set aside.
In medium bowl, combine all-purpose flour, cornmeal, sugar, baking powder and salt.
With pastry blender or 2 knives, cut in vegetable shortening until coarse crumbs.
Stir in enough scalded milk to make a soft dough.
On floured surface, knead dough for 1 to 2 minutes until just smooth.
Roll out into 1/4-inch thick rectangle.
Cut into 12 equal squares.
Place on prepared baking sheet.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes until lightly browned.
Serve warm. Makes 12 biscuits.

title: holy smoke
directions: Crust:
Mix flour, 1/2 cup nuts and melted margarine.
Spread in 9 x 9-inch pan and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Cool.

title: bread or buns
directions: Mix sugar, salt, yeast, and some flour.
Add water, vinegar, and oil.
Add more flour.
Knead to make a dough that is soft and easy to work with.
Let rise for 15 min.
Punch down.
Let rise until doubled in bulk.
Form into buns.
Let rise for 1 hour or until almost doubled.
Bake at 400°F for 15 - 20 min.

title: simple spaghetti
directions: Brown hamburger meat in skillet; drain.
Add tomato sauce and tomato paste; mix well.
Add a little water if necessary to reduce the thickness.
Let simmer for 30 minutes.
Season as desired. Prepare spaghetti according to package.
Goes well with tossed salad.

title: chocolate icebox pie
directions: Mix
oleo,
flour
and	nuts
together.
Press	in
8 x 12-inch
or 7 x 10-inch Pyrex oblong dish (bottom only).
Bake for 20
minutes at 325° (do not brown).
Let cool.
Mix cream cheese and
powdered
sugar
together and spread mixture over crust. Cover with your favorite chocolate pie filling recipe. Top with Cool Whip and refrigerate.

title: never fail rolls
directions: Combine 1 teaspoon sugar, yeast and warm water.
Let stand 5 to 10 minutes, until yeast begins to foam.
Thoroughly mix in a large bowl warm milk, butter, sugar and egg.
Stir in yeast mixture and flour, adding a bit more if necessary to make a soft, pliable dough.
Turn dough out onto floured surface and let rest while you clean and butter bowl.

title: mexican punch
directions: Mix and refrigerate.
Add more sugar, if desired.

title: molasses crinkles
directions: Mix in order given; form into balls.
Dip in granulated sugar and bake at 350° to 375°.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix 3 cups cold milk and both packs vanilla pudding mix.
Beat on low speed until thick. Add 1 cup sour cream and 8 ounces Cool Whip to pudding mix.
Beat on low speed until mixed well. Layer dish with crackers, bananas and then 1/2 of mix.
Add another layer of crackers, bananas and rest of mix. Top with vanilla wafers.

title: ham balls
directions: Mix together and form into balls.

title: cooked lettuce dressing
directions: Mix together; cook until dissolved and hot.
Take a head of lettuce and break apart and wash.
When dressing is done, add to lettuce that you are going to eat.
Toss slightly; serve hot.

title: turkey chili
directions: *For milder chili, substitute chopped tomatoes.

title: spice cake or prune cake
directions: Beat eggs.
Add remaining ingredients except nuts.
Beat well. Fold in nuts.
Cook 1 hour at 350° in greased and floured tube pan.

title: easiest key lime pie
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Beat egg yolks until light in color. Add milk and beat lightly.
Add lime juice and beat until smooth. Pour into pastry shell.
Beat egg whites until soft peaks form. Add sugar gradually and continue to beat until stiff peaks are formed.
Pile meringue on top of pie and bake 4 minutes.

title: apple and orange slaw
directions: Place first 3 ingredients in a bowl, tossing to combine. Combine mayonnaise and brown sugar.
Add this mixture to cabbage mixture and coat well. Cover and chill 1 hour.
Yields 4 servings.

title: special k loaf
directions: Mix and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: sheep dip cookies
directions: Mix cream cheese, butter, sugar, vanilla and Sheep Dip until fluffy.
Mix in flour until blended.
Divide dough in fourths; shape into flattened rounds.
Wrap and chill 2 hours.
Heat oven to 350°.
On well floured surface roll dough to 1/8-inch thickness.
Cut with scalloped sheep-silhouette cookie cutter. Place 1/2-inch apart on cookie sheets.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes until lightly browned around edges.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar before cool.

title: red beans and rice salad
directions: Mix together and chill. Serve.

title: chocolate butterscotch bars
directions: Add margarine to sugar and mix well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating thoroughly after each.
Add sifted dry ingredients and mix.
Add nuts, chocolate chips and vanilla.
Spread into greased 15 x 10 x 1-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.
Cut while warm.

title: corn fritters
directions: Mix flour, baking powder and salt.
Mix the egg and corn together.
Add to flour mixture.
Heat corn oil in large pan and drop batter by tablespoon into hot oil, one layer at a time.
Fry 2 minutes on each side until golden brown.
Drain on absorbent papers (16 fritters).
Good served with honey mixed with butter or maple syrup.

title: cereal and nut snack mix
directions: Melt chocolate in oven at just under 200°.
Add remaining ingredients and stir until cereal and nuts are coated with chocolate.
Pour out onto wax paper and let harden.
Break into pieces.

title: carrot mold
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients.
Mix well and place in a greased round mold.
Mixture will be thick (stiff) so spread as evenly as possible into mold.
Bake in 350° oven for 50 to 60 minutes.
Use toothpick to judge if mold is done.
Good in place of bread or rolls.

title: orange kiss-me cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour bottom of 13 x 9-inch cake pan.

title: green beans creole
directions: Cook onion in butter until tender, but not brown.
Add chili sauce, salt and drained beans.
Heat through, stirring often.

title: buttery peanut brittle
directions: Heat and stir sugar, syrup and water in 3-quart saucepan until sugar dissolves.
When syrup boils, blend in margarine.
Stir often after 230° on candy thermometer.
Add peanuts at 280°.
Stir constantly to hard crack stage (305°).
Remove from heat and quickly stir in baking soda, mixing well.
Pour onto 2 buttered cookie sheets.
Cool and then break.

title: white high frosting
directions: Cook flour and milk until thick.
Refrigerate until completely cooled.
Beat until very fluffy the remaining ingredients, then add the cooled flour mixture.
Continue to whip until very fluffy.

title: gingerbread in a cup
directions: Will need 5 ounce paper cup.

title: no fail cornbread
directions: Mix all dry ingredients together.
Add oil, eggs, buttermilk and onion, if desired.
Bake in greased skillet in preheated oven at 450° for 20 to 25 minutes (until golden brown).

title: chocolate ice tubs
directions: Mix egg, syrup and milk.
Stir with wire whisk.
Add water. Pour into ice tubs.
Freeze.
Makes 6 Tupperware tubs.

title: versatile cheesy chicken 'n rice supreme
directions: Cook chicken in water seasoned with salt, 1 tablespoon Chefway oil and 1/8 teaspoon minced garlic.
Remove chicken when done. Cool, bone and cut into cubes.
Save broth; add bouillon cube. Cook rice in broth.

title: chiles rellenos
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray shallow 2-quart casserole or a 12 x 8-inch baking dish with nonstick cooking spray.
Discard seeds from chiles.
Slice cheese into same number of pieces as there are chiles.
Place 1 slice of cheese in middle of each whole chile. Arrange stuffed chiles in casserole.

title: banana nut cake
directions: Cream together sugar and shortening.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each.
Add flour alternating with milk and soda. Add banana and nuts; beat well. Put into layer pans that have been greased and floured.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: blueberry sauce supreme(for diabetics)
directions: In a saucepan, combine Splenda, orange juice and cornstarch. Stir until smooth. Add blueberries and bring to a boil.
Boil for 2 minutes, stirring constantly. Use as a topping for pancakes or waffles.

title: sherbet
directions: Liquefy the pineapple.
Mix all ingredients well and freeze, stir occasionally.

title: low-fat chicken-corn chowder
directions: Cook chicken breasts in water until done; set aside to cool. Strain liquid that chicken was cooked in and add onion, potatoes, corn and bouillon cubes to it.
Add water to cover.
Cook until vegetables are tender.
Break chicken into pieces and add to vegetables.
Add cornstarch-water mixture to thicken.
Add canned milk.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Spread beans in bottom of loaf pan.
Cook ground meat and drain off all the grease.
Add taco mix, onion flakes and chilies. Cook slowly a few minutes and spread mixture over beans.

title: hot apple cider
directions: Put apple cider in a crock-pot.
Use a tea ball.
In tea ball, put 1 teaspoon whole allspice and excess cloves.
Use a whole orange, making slits down orange from top to bottom.
Use 1 tablespoon whole cloves; stick in rind of orange.
Put the leftover cloves in tea ball with the allspice.
Mix with apple cider in the crock-pot.
Float cinnamon sticks in cider.
Heat to serve.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Spread hamburger over bottom of 13 x 9-inch dish. Scatter onion soup mix over meat.
Add all cans of vegetables, drained. Spread soups over all vegetables, saving the Cheddar cheese soup as your last soup to spread.
Spread Tater Tots on top.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Bake at 350° for about 1 1/2 hours.

title: no bake orange balls
directions: Thaw orange juice.
Do not dilute!
Crush wafers into crumbs with rolling pin in plastic bag.
Mix crumbs, coconut and 3/4 cup sugar.
Stir orange juice into mixture.
Form into 1-inch balls. Roll balls in remaining coconut and confectioners sugar.

title: creamy potato salad
directions: Place potatoes in 3-quart saucepan.
Add enough water to just cover potatoes.
Cover and heat to boiling; reduce heat to low. Cook, covered, 30 to 35 minutes or until potatoes are tender; drain.
Cool slightly; cut potatoes into cubes.

title: oatmeal toffee lizzies
directions: Combine sugars and shortening, add eggs, milk and vanilla; mix well.
Add flour, soda and salt, mix well.
Stir in oats, chips and nuts by hand.
Refrigerate for 30 minutes for easier handling. Make 1 1/4-inch balls.
Place 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Cool and store in airtight container.

title: houston breakfast buffet
directions: Wake up early.
Stand in line.
Take a look at the scrumptious buffet.
Go back to hotel room and call room service or eat junk food.

title: men folk's cornbread
directions: Combine all ingredients together; mix well.
Heat a well-greased 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking pan in oven at 400° for 3 minutes or until very hot.

title: onion casserole
directions: Peel and slice onions into thin rings.
Saute slowly in butter until limp.
Pour 1/2 of the onions into a greased casserole. Cover with Parmesan cheese and cracker crumbs.
Repeat layers. Bake in a preheated oven for about 25 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes about 6 to 8 servings.

title: party mix
directions: Combine salad dressing mix and dill weed in a large bowl; add cereal, Ritz Bits, pretzels and nuts and toss lightly.
Drizzle oil over mixture.
Stir well.
Place in a large paper bag.
Fold to close.
Let stand for 2 hours, shaking occasionally.
Store in an airtight container.
Yield:
16 cups.

title: broccoli-cheese soup
directions: Simmer all ingredients in crock-pot or on stove top.
Cooked rice can be added, or soup can be served over rice.

title: oatmeal-butterscotch cookies
directions: In mixing bowl, cream sugars and butter.
Add eggs and vanilla.
In another bowl, mix flour, soda, salt and cinnamon together.
Gradually add to butter mixture; mix with mixer.
Stir in oats and morsels.
Drop by rounded teaspoon onto ungreased baking sheets.
Bake in preheated oven at 375° for 7 to 8 minutes. Cool some before removing cookies from baking pan with spatula. Store in airtight container.
Makes 4 dozen cookies.

title: cranberry banana bread(food processor recipe)
directions: Place steel blade in work bowl; add pecans and fine chop.
Set aside in a bowl.
Reinsert steel blade in work bowl; add cranberries and fine chop.
Drain and set aside in another bowl. Rinse work bowl and reinsert steel blade.
Add banana, sugar, butter, milk, egg and orange peel.
Process until smooth.
Mix together flour, baking powder, cinnamon and salt; add to work bowl.
Process with 3 on/off turns, just until flour disappears. Do not overmix! Transfer to a mixing bowl and gently stir in pecans and cranberries.
Mix will turn pink.
Turn into a greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 60 to 65 minutes.
Cool in pan for 10 minutes, then remove to rack and cool completely. Yields 1 loaf.

title: kelli's perfect pork roast
directions: With fat side up, place on rack in roasting pan. Sprinkle with salt and pepper and a little garlic powder. Bake, uncovered, until browned well.
Tent with foil.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes per pound. Surround with sauerkraut the last 20 to 30 minutes. Remove ties, slice and serve.
It's great!

title: boiled cookies
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients in skillet.
Bring to a full boil. Boil for 2 full minutes.
Remove from heat.
Quickly add peanut butter, oats, nuts and vanilla; stirring fast.
When completely mixed, drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto wax paper.
Let cool at room temperature.

title: french apple cake
directions: Peel and dice apples; set aside.
Sift together the dry ingredients; set aside.
Beat eggs and sugar and add oil and vanilla.
Add half of flour mixture to egg mixture and mix well. Add remaining dry mixture and mix well.
Stir in diced apples and nuts.
Pour into greased tube or Bundt pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: juice de san marino(designed to use your home grown citrus with a flair!)
directions: Ahead of Time:
Squeeze and freeze (or use immediately) juice from citrus in your yard.
Oranges and tangerines for the best base.
Freeze in 8 ounce containers for later use.

title: apple butter
directions: Put applesauce in large pan.
Add sugar, cinnamon and allspice.
Cook at a full rolling boil for 2 minutes, stirring carefully.
Remove from heat and at once stir in Certo.
Stir until well mixed.
Skim off foam with metal spoon.
Put in scalded glasses and top with melted paraffin.
Yields about 10 to 12 medium glasses.

title: clemons goulash
directions: Saute onion in oil; add ground chuck and brown.
Add Spanish rice and part or all of the beans and seasonings.
Simmer for 30 minutes.
Add cheese and/or Fritos if you wish.

title: vegetable bars
directions: Spread out flat the can of crescent rolls in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 8 to 9 minutes.
Mix the cream cheese, Miracle Whip or sour cream and Ranch dressing.
Spread evenly on top of crescent rolls.
Chop cauliflower, broccoli, green onion and tomato.
Press on top of cream cheese mixture. Chill 2 hours. Top with sharp Cheddar cheese.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream
butter and Crisco thoroughly.
Add eggs one at a time, beating after each egg.
Add baking soda and sour cream. Add sugar, flour and flavoring.
Mix well.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours in 10-inch tube pan.

title: pepsi pot roast
directions: Mix the mushroom soup, dry onion soup mix and Pepsi together in the bottom of the crock-pot. Place the roast in the mixture and cook on medium-high or high for 6 to 8 hours. Meat will be very tender in its own gravy. Serve with rice, potatoes or noodles.

title: texas hash
directions: Brown ground beef, green pepper and onion.
Stir in tomatoes, rice, chili powder, salt and pepper.
Pour in greased casserole dish.
Cover and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Remove; cover and bake 15 minutes longer.
Add water if necessary.

title: sour cream cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour in a greased tube pan or greased 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
(Be careful not to overmix.)
Bake according to temperature directions on cake mix box.

title: no cook boiled custard
directions: Combine pudding mix with a little milk and beat for 5 minutes with a mixer.
Add sugar and Cool Whip.
Beat 3 more minutes. Stir in vanilla.
Pour in container and refrigerate.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: chicken ala orange
directions: In large skillet, brown chicken in butter.
Season with salt and pepper.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer, covered, for 25 to 35 minutes, or until tender.

title: no cholesterol chocolate cake
directions: Beat for one minute in a bowl.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 30-40 minutes.
Cool and frost.

title: pepper steak
directions: Cut steak into bite size pieces.
Roll in flour and fry until brown.
Meanwhile, cut peppers into strips.
After meat has browned, place in 3 quart pot.
Cover with water.
Add soy sauce and peppers.
Let come to a boil.
Reduce heat and cover.
Simmer until meat is done, about 1 hour.
Serve over hot rice.

title: chicken brunswick stew
directions: Cook chicken in water to cover with 1 cup chopped celery and 1 small chopped onion.
When chicken is tender, let cool.
Take off bones and chop fine.
Combine all ingredients and simmer 2 hours. Stir often, as the corn will stick.
Sometimes I wait until the last hour to put corn in so I won't have to stir as often.
Eat with crackers or garlic toast.

title: mizuno-style fried fish
directions: Scale and clean fish; sprinkle salt and pepper.
Pan-fry fish in vegetable oil until golden brown.
In the meantime, heat peanut oil in a pot.
After removing cooked fish from pan, place it in a plate (make sure it can withstand hot oil!).
Sprinkle chopped ginger on and around the fish.
Carefully pour the hot peanut oil over the entire fish.
Be careful!
The oil will splatter. Finally, garnish with green onions and shoyu.

title: quick dessert
directions: Mix together flour, margarine and nuts; press into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes; let cool.
Blend together powdered sugar and cream cheese; add 1/2 the Cool Whip.
Spread over baked crust.
Mix together pudding and milk until thick; spread over cream cheese mixture.
Top with remaining Cool Whip.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs until light and fluffy.
Add sugar, vanilla and oil. Blend well.
Stir in grated zucchini.
Sift flour, baking soda and cinnamon.
Blend with creamed mixture.
Fold in nuts.
Turn into two greased and floured 9 x 5-inch pans.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: homestyle mac and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni noodles.
Place 1/2 in 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Top with half of each ingredient, then place the rest of ingredients in baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: crunchy ice cream squares
directions: Remove ice cream from freezer to soften as you prepare the crunchy base for dessert.

title: skillet sausage and sauerkraut
directions: Empty potato slices and packet of seasoned mix into 10-inch skillet. Stir in amount of water called for on package. Add enough water to reserved sauerkraut liquid to measure 2/3 cup. Stir liquid, sauerkraut and caraway seeds into potatoes. Heat to boiling; stir occasionally. Reduce heat, cover and simmer 30 minutes. Arrange sausage on top. Cover. Cook 10 minutes longer. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: chocolate sheath cake
directions: Mix flour and sugar in a large bowl.
Put margarine, cocoa, water and shortening in heavy saucepan and bring to boil.
Pour mixture over dry ingredients and mix together well.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well and pour into prepared (greased and floured) 11 x 16-inch pan.
Bake 20 minutes at 400°.

title: fresh cut beans with almonds
directions: Cook French-cut beans two-thirds required time.
Add soup and slivered almonds.
Place in casserole dish.
Mixture can then be topped with bread crumbs or cheese of your choice.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes, covering when bread crumbs start browning.

title: party cheese ball
directions: Let cream cheese soften.
Mix cream cheese and pineapple with a fork.
Add pepper, onion and pecans.
Mix well.
Shape into a ball and roll in remaining pecans.
Wrap in plastic wrap; chill overnight.
The longer it chills the better.

title: butch's chili
directions: Cook meat in large pot.
Sprinkle with salt.
Pour 1 pint water over salt.
Cook 1 1/2 hours until meat is tender.
Stir often.
Use low heat at all times.
Grind and render suet; strain and let cool.
Grind pepper pods, onions and garlic twice.
Once use the chili plate, then
the sausage plate.
After meat is tender, pour rendered suet over it; stir and cook 5 more minutes. Then pour all spices (ground and dry) on top of meat.
Let them melt, then stir in and cook 5 more minutes.
Now it is ready to eat.

title: west coast chicken
directions: Combine salt, pepper, orange juice concentrate, butter, ginger and soy sauce.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Grease large pizza pan.
Slice cookies and press into pan to form 1 large cookie.
Cook at 350° for 12 minutes.
Cool in pan. Remove from pan and wash pan and replace cookies or may serve from large flat platter.
Mix Cool Whip and cream cheese; spread over cookie.
Start at outer edge with strawberries, then bananas, peaches and pineapple.
In each half of pineapple, place a cherry. End with orange slices and place a large cherry in center. Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Cream together oatmeal and hot water and let stand 20 minutes. Mix Crisco, sugar, brown sugar, eggs and vanilla and add oatmeal, flour, nutmeg, salt and soda.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: smores chew
directions: Put 4 marshmallows and 3 Hershey's Kisses in a bowl. Then put the bowl in the microwave for 16 seconds. Take it out, then put it back in for 16 more seconds. Then take it out and mix it with a spoon and spread on graham cracker with a knife and then eat it. Just a snack!

title: potato stuffed apples
directions: Mix together mashed sweet potatoes, cream and egg yolk.
Add stiffly beaten egg white.
Fill apples with this mixture.
Place in pan with a little water and bake at 350° about 45 minutes or until apples are tender.

title: strawberry nut bread
directions: Cream together margarine, sugar, vanilla and lemon juice.
Add eggs.
Beat well.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Mix jam and sour cream.
Add dry mixture and jam mixture to creamed mixture alternately.
Beat until well combined, stir in nuts.
Bake in 2 greased and floured loaf pans for 1 hour at 350° until toothpick in center comes out clean.
Cool pans 10 minutes before removing bread.
Cool loaves completely.
Wrap in foil and freeze.
Thaw to serve.
Freezing seems to improve the taste and slicing although it's not necessary.
This recipe is well worth the time involved and always sells great at bake sales.

title: party crabmeat salad
directions: Soften gelatin in cold water, dissolving over hot water, cool to lukewarm.
Add lemon juice, salt, pepper and mayonnaise.
In bowl mix egg, celery, pickle and crabmeat, then add gelatin mixture.
Pour into individual molds and chill.

title: christmas pickles
directions: Mix all ingredients together (no cook).
Drain Kroger brand dill kosher pickles.
Quarter lengthwise.
Cut off stems.
Layer in same jar with alternate sugar mixture.
Put top on.
Let set in refrigerator 24 hours before using.

title: fruitcake cookies
directions: In a large mixing bowl cream the butter, shortening and brown sugar.
Add eggs one at a time beating well after each addition. Beat in vanilla. Combine flour, baking powder and salt and gradually add to the creamed mixture.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Shape into three 10 inch rolls. Wrap in plastic wrap.
Refrigerate for two hours or until firm.
Unwrap and cut into 1/4 inch slices.
Place 2 inches apart on ungreased baking sheets and bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes or until golden brown. Remove to wire racks to cool. Makes 7 dozen.

title: quick quiche
directions: Mix all ingredients; pour in uncooked pie shells. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: santa fe salad
directions: Heat oil in large skillet over medium-high heat.
Add green peppers and onions.
Cook until tender-crisp.
Add salsa, beans, corn and rice.
Cook until thoroughly heated.
For each serving, place 1 cup lettuce on serving plate.
Surround lettuce with tortilla chips.
Top with warm vegetable mixture.
Sprinkle 1/4 cup cheese evenly on top of each serving.
Garnish with sour cream. Yields 6 servings.

title: "eagle brand milk" chocolate cookies
directions: Melt chocolate and butter over double boiler.
Remove from heat.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet.
Bake 13 1/2 minutes at 325° (very important about time).
Cookies will remain same size as dropped on sheet.

title: texas taters
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except corn flakes and margarine. Use 3/4 of melted margarine and pour into bottom of 13 x 9-inch dish.
Add ingredients to dish, then mix the remainder of margarine with the corn flakes.
Sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pork chops first class
directions: Make mixture of flour, salt, pepper and sage to taste.
Roll pork chops in this mixture and brown in oil.
After browning place the pork chops in a covered baking dish.
To the pan drippings add several tbsp of the flour mixture; brown the flour mixture and add can of onion soup and one can water.
Bring to boil.
Pour over pork chops, then bake at 325° for one hour.
When done you have a delicious gravy for potatoes or rice.

title: ma's syrup
directions: Place all ingredients in a saucepan.
Boil 3 minutes.
Makes 2 cups.

title: easy bake chicken breasts
directions: Arrange breasts
in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.	Place a slice of cheese on each chicken breast; layer sliced mushrooms over cheese.
Combine soup and wine; pour over mushrooms.
Top with dressing
and
margarine.
Bake
for 45 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: chocolate chip pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs in mixer bowl until light and fluffy.
Add sugar, flour, butter, chocolate chips, pecans, salt, lemon juice and corn syrup.
Beat well.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until golden
and set.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix together and press into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 3 minutes at 350°.

title: cheese ball
directions: Form into a ball and roll in nuts.
Wrap in waxed paper and refrigerate.

title: lemon meringue pie
directions: In bowl, mix together 1 cup sugar and cornstarch.
Stir in water until smooth.
Stir in egg yolks.
Stirring constantly, bring to boil over medium heat and boil 1 minute.
Remove from heat; stir in lemon rind, lemon juice and margarine.
Cool.
Pour into baked pie shell.

title: pumpkin pecan muffins
directions: Mix eggs, pumpkin, sugar, buttermilk, pecans or raisins.
Beat eggs.
Add rest of moist ingredients.
Stir in dry ingredients just until moistened.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Layer as follows in a 9 x 13-inch pan: Layer 1, chicken; layer 2, sour cream and chicken soup mixed together.
Mix together crackers and poppy seed and make layer over sour cream and soup mixture.
Fourth layer, drizzle butter over the top.
Can be refrigerated at this point or baked for 30 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: chili beef soup
directions: Cook beef and onion over medium-high heat until meat loses its pink color and onion is soft; spoon off and discard fat.
Reduce heat; stir in broth, tomato puree, chili powder, cumin, oregano, garlic powder, beans and corn.
Cover and simmer for 30 minutes. Salt and pepper to taste.
Top with cheese after serving.
Serves 4.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Reserve chicken broth.
Boil chicken in water with onion until cooked.
Cut cooked chicken into bite size pieces.
Combine soups and sour cream together with chicken.
Moisten stuffing mix with chicken broth and spread over top of chicken mixture.
Bake in heated oven at 350° for approximately 45 minutes to 1 hour. Serves 12.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Measure oats, nuts, vanilla and peanut butter and set aside. Bring sugar, milk, oleo and cocoa to boil.
Boil 1 1/2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat; add oats, nuts, vanilla and peanut butter.
Beat until well blended.
Drop small amounts on greased cookie sheet or wax paper.
Makes about 30 to 32 cookies. Do not use instant oats.

title: sugared pecans
directions: Combine sugar and milk; stir and cook until mixture threads. Pour 3 to 4 teaspoons vanilla over pecans in a pan; sprinkle with salt.
Let vanilla soak in while syrup cooks.
Pour syrup over pecans and stir to coat.
After cool, break up into individual pecans.
These turn very white as they dry.

title: sopaipillas(mexican fried bread)
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt, then add Crisco and milk. Mix and knead the dough well.
The dough doesn't need to rise unless you want it to.

title: sacher torte bites
directions: Cream butter and pudding powder together.
Beat in egg.
Mix in flour.
Shape into small balls.
Roll balls in sugar.
Place on greased baking sheet.
Make a dent in each cookie with your thumb. Bake in a 325° oven for 5 minutes.
Remove cookies from oven and press dent again.
Continue baking for about 10 to 15 minutes. Fill dents with jam.
Melt chocolate chips and butter in small saucepan over low heat.
Glaze top of cooled cookies with melted chocolate.

title: carrot casserole
directions: Cook carrots until tender; add the onion and cook 3 more minutes.
Drain and set aside in a casserole dish.
Make a cream sauce of the flour, margarine, tarragon, salt, mustard and pepper with milk.
Stir and heat until thick, then add cheese.
Mix in until melted.
Pour cream sauce over carrots in casserole; top with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: coconut cookies
directions: Melt butter or oleo in a baking dish.
Sprinkle butter with crushed wafers.
Then layer the chocolate bits, nuts and coconut. Pour the condensed milk over all.
Do not mix!!!
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: game bird pie
directions: Preheat the oven to 400°.
In
a large saute pan, melt the butter. Add the onions and celery; saute for 3 minutes. Add the duck and pheasant and cook until the meat is browned, 6 to 8 minutes. Stir in the flour.
Reduce the heat and cook 5 to 7 minutes, stirring occasionally, until the mixture is bubbling in the center of the pan and a roux has formed.
Stir in the wine and stock.
Bring to a simmer and add the thyme, cinnamon, allspice, nutmeg, bay leaves, salt and pepper. Cook, stirring constantly, for 10 to 15 minutes.
Pour in the pie crust and top with top crust.
Crimp the edges with fork and cut seam so steam can escape.
Bake 50 to 60 minutes or until the juices are bubbling up through the middle of the pie. Remove from oven and cool 10 to 15 minutes before cutting.

title: schinken flecken
directions: Cook noodles; fry together ham, onion and green pepper.
To noodles and ham mixture, add soup, cheese (reserve some to sprinkle on top), brown sugar, water, mushrooms, salt and pepper. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: blender spicy apple jam
directions: First, prepare the fruit.
Peel, cut in eighths and core about 3 pounds fully ripe apples.
Place 1/4 of the apples and 1/2 cup water in electric blender.
Blend at high speed about 15 seconds. Repeat with remaining apples and water.
Measure 5 cups into very large saucepan.
